title: grasshopper pie
directions: Combine chocolate wafer crumbs and melted butter.
Press onto sides and bottom of a nine-inch pie plate.
Chill.
Heat milk in top of a double boiler over boiling water.
Add marshmallows; stir until melted.
Cool thoroughly.
Combine whipped cream, creme de menthe and creme de cacao.
Fold in cooled marshmallow mixture. Add filling into chilled crumb crust and chill until firm.

title: plain cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add one egg at a time.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Gradually add flour and milk.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Start in a cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Clean, cut and cook carrots until tender.
Drain.
Mix soup and broth.
Heat.
Add drained peas and carrots.
Mix chicken and 1 1/2 cups of cheese.
Roll chicken and cheese loosely in each wedge. Place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Pour soup mixture over this.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
When ready, sprinkle rest of cheese over top and melt.

title: clara lee's chocolate candy
directions: Melt milk chocolate in double boiler.
Add white chocolate melt.
Swirling together lightly.
Add peanut butter mixing lightly.
Line a pan with wax paper.
Pour in candy.
Let cool at room temperature.
Cut in pieces.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese until fluffy. Add sugar. Cream until fluffy. Add eggs 1 at a time alternately with 1/2 cup of flour at a time. Mix well after each addition. Add vanilla and salt. Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: texas taco salad
directions: Brown meat and season with salt, pepper and minced onion.
Add beans, rice, peppers and picante sauce.
Mix well.
Stir in cheese and let simmer until cheese is melted.
Serve over tortilla chips.

title: crawfish etoufee
directions: Brown together the bacon fat, onion and okra.
Add tomatoes, black pepper and salt.
Add enough water to simmer.
Cook until tender.
Add boiled crawfish tails or shrimp.
Serve over rice. So yummy!

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and marshmallow cream. Dip fruit of any choice.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer slowly for about 20 minutes. Great for pork and chicken.

title: chocolate cream cheese brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over low heat; set aside.
Beat eggs; gradually add sugar until thick.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt and add to egg mixture.
Stir in melted chocolate, extracts and nuts.
Pour 1/2 batter into a greased 8-inch square baking pan; set aside.

title: everlasting rolls
directions: Mix well together the yeast, sugar and 3 cups flour.
Add hot water and mix until yeast is dissolved.
Add shortening, salt and egg beaten well.
Add remaining flour, 1 cup at a time.
Knead until elastic.

Place in lightly greased bowl, turning to grease all surfaces (or dough may be refrigerated at this point in tightly covered container; when used, knead down, make into rolls while still cold, raise and bake.
Dough may be kept about 1 week).
Allow dough to raise to double; punch down.
Shape into loaves of bread or dinner rolls.
Let rise again; bake at 375° until golden brown and sounds hollow when tapped on top.
Remove from oven and brush top with butter.
Dump from pan immediately and cover with towel until cool.
I wrap in foil, freeze and rewarm the amount I want for each meal.

title: banana loaf
directions: Mix butter, sugar, eggs, salt and soda together.
Add bananas. Mix well.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and bone.
Cut in pieces.
Mix soups, corn, salsa, onion and juice from chicken.
Put in layers in greased casserole dish, starting with chicken, 3 layers ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well; save 1/4 cup oleo for crumbled crackers.
Mix oleo and crackers; sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until lightly browned. Serves 12 to 15.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix water, sugar and cornstarch and bring to a boil until liquid is clear.
Mix in jello; cool.
When cooled, pour over slices peaches that are in the pie shell.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: bacon chicken and rice
directions: Layer 9 x 13-inch pan with uncooked bacon, rice and seasoned chicken.
Mix together soups and water.
Pour over chicken and bake 1 hour at 375°.
Makes 4 servings.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, melt butter or margarine over low heat. Remove from heat; stir in brown sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Add to brown sugar mixture with coconut and walnuts.
Mix well.
Spread in greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes. Cut into bars while warm.
Remove from pan when cool.
Makes 36 bars.

title: cookie-jar sugar cookies
directions: For candy cane or any cut outs.
Heat oven to 375°. Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg; beat until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and grated orange peel; mix thoroughly.
Sift dry ingredients.
Stir into creamed mixture with milk.
Divide dough in half; chill 1 hour.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: vanilla pudding strawberry parfait
directions: Prepare pudding mix according to package instructions.
Cool. Prepare strawberry gelatin according to package instructions, using 1/2 cup less liquid.
Chill.

title: italian chicken over rice
directions: While your rice is cooking, turn on your oven broiler.
Chop up onions and green pepper and mix with 1/2 bottle Italian dressing.
Pour into baking pan and place under broiler.
Cut up chicken into bite size pieces and wash and slice mushrooms.
Add chicken to pan with onions and green pepper and pour in rest of dressing.
Broil about 8 minutes.
Add mushrooms and cayenne pepper; broil about 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes; stir well to coat and broil 5 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice; sprinkle with fresh Parmesan cheese.

title: cream potato cookies
directions: Mix all together and drop by small drops on cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: applesauce fruit cake
directions: Cream butter, adding sugar gradually and blend in applesauce to which soda has been added.
Stir in raisins; add sifted dry ingredients.
Blend until smooth.
Add nut meats and candied fruit.
Turn into a tube pan (sprayed with vegetable oil).
Bake in a moderate 350° oven approximately 45 minutes.

title: wilted lettuce(this is a super dressing for lettuce.)
directions: Fry bacon in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients and stir, mixing thoroughly.
Cut lettuce into bite size pieces in a bowl and pour in mixture.
Toss lightly and serve.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Mix all together.
Makes 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Remove crusts from bread and cut into cubes.

title: vegetable pie
directions: Saute vegetables in butter until crisp, but not soft.
Drain well and add seasonings.
Place tomato slices in bottom of shell. Add veggies; spread mayonnaise and cheese over the top and bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Do not separate rolls.
Slice off tops of rolls.
Mix margarine, mustard, onions and poppy seed.
Spread both insides of rolls with mixture.
Place back in foil pan.
Put ham and cheese in.
Cook in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cut to separate.

title: cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients; beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Pour into well-greased and sizzling hot cast-iron pan or skillet.
Bake until well browned, about 20 minutes.

title: shrimp dip(hot appetizer)
directions: Blend together over medium heat.
Serve hot with crackers or bagel crisps.

title: apple butter
directions: Core and quarter apples; cook with cider in large heavy saucepan until soft, about 30 minutes. Press through food mill. Boil gently 30 minutes; stir often. Stir in sugar and spices. Cook and stir over low heat until sugar dissolves. Boil gently, stirring often, until desired thickness, about 1 hour. Pour into hot 1/2-pint jars; adjust lids. Process in boiling water bath 10 minutes (start counting time after water returns to boil). Makes 8 half pints.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix turkey and rice pilaf.
Make balls size of golf balls. Place in baking dish.
Add enough water to cover balls.
Cover tightly with tinfoil and bake at 350°.
When cooked, you may pour small can tomato sauce over them and put back in oven to warm through.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to instructions on box.
Mix cottage cheese and eggs in small bowl.
Mix Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella cheese in medium bowl.

title: dutch oven potatoes number 2
directions: In a
Dutch
oven,
layer
sliced
potatoes,
cream
of mushroom soup,
Cheddar
cheese soup, small pats of butter and sliced onions.
Add
about
1/2 can of beer for liquid.
Check occasionally for moisture.
Leave some headspace so it doesn't overflow.
You can cook this at 325° in the oven or with coals from the campfire.
Cook until potatoes are tender.

title: blender gazpacho
directions: Puree tomatoes in blender.
Place in large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Ladle the mixture (about 2 cups at a time) into blender and blend until smooth.
Combine with tomato puree. Chill.
Serve very cold.
Sprinkle with garnish.
Serves 8. Contains 91 calories.

title: deer hash, potatoes, and onion casserole
directions: Cook deer meat.
Drain off all juice.
Mix all ingredient together and place in casserole dish.
Cover with tinfoil, and cook until potatoes are tender (not over 15 minutes) at 350 degrees.
Uncover and cook until casserole is brown and almost dried out.

title: quick beef burgundy
directions: Mix all ingredients except onions.
Place in covered casserole and bake 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 325°.
About half hour before done, add drained onions.
Serves 5.

title: gay nell's pea salad
directions: Mix together sugar, vinegar and salt.
Let dissolve.
Then mix with vegetables.
Let stand in refrigerator for 12 hours before serving.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Combine tomatoes, catsup, mustard and garlic and pour over ground beef.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Spoon over hamburger buns.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into flour and sugar mixture.
Add buttermilk. Stir just until dough clings together.
Turn out on floured surface.
Knead a few times.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
Yields 10 biscuits.

title: low calorie coke salad
directions: Bring pineapple to a boil. Add the cherry and lemon jello to dissolve.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 can drink and cherries.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hungarian goulash soup
directions: Brown beef and saute onion, garlic, caraway seed, paprika and cayenne.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add tomatoes and bell pepper and water to equal 3 cups.
Cook until meat and vegetables are tender, for 30 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve hot with dollop of cream.

title: tea cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: fudge cake
directions: Sift together flour and sugar. In a saucepan, bring butter, shortening, water and cocoa to a boil. Pour over sifted flour and sugar while it is hot. Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla. Bake in large pan at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Put the hash browns in a colander to thaw and let the water drain.
In a bowl, mix sour cream, Cheddar cheese and chopped onions.
If you use less potatoes, you also will cut the amount here.
Brown and drain sausage meat.
In a large bowl, put all of the ingredients and mix well.
Put in a casserole and bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: copper pennies(marinated carrots)
directions: Cook carrots tender (do not overcook).
Put into deep dish. Mix all other ingredients well.
Pour over carrots and let set in refrigerator before serving.
Will keep indefinitely or until they are all gone!

title: oreo frozen delight
directions: Pat cookie and butter mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan, buttered.
Soften ice cream and spoon on Oreo crust.
Place in freezer.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Mix all together and pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: rice cheese balls
directions: In medium bowl, combine rice, cheese, eggs, salt and 1/4 cup bread crumbs.
With hands, shape teaspoonfuls into balls.
Coat with remaining bread crumbs.
Heat salad oil to 370°.
Fry balls until golden brown.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat with spoon.
Drop batter by teaspoons (or smaller) into heating salted water.
Cook about 10 minutes.
Drain.

title: strawberry romanoff(for 2)
directions: Mix all ingredients with slightly softened ice cream.
Divide and place mixture in 2 red wine or balloon glasses.
Garnish with whipped cream and whole or split strawberries.

title: super cinnamon rolls
directions: Soak yeast in warm water.
Add buttermilk, sugar, salt, shortening, eggs, flour and soda.
Roll out and spread with butter, cinnamon and brown sugar.
Let rise until light and bake at 375°.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: tomato beef salad canton
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions, rinse, drain and set aside.
Drain tomatoes, reserving 1/4 cup of juice, vinegar, oil and soy sauce.
In a large bowl, place pasta shells, tomatoes, sliced steak, sliced onions and parsley.
Pour sauces over, then toss well to completely coat.
Serve chilled or at room temperature.
Garnish with sesame seed, if desired.
For a spicier salad, add a few drops of pepper sauce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: italian potato wedges
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cut each potato into 8 wedges.
Rinse in cold water.
Drain.
In a large bowl, combine remaining ingredients until well blended.
Add potatoes.
Toss to coat well. Place potatoes on an ungreased jelly roll pan.
Bake 40 minutes or until potatoes are golden brown and tender, stirring occasionally.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, Karo, milk and salt.
Cook, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Continue cooking without stirring until candy forms soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat, add margarine and let candy cool.
When lukewarm, add vanilla and beat until thick and creamy.
When candy holds shape when dropped from a spoon, add nuts.
Pour into a buttered dish.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well.
Form into small balls.
Press with fork tines into X's.
Mix sugar and shortening first, add peanut butter, eggs and flour and soda sifted together.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: boiled custard
directions: Mix milk, sugar and salt in large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is almost ready to boil. Add eggs, which have been beaten until foamy throughout.
Continue beating until mixture coats spoon (about 10 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and cool.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Melt chocolate chips over hot water.
Add corn syrup and bourbon.
Combine vanilla wafer crumbs, confectioners sugar and nuts.
Add chocolate mixture (chocolate, corn syrup and bourbon). Let stand 30 minutes.
Shape into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar. Let stand in covered container for at least 3 days. Makes 4 dozen.

title: chicken in a nest
directions: Bring to a boil the wine, onion rosemary and basil.
Add chicken, salt and pepper.
Cook until tender, about 60 minutes. Boil spinach.
Put chicken on top of spinach.
Serves 4.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Combine all of the ingredients and put in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Top with 2 to 3 slices of bread, cut in cubes and soaked in 3 tablespoons of melted butter.

title: low calorie salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O and cool until slightly thick.
Gently fold in other ingredients.
Pour into oblong dish and chill until set.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Mix and freeze. Will serve 4 people.

title: eire-koekjes (egg cookies)
directions: Beat eggs and sugar 10 to 15 minutes until thick.
Add salt and sift flour over this.
Fold in carefully.
Grease and flour cookie sheet.
Drop cookies several inches apart.
Bake at 350°. Keep them light of color.

title: blueberry crumb cake
directions: Cream together with a fork the melted oleo and dry ingredients. Add beaten eggs.
Mixture should be lumpy.
Lightly pat half of the mixture into bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour in fruit filling.
Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture on top.

title: banana jam
directions: Combine all ingredients in large kettle.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Boil rapidly for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat; simmer, stirring constantly, for about 20 minutes or until thick.
Remove from heat and ladle into sterilized glasses or jars immediately.
Cap tightly; invert for a moment.
Process in water bath for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 6 pints.

title: turkey and black bean chili
directions: Heat the oil in a large wide saucepan over medium-low heat. Add the onions, peppers, carrot and garlic and cook, stirring until the vegetables are very tender and the onions are golden, about 8 minutes. Sprinkle with the chili powder and cumin and stir to blend, letting the spices toast for a minute or so. Add the turkey and cook, stirring and breaking up the meat until the turkey loses its pink color, about 5 minutes. Add the beans, broth and tomato paste. Bring to a simmer over medium heat. Reduce the heat and simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally until the liquid has reduced and the chili has thickened, about 1 hour. Correct the seasonings and serve with bowls of toppings. Makes 8 servings.

title: zucchini bread(oven or microwave)
directions: Oven:
Blend all ingredients until moistened.
Beat 1 minute on medium speed.
Grease and flour bottom of loaf pans.
Pour in mixture and bake for 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Loosen edges and remove from pans.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: blackberry jam
directions: Wash fruit thoroughly and crush.
Add lemon juice.
Add grated rind of 1/2 lemon.
Add sugar and mix thoroughly.
Heat rapidly to full, rolling boil.
Stir constantly before and while boiling. Boil hard 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in fruit pectin. Skim and place in jars for storage.

title: party slush punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and freeze in a wide mouth container.
Let thaw 6 hours before serving.
Use plastic wide mouth jugs.
Tint with food coloring.
Pour ginger ale over slush before serving (128 ounces equals 1 gallon).

title: double quick dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; stir in sugar, half of flour and salt.
Beat with a spoon until smooth.
Scrape down sides of bowl; cover with cloth.
Let rise about 30 minutes, until double in bulk.
Grease 12 large muffin cups.
Stir down raised dough. Spoon into muffin cups, 1/2 full.
Let rise for 20 to 30 minutes or until dough reaches tops of muffin cups.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 12 rolls.

title: out-of-this-world salad
directions: Combine tuna, celery and onion.
Toss lightly with dressing. Season to taste.
Chill.
Cut cucumber into tissue thin slices. Line individual salad dishes with cucumber slices.
Fill with tuna mix; garnish with cucumber.
Yields 3 servings.

title: corinne's quick and easy stuffed fish fillets
directions: Assemble by laying onions, mushrooms and bread crumbs on fillets and rolling up.
Close with toothpick.
Bake, basting with dressing, 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: mexican seasoning
directions: Mix all ingredients. Add to your favorite Mexican dishes. Makes great fajitas.

title: snowball cake dessert
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Combine gelatin mixture and boiling water in bowl, stirring until gelatin dissolves.
Add sugar, lemon juice, crushed pineapple and juice; mix well.
Chill for 1 hour or until partially set.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind cranberries, apples and oranges in food grinder with large attachment.
Add sugar and mix well.
Refrigerate.
Do several days before holidays.
Color will get redder; if not red enough for you, add a dash of red food coloring.
Keeps very well and can be done well ahead of time.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add and beat in sugar.
Add and mix in oil, vanilla and zucchini until smooth.
Add and mix in baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon, nuts and flour.
Fill pan 3/4 full. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in greased and floured pan.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Sprinkle nuts in bottom.
Place frozen rolls on top of nuts.
Sprinkle dry pudding over rolls.
Mix sugar and butter together and pour over rolls.
(Sprinkle cinnamon, if desired.)
Cover with a tea towel and let it rise overnight on the counter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool no longer than 5 minutes.
Turn out on a 10-inch cake tray.

title: two step beef goulash
directions: Lightly toss beef with flour.
In Dutch oven, heat oil and brown beef over medium-high heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients and simmer, covered,stirring occasionally, 1 1/2 hours or until beef is tender.
Serve over hot egg noodles.

title: slushy punchfirst tasted at united methodist temple
directions: Freeze the above mixture; will keep several weeks.
Two hours before serving, remove from freezer.
Just before serving, place in a large punch bowl.
Add two 64 oz. bottles of gingerale.
As the punch needs replenishing add more gingerale.
Left over punch may be refrozen for a later party.
Note:
almond flavoring is good instead of bananas; also, punch is good without bananas or flavoring.
Fresh fruit is good and pretty floating on top or frozen strawberries (the kind packaged with sugar and syrup) is good when added.
Serves 50.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cut cooked chicken into cubes.
In
blender, mix oil, vinegar, paprika, salt, dry mustard and green onion.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Mix, cover and refrigerate overnight.
The next day, add celery and eggs to marinated chicken.
Mix well, then add mayonnaise, sour cream and salt.
Mix.
Serve on lettuce.
Top with almonds and sliced stuffed olives.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: *May use 1 1/2 cups of sugar if no brown sugar.

title: hot drink mix
directions: In a bowl, combine all the ingredients and mix well. Store in an airtight container in a cool dry place or up to 6 months. Yield: 5 cups.

title: noodle-rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add angel hair spaghetti. Break spaghetti noodles into 1 1/2-inch pieces before adding to butter. Cook until golden brown, stirring noodles constantly. Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a lightly greased baking dish. Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: candy bar pie
directions: In bowl, combine coconut and butter.
Turn into 9-inch pie plate, pressing onto bottom and sides to form a firm, even crust. Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes or until golden.
Cool thoroughly.
In small pan, melt candy bar over low heat.
Cool to room temperature.
Dissolve coffee in 1 tablespoon hot water; fold into topping.
Fold in melted candy bar. Pile into crust and chill in freezer until ready to serve.
Can freeze overnight, it wil not freeze overnight.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: puppy chow snack
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients in a large bowl. Add Crispix cereal. Pour mixture into trash bag filled with powdered sugar. Mix until coated well.

title: pork fajitas
directions: Slice pork across grain into 1/8-inch strips.
Mix together garlic, oregano, cumin, salt, orange juice, vinegar and hot pepper sauce.
Marinate pork strips in mixture for 10 minutes.
Heat oil in heavy skillet or on griddle until hot.
Stir-fry pork strips, onion and green pepper until pork is no longer pink, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve with flour tortillas, onions, lettuce, sour cream and salsa.

title: cookie sheet apple pie
directions: Place one pie crust on slightly greased cookie sheet or pizza pan.
Place corn flakes on crust, place apples on corn flakes, sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. When cooled, mix maple syrup and powdered sugar together, drizzle over pie.

title: russian strawberry soup
directions: Mix strawberries in blender or chop by hand.
For each cup of volume, add 1 tablespoon Burgundy wine.

title: crawfish pie
directions: Saute onions, garlic, pepper and celery in butter until limp. Add soup, tomato sauce, crawfish and parsley.
Cook slowly for 10 minutes.
Turn off heat and add breadcrumbs, salt and pepper and egg.
Add milk and mix well.
Add 1/2 mixture to uncooked pie shell and cover with other shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: zucchini cakeeverton, missouri
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 c. chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Arrange broccoli and chicken in casserole dish.
Mix the soup, milk, curry powder and lemon juice; pour over the chicken and broccoli.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: doty's make ahead casserole
directions: Cook noodles; rinse and drain several times with hot water and set aside.
Gradually beat sour cream into cream cheese; stir in onion and garlic.
Brown beef lightly.
Stir in tomato sauce and salt and pepper to taste.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer 1/2 noodles, 1/2 sour cream mixture and 1/2 beef mixture.
Repeat layers in same order.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
May be covered with plastic wrap and stored in refrigerator overnight and baked the next day.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: beef and barley soup
directions: In a
heavy 4 to 6-quart pot, put bones, meat, onion, 1 cup carrots,
1 cup celery, bay leaves, parsley, salt, pepper and water.
Bring
to a boil over medium-high heat.
Reduce to low; cover
and simmer for about 2 1/2 hours.
Lift out bones and when cool
enough
to
handle, remove any meat from them. Discard bones and
put
meat back in pot.
Skim fat from surface.
Add tomatoes, barley, carrots and celery.
Partly cover and cook
45 minutes to 1 hour until tender.
Stir in chopped parsley.

title: cafe au lait
directions: Use 1 level teaspoon coffee to each cup.
Grind the coffee finely and prepare as a filtered coffee, using only half the quantity of water.
When filtered twice, pour off the coffee and add an equal amount of freshly scalded milk.

title: fish cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into patties.
Coat with flour. Fry in shortening until brown on both sides.
Makes 12 cakes.

title: popcorn balls
directions: You will also need a medium saucepan, 2 big spoons and a large bowl.

title: hamburger goulash
directions: Brown hamburger meat in a small amount of cooking oil with the chopped onion.
Remove any fat from pan.
Mix the small can of tomato paste with the cup of water.
Stir into the hamburger and onion mixture.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add cooked, drained macaroni; heat well.

title: crab dip with shrimp sauce
directions: Chop crab and mix approximately 3 sticks with cream cheese. Then spread cream cheese on your favorite serving dish. I use a 5 x 5-inch dish.
Take shrimp sauce and pour over cream cheese. Smooth sauce over the entire top of dish. Take the rest of the crab meat and sprinkle over the top.
For best results, refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Add Cheez Whiz to broccoli.
Pour into casserole dish.
Crush Ritz crackers.
Melt butter and add to crackers.
Toss to coat.
Put cracker mix over broccoli.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: crab-potato nibbles
directions: Add instant onion to water called for when preparing potatoes according to package directions, and use 2 tablespoons less milk than directions specify.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder, and pepper.
Add crab meat.
Shape mixture into bite-size balls.
Dip into beaten egg, then roll in crumbs.
Fry in deep hot fat till golden brown, about 1 minute.
Drain.
Makes 36 appetizers.

title: date nut stuffed cheese balls
directions: Stuff 1/2 pecan in each date.
Combine cheese and margarine, blend well.
Stir in flour and paprika; mix well.
Chill dough for 15 minutes.
Put one (1) tsp. dough around each date to form a ball. Place balls two (2) inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Yields four (4) dozen.

title: pork pie
directions: Place the meat in saucepan.
Add water, nutmeg, allspice, salt, pepper and onion.
Cook for 30 minutes over moderate heat; stir often.
Remove from heat; stir it over mashed potatoes.
Mix well.
Cool.
Line pie plate with crust.
Add filling and top crust; vent.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: white chili
directions: Cook chicken breasts, debone, discard fat.
Take chicken broth and combine with all ingredients but chicken.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add shredded chicken.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add 1/2 pound grated Monterey Jack cheese.
Place in bowl.
Sprinkle more cheese.
If desired, add a dollop of sour cream.
Serve with salad and bread.

title: three cheese delight
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Brown beef. Add tomato sauce, sugar, salt, garlic salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheeses (except Parmesan), onion and green pepper.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix together ingredients, except for chocolate chips and paraffin.
Mix the chocolate chips and paraffin together separately; melt.
Dip balls.

title: almond cherry chicken
directions: Dip chicken in buttermilk, then in salted flour.
Saute in hot oil until browned on both sides.
Let chicken drain on paper towels.
Drain oil from skillet; add sugar and cornstarch to skillet.
With wire whisk, stir in cherry juice and almond flavoring.
Cook until thickened.
Place chicken in greased baking dish; pour cherry sauce over chicken.
Sprinkle with almonds and bake in a 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water and salt; drain.
Add corned beef, cheese, soup, milk and onions.
Put in casserole.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: california overnight rolls
directions: *Dry yeast packet can be used, but rolls are not as light.

title: duckling with orange sauce
directions: Thinly peel oranges.
Cut into 1-inch strips, about 1/8-inch wide.
Bring 2 cups water to boiling.
Add orange strips.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes; drain.
Peel and discard white skin of oranges.
Separate oranges into wedges.
Mix with liqueur.
Rinse duckling.
Pat dry.
Reserve giblets and neck.
Discard excess fat.
Sprinkle with salt.
Place about a third of the orange peel inside.
Pierce skin with a fork around legs and lower breast.

title: braunschweiger cheese ball
directions: Let braunschweiger and cream cheese soften at room temperature (keep wrapped).
Mix together in bowl by hand.
Mold into cheese ball shape.
Serve with your favorite crackers.
Tell you friends it's pate and never admit to kids that it's pork liver.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook first 6 ingredients until half done, add frozen broccoli and cauliflower.
Simmer until soft.
Add cream of chicken soup; bring to boil, stirring often.
Add cheese cubes; stir until melted.

title: rum slush
directions: Mix and freeze.
Fill glasses 3/4 full with slush and add sprite or 7-UP; stir.

title: beans
directions: Cook beans with salt, pepper and onion until beans are done. Brown ground meat in skillet, then add spices and tomato sauce. Add the ground meat mixture to beans.
Add sausage and cook 30 minutes.

title: quick chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken, onion and celery.
Debone chicken.
Keep 4 cups of broth from fryer.
Cut tortillas into strips.
Drop strips one at a time into mixture.
Add cream of chicken soup.
Cover and cook on low for 30 minutes.

title: confetti cheese dip
directions: In medium bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat cream cheese and yogurt until well blended.
Stir in soup mix and dill.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Makes 2 cups.
Serve in red or green bell peppers.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and mix well.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Boil hamburger and onion; drain.
Add other ingredients and simmer until thick and set.

title: doug's dare-devil chili
directions: Brown meat and drain off grease.
Add all other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer on low for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve with saltine crackers and a dash of hot sauce.

title: danish apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a bowl, mix together all ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 8-inch square pan. Bake about 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Remove from pan. Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: golden rod salad
directions: Prepare jello following directions on package.
Add carrots and crushed pineapple, using a little bit of pineapple juice.
Let jello set in refrigerator.

title: two-cheese fettuccine primavera
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil in medium saucepan.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Gradually add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Toss hot pasta with sauce and remaining ingredients.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Melt butter and sprinkle vanilla wafer crumbs on top of butter.
Add chocolate chips next, then coconut and pecans. Last, pour milk evenly on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Let stand 24 hours before cutting.
(If doubling recipe, use 9 x 13-inch pan.)

title: lo-cal quiche
directions: Combine tuna, onion and pepper in bottom of greased pie plate. Combine remaining ingredients in blender and blend until mixed. Pour over items in pie plate.
Sprinkle on Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water together and set aside; let cool. Bake cake as directed on package.
When cake is cool, poke holes in it with a fork, then pour Jell-O over cake.
Mix Cool Whip and strawberries together.
Drain strawberries a little; spread over cake.
For best results, use oblong pan.
Refrigerate 4 hours.

title: fiesta surprise buffet serving line
directions: Place each item in separate dishes in order as listed for buffet serving.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Combine with sauce.
Spread 1/3 of meat sauce in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Arrange 4 noodles on sauce.
Layer one cup of cottage cheese.
Spoon 1/2 remaining sauce on cottage cheese.
Arrange 4 noodles on sauce, then 1 cup cottage cheese, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese and remaining sauce.
Top with Parmesan. Cover tightly with plastic wrap.
Microwave at Medium (50% power) for 32 to 35 minutes.
Uncover.
Sprinkle with remaining sauce. Microwave 2 more minutes at 50% power.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn after first 15 minutes.
Let set for a few minutes before serving.

title: peaches-n-cream pie
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and pudding mix; beat for 2 minutes.
Pour in pan (round glass casserole dish works best). Drain peaches; reserve liquid.
Place them over batter.
Mix cream cheese, 1/3 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons reserved peach juice.
Mix 2 minutes.
Pour within 1 inch of edge of batter.
Sprinkle with mixture of 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: whole wheat batter bread
directions: In large bowl dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup water.
Add 1 cup water.
Add brown sugar, 1/2 cup wheat flour, 1 cup white flour, the salt and shortening.
Beat 2 minutes with electric mixer.
With spoon, beat in the other 1/2 cup wheat flour and 1 cup white flour. Scrape batter from sides and bottom of bowl with spatula.
Cover with towel and set in warm place (85°) to rise until double (about 30 minutes).
Grease loaf pan.
Stir down batter.
Pour into loaf pan.
Smooth top with floured hand.
Cover and let rise again. Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: fish sauce
directions: Use as a marinade or a basting sauce.
Great sauce for grilled fish.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Mix butter in large saucepan. Add flour and whisk until smooth. Slowly add milk and cook over medium heat until thick and bubbly. Scoop pulp out of potatoes and mash slightly. Add to thickened milk along with salt, pepper, 1 1/2 cups cheese, 2 tablespoons green onion and 10 slices bacon. Cook until cheese melts. Stir in sour cream and thin if necessary with more milk. Pour into individual bowls. Top with remaining bacon and onion.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat egg yolks.
Stir in Eagle Brand, ReaLemon and food coloring (if desired).
Pour into crust.
Chill thoroughly.
Top with whipped topping.
Garnish as desired. Refrigerate leftovers.
Use only Grade A clean eggs.

title: peroghi(potato dumpling)
directions: Mix flour and salt together; beat eggs and add with enough water to make pliable for rolling as in pie dough.
Roll out to 1/8-inch thickness and cut into 3-inch squares.
For filling, use mashed potatoes with sauted onions and salt and pepper to taste or onions saute in butter and salt and pepper to taste or ground Polish sausage and drained sauerkraut.
Add just enough filling to each square so that when it is folded in half, it can be sealed tightly when sides are pinched together.
Drop into boiling water and boil for 10 minutes.
Serve hot with melted butter over top.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions, adding the 4 tablespoons creme de menthe. Bake and cool. Spread frosting over entire cake. Combine Cool Whip and 6 tablespoons creme de menthe. Spread on top of the frosting. Refrigerate.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix together and press into 9 x 13-inch dish. Bake at 350° until brown.
Cool.

title: breakfast cookies
directions: Combine and mix well the first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoons 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Center should be soft.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook hamburger and onion together until meat is done.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer about 15 or 20 minutes or until zucchini is done.
Use covered skillet at 200°.
Serves 4 to 6 or more.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Raisins or butterscotch morsels may be substituted for chocolate chips.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Beat flour, salt, eggs and milk together.
Chop chilies and add to flour mixture with cheese.
Mix well.
Pour into baking pan (12 x 9-inch) that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake for 60 minutes at 325°.
Pour tomato sauce on top and bake until brown.
Serves 10.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Mix.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: peach chadfonti
directions: Generously butter a shallow 1 1/2 qt baking dish.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Place peaches in dish.
In the blender, blend the remaining ingredients for 2 minutes.
Pour the mixture over the peaches.
Bake in a 375 degree oven for about 45 minutes OR until Chadfonti is golden.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Drain zucchini and pineapple; mix.
Combine rest in order given.
Fold in zucchini and pineapple mixture.
Pour in angel food cake pan or 10-inch Bundt; bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: jambalaya
directions: Fry bell pepper, garlic, onion and smoked sausage all together. Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix tomato sauce and diced tomato with sausage mixture and cook 45 minutes slowly.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Unroll the crescent rolls in the bottom of the pan.
Press perforations together.
Spread the sausage over the crust, then add the shredded cheese.
Mix the eggs, milk and seasonings together, then pour over the casserole. Bake in a preheated 425° oven for 20 minutes or until a knife comes out clean from the center.
Let stand about 5 minutes before cutting to serve.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
While meat mixture is browning, mix chilies, mushroom soup, chicken soup and water in small pan and heat.
In 8 x 8 x 2-inch Pyrex pan, crumble chips for bottom layer.
Add 1/2 meat mixture, then 1/2 soup mixture, then 1/2 grated cheese; repeat layers of chips, meat mixture, soup mixture, cheese.

title: easy corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix corn bread mix, butter, eggs, corns and sour cream.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In a large, heavy saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup, water, butter and salt.
Stir constantly over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until syrup reaches 300° on candy thermometer (hard crack stage).
Stir in peanuts.
Mix soda and vanilla and quickly stir into candy (mixture will foam).
Quickly turn out in greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Cool completely, then break into pieces.
Store airtight in a cool, dry place.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze out water.
Mix all ingredients with drained spinach.
Refrigerate.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Parboil
cabbage
leaves.
Mix
other ingredients using 1/2 of the tomatoes.
Take about 3 tablespoons of mixture, put on a cabbage leaf
and roll up like a roll. Fasten with toothpicks. Put in
a
greased baking dish or pan.
Pour remaining tomatoes over
the
rolls.
Bake,
uncovered, in moderate oven (350° to 375°) for about an hour.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Pinch off small amounts of dough and roll into balls.
Put on cookie sheet and mash top with a fork to flatten.
Bake at 250° to 275° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hawaiian chicken breasts
directions: Marinate chicken in soy sauce.
Place in a baking dish. Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Pour remaining soy sauce over chicken. Bake, uncovered, for 1/2 hour at 350°.
Uncover.
Add pepper and pineapple.
Bake 1/2 hour longer.
Serves 6.

title: waldorf astoria stew
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover tightly and cook 5 hours at 250°.
Don't lift lid.
Do not brown meat.
If desired, may add mushrooms or water chestnuts.

title: fudge
directions: In a large deep pan, melt butter with evaporated milk. Add sugar. Cook on stove at 400°. Stir almost constantly. When it reaches a boil that you can't stir away, time for 9 minutes. Turn heat off. Add chocolate chips and marshmallows; stir until melted. Add chopped pecans last.
Pour into well buttered 10 x 14 dish. Makes 5 pounds.

title: potato croquette
directions: Boil potatoes until soft.
Brown meat with onions, garlic and celery.
Mash potatoes and add to browned ingredients.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix lightly beaten egg yolks to the potato mixture.
Roll into balls 1-inch or more in diameter.
Dip balls in beaten egg whites and then roll in bread crumbs.
Fry the balls in hot oil until nice and brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with sour cream onion soup dip or Hidden Valley dip.

title: low-fat lemon filled pumpkin roll
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg substitute in a large bowl on high until foamy.
Gradually add granulated sugar.
At low speed, add pumpkin, buttermilk and oil.
In a small bowl, combine flour, cinnamon, salt, nutmeg, ginger and baking powder.
Add flour mixture to egg mixture, beat until well blended.
Bake in a 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onions and garlic in olive oil until slightly limp.
Add ground beef and cook until brown (3 to 4 minutes over medium-high heat).
Push meat and onion mixture to one side of pan and add mushrooms (you may need to add a drop of oil).
Saute mushrooms until they begin to soften, and then mix contents of pan together. Season with pepper, paprika and nutmeg.
Add soup (undiluted) and wine.
Simmer for a few minutes.
Add parsley and sour cream just before serving.
(I frequently omit the sour cream!)

title: german corn bread
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Rinse cabbage, cut up in small pieces and place raw pieces in 13 x 9-inch cake pan (1-inch thick layer).
Saute onion, bell pepper and celery until tender; add meat and cook until brown or no longer pink in color.
Add the rest of the ingredients to meat. Stir it well and spread it evenly on top of the raw cabbage.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Take out, stir it up well again and spread it evenly.
Put it back in oven and bake another 30 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except butter.
Put in a casserole dish and dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: stuffed dill pickles
directions: Use long style potato peeler to remove pulp from dills.
Mix cream cheese and Bac*Os together.
Use knife to push cheese mixture into pickles.
Chill, slice and serve.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: In saucepan, combine margarine, season all, Worcestershire sauce and heat until margarine is melted. Combine cereals, pecans, peanuts and pretzels
in a dishpan and pour melted margarine over cereal.
Stir until evenly coated.
Bake in a 250°
oven stirring every 15 minutes for 1 hour.

title: nut crunch wheel
directions: Line 9-inch cake pan with aluminum foil and butter foil on bottom and up the sides. Combine nuts, margarine, sugar and syrup in skillet. Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Boil until mixture turns golden brown, about 5 or 6 minutes. Spread candy in prepared pan and let cool. Remove candy from pan by lifting edges of foil. Peel off foil. Break in pieces or leave in dish until ready to eat.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with large corn chips.

title: mom's spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti in boiling water until done.
Brown ground round in skillet.
Stir in Manwich.
Cook on low heat for 20 minutes.
Drain spaghetti and rinse off with hot water.
Pour in bowl.
Serve with sauce and garlic toast.
Serves 6.

title: marinated cole slaw
directions: Combine all vegetables and toss.
Mix together the dressing and pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Put in a greased casserole dish in order given.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes, covered, and 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add taco seasoning.
Set aside. Warm soup (do not add water) with onion and green chiles.
Put in layers in large, deep casserole and repeat as follows:
tortillas, then soup mixture, then ground beef, then Cheddar cheese.
Repeat twice and end up with tortillas on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with taco sauce and sour cream.

title: fruit salad
directions: Slice bananas and pour pineapple juice over them.
Then drain well and mix with other ingredients.
Chill.

title: chili
directions: In a large Dutch oven, cook the ground meat and chopped onions until meat is brown and onions are tender; drain off fat.
Stir in the undrained beans and tomatoes.
Add chili powder, garlic powder, oregano and pepper.
Bring to boiling and reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, about 1 1/4 hours, or until of desired consistency, stirring occasionally.
Makes 12 (1-cup) servings.

title: canned okra
directions: Cover okra with water in a large pan.
Add salt and vinegar. Bring to a boil.
Put in jars and seal.

title: quick potatoes au gratin
directions: Grease casserole.
Mix first 6 ingredients and spread cornflake mixture on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: sour cream softies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend dry ingredients, add to sugar mixture alternately with sour cream. Drop by rounded teaspoonful on lightly greased cookie sheet.
(You can add 1/2 cup chocolate chips, fruit, raisins or nuts to recipe if desired).
Bake in 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven; cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: margarita pizza
directions: In a small bowl, place garlic, tomatoes, olive oil, salt and pepper.
Thoroughly coat tomatoes.
Place cheese slices over tortillas and place tomatoes on top.
Sprinkle on basil and parmesan.
Place tortillas on a cookie sheet and bake for 8 minutes at 350 degrees.
Cut into wedges and serve.

title: butter nut balls
directions: Beat butter and 10x sugar together.
Add salt, flour and vanilla.
Add nuts and mix well.
Shape dough in 1-inch balls. Bake at 375° on an ungreased cookie sheet for 12 to 14 minutes. Roll in 10x sugar while warm.

title: zucchini apricot jam
directions: Cook zucchini in its own moisture on low heat for 1 hour.
You may need to add a little water.
Add pineapple, lemon juice and Sure-Jell.
Bring to a boil.
Add sugar and boil 6 minutes. Remove from heat and add dry gelatin.
Can as you would any jam.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix 1 stick butter in crumbled cornbread.
Mix cabbage and cornbread (reserve enough cornbread to put on top of casserole) and place in a large casserole dish.
Mix cheese sauce ingredients (all other ingredients) on top of stove until thickened.
Pour over cabbage/cornbread mixture.
Sprinkle reserved cornbread on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and browned on top.

title: homemade fry bread
directions: In skillet, heat 2 inches
of
oil
Mix flour and buttermilk.
Dough may be rolled and cut in 2-inch squares or patted into small pieces.
Drop
into hot oil and fry until golden brown.
Serve
with butter, confectioners sugar, honey or syrup.

title: cake cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cake mix, margarine, egg and milk in mixing bowl.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto baking sheet.
Bake just until cookies start to turn.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: golden puffs
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add oil, milk and egg.
Mix well with a fork.
Drop by teaspoonful into hot oil (375°).
Fry about 3 minutes or until golden.
Drain.
Roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture while still warm.
Just like little doughnut holes! Kids love them!

title: busy day cobbler
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add milk.
Put margarine in bottom of 8 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish and melt in oven.
Pour batter over melted margarine.
Do not stir!
Add 1 quart can of fruit on top of batter.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar on top of fruit. Do not stir!
Bake for 30 minutes or until brown at 350°.
Serve warm.

title: spaghetti and ham and cheese sauce
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Saute onions in butter.
Add flour until butter is soaked up.
Add milk and cheese.
Add ham and stir constantly until sauce starts to thicken.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: chic-olie bake
directions: Combine soup and mayonnaise.
On bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, spread rice or noodles.
Then in this order layer following ingredients:
broccoli, half of the soup and mayonnaise mixture, chicken and other half of soup and mayonnaise mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese and then bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: exotic shish-kebab
directions: Cut the pork into one-inch pieces.
Marinate for 2 or 3 hours in the mixture of oil, wine or juice, molasses soy sauce and garlic.
Stir occasionally.
Set on skewer pieces of pork intersected with pieces of carrots, mushrooms, green pepper, onions and pieces of pineapple.
Cook in oven at 350° (12 minutes for 2 skewers).

title: nelda's cake(never named)
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 cup of the nuts into a greased and floured tube pan.
Cream the butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour and salt.
Stir in vanilla and rest of nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes before turning out.

title: chicken and stuffing bake
directions: Place chicken in shallow baking dish (7 x 11-inch glass).
Top with cheese slices.
Mix soup with sherry; pour over chicken and cheese.
Top with prepared stuffing.
Drizzle melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 1 hour.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Add all ingredients in a slow cooker and cook on high for about 4 hours or you can put it on the stove in a large pot and cook until all of the flavors are blended, about 1 hour.

title: crazy meat balls
directions: Combine first four ingredients in bowl and form into 1-inch balls.
Place these into a 9 x 13-inch pan, then mix the remaining ingredients together and pour over the meatballs.
Bake for 2 hours at 350° uncovered.

title: hot cranberry spice punch
directions: Bring juices and water to a boil in a saucepan.
Add cinnamon, spices and simmer for 3 to 5 minutes.
Press 2 to 3 cloves through rind of each lemon slice.
Ladle punch into mugs, garnish with cinnamon sticks (as stirrers) and lemon slices.
Drop margarine on top at last minute and serve immediately.
Serves 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Add garlic powder to melted margarine.
Set aside.
In bowl, mix bread crumbs, Cheddar cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Dip chicken pieces in melted margarine, then in bread crumb mixture. Place in shallow baking dish.
Drizzle remaining margarine over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: punch slush
directions: Heat 3 cups water to boil.
Dissolve jello and sugar.
Add 3 cups cold water; add juice.
Freeze.
One hour before serving, use potato masher and mash to soften.
Add ginger ale.

title: crisp "n" crunchy turkey
directions: Pound out cutlets.
Pour milk in dish.
Combine cornflakes, flour and ground red pepper in pie plate.
Dip cutlets.
Over medium heat, cook cutlets in oil; brown.
Accompany with okra. Makes 4 servings.

title: joes to go
directions: In a large skillet, cook and stir ground beef and onion until beef is brown; drain.
Add garlic salt, pepper, chili sauce, brown sugar, white vinegar, mustard and tomato sauce.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serves 6 with potato chips and carrot and celery sticks.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, syrup, salt, vanilla and butter. Beat until smooth.
Add pecans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
May cover pie loosely with foil after baking for 30 minutes to prevent pecans from getting too brown.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix together and chill 2 hours.

title: nutty buddy pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and milk. Mix well. Add sugar, peanut butter and Cool Whip. Mix well and pour into pie shells. Drizzle chocolate syrup over pies. Sprinkle peanuts on top of pies. Freeze until ready to eat. Makes 3 pies.

title: chocolate intrigue
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream butter thoroughly and gradually add sugar, creaming until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Combine milk and vanilla.
Add alternately with the dry ingredients, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Blend thoroughly on low speed after each addition.
Pour two-thirds of batter into 10-inch tube pan, greased on the bottom.

title: tart dough
directions: Sift together first 3 ingredients.
Add oleo and eggs.
Add milk if dough is too dry.
Roll or press 1/2 of the dough into ungreased 10 1/2 x 15 1/2 inch pan.
Place filling on top of dough and with remainder of dough roll out and cut into strips and lattice it across the top of filling.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: cookies and cream delight
directions: Dip cookies in milk and make a layer of them in the bottom of a large bowl.
Spoon on a layer of Cool Whip.
Continue layering cookies, dipped in milk, and Cool Whip until you reach the desired level.
Makes a great dish for kids to prepare!!

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix together real well.
Add 1 cup of hot water (mix).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yields one 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.

title: taffy spoof pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, syrup, salt, vanilla and butter.
Fold in cereal.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Costs under 50 cents to serve six delighted people.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Cover with marshmallows.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cookies while you sleep
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add salt and cream of tartar.
Beat well.
Gradually add sugar and beat until stiff.
Add almond extract.
Fold in nuts and chips.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Turn oven heat off and drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Place in oven when heat is off.
Don't peek.
Leave in oven overnight.

title: white cookie frosting
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water until soft-ball stage when tested in cold water.
Pour mixture slowly into stiffly beaten egg whites, beating constantly.
Beat until quite cool.

title: mamaw's bird nest
directions: Spread margarine thinly on both sides of bread.
Make hole in middle of bread big enough to put egg in.
Place in your skillet over medium heat.
Break egg in hole.
When egg is halfway cooked, flip and cook other side.

title: rose's banana nut oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugars and margarine until well blended.
Blend in egg.
Add mashed bananas, extract, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Add flour.
Blend.
Stir in oatmeal and nuts as batter is very thick. Bake at 300° on lightly greased cookie sheets for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: chimmey corner dressing
directions: Beat in blender; shake before serving.

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in shortening. Add seasonings and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes. Add beans.
Pour meat mixture in greased casserole dish. Top with cornbread batter. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to instructions on package.
In a deep pan, layer first crackers, then macaroni, then cheese.
Continue to layer ingredients, ending with cheese on top layer.
Pour milk over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffing for tomatoes
directions: Stuff uncooked tomatoes, pepper or zucchini (or use for meatballs).
Bake in uncovered casserole with oil in bottom, roll peppers in oil to coat.
Bake at 400° covered for 30 minutes.
Then bake at 350° for 30 minutes uncovered.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Cook frozen broccoli according to directions or cook fresh broccoli until tender.
Melt butter, add flour, stirring until smooth.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly until thickened. Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Add drained broccoli.
Heat thoroughly.

title: cherry rex pie
directions: Pour cherry pie filling into a 10 x 8 inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over pie filling.
Sprinkle nuts on top. Pour melted oleo over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: spicy chinese chicken wings
directions: Place wings in a large recloseable plastic bag.
Combine Hoisin sauce, brown sugar, soy sauce, red pepper and garlic in a separate bowl to make marinade.
Pour 2/3 of marinade over wings; toss to coat.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Reserve remaining marinade for basting.

title: lemon brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, Jell-O, eggs and grated lemon rind together. Cook in a 13 x 9-inch pan that has been floured and greased.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Do not overcook.
Prick with a fork and pour a mixture of the lemon juice and powdered sugar over the top.
Cut while still warm in the pan. Store in tight tin after they have cooled.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine, add eggs and dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Chill or make day before.
Drop by teaspoons on foil-lined cookie sheet (foil dull side up) about 12 per pan.
Bake about 10 minutes in 350° oven or until light brown.
Let set about 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Makes about 10 to 12 dozen.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Cool raisins until tender in water, then drain.
Mix sugar, flour and cream together and add the raisins.
Cook 5 minutes. Add egg yolks and cook until thick.
Add vanilla and butter.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue and brown in oven.

title: chicken with spanish rice
directions: In a large, heavy pot, place whole chicken and 4 cups of water; bring to a boil.
Add all other ingredients except oil and rice.
Cook chicken until done.
In separate frypan, heat oil and fry rice.
Add to chicken and continue to cook over medium fire for 20 minutes.
Cover and cook an additional 15 minutes.

title: toll house pie
directions: *If using frozen pie shell, it's necessary to use deep dish style, thawed.
Place on cookie sheet and bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: orange-pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving liquid.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
To the lemon juice, add reserved pineapple juice.
Add sufficient cold water to make 1 cup and add to gelatin.
Add the crushed pineapple, carrot and salt.
Let harden in molds and serve on lettuce.

title: candy bar pie
directions: Crush the candy bars very fine.
Mix with the whipped topping, saving enough to sprinkle on top.
Spoon the mixture into a pie shell and freeze.
Serve with berries on top if desired.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: In 2-quart round casserole pan, mix together raw ground beef, egg, oatmeal, milk, thyme, sage and onions.
Place lid or foil on top.
Bake at 350° until done or 15 to 20 minutes in microwave on High.

title: biscuit pudding
directions: Mix together egg, milk, sugar, vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg. Warm mixture in saucepan.
Place biscuit in 9 x 13-inch pan and pour warmed milk mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Insert toothpick to check for doneness.
Serve warm.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and pour over shredded tortillas in baking dish.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: buttered asparagus
directions: Arrange asparagus in 2 layers in a 9 or 10-inch skillet. Sprinkle with salt and sugar; pour on 1-inch boiling water. Boil, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Cover and cook 7 to 10 minutes longer or until just tender-crisp when tested with a fork.
Carefully lift out asparagus; arrange on serving dish.
Pour melted margarine over asparagus.
Garnish with chopped egg if desired.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Bring to boil margarine and water.
Stir in flour (all at once).
Cool and add eggs, one at a time, stirring with wooden spoon.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch baking dish at 400° for 35 minutes. Mix together pudding mix, milk and cream cheese.
Spread on crust. Top with Cool Whip.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup.

title: tuna-macaroni salad
directions: Cook the macaroni according to directions on package. Rinse in cold water and cool. Toss macaroni and the remaining ingredients slightly, except the salad greens and parsley. Blend mixture well, but avoid making the salad drippy. Place on salad greens and garnish with parsley.

title: sour cream potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, water, salt, pepper and onion; simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Add cream and cook, uncovered, until potatoes are tender, about 5 minutes longer.
Serve garnished with parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate chippers
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together the flour and baking soda. In a mixing bowl, beat the margarine with an electric mixer on medium speed for 30 seconds.
Add sugars.
Beat until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients to mixture, beating until well combined.
Stir in chocolate pieces.
Drop dough from rounded teaspoonful 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Transfer to cooling rack; cool completely.
Set aside.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, egg, milk and Bisquick; beat hard 30 seconds.
Add bananas and nuts.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until toothpick stuck in center comes out clean.
(Crack in top is typical.)
Cool before slicing.

title: tuna charlies
directions: Pour on steak, cover.
Cook 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Serve over rice.

title: punch
directions: Add water, enough to make 1 2/3 to 2 gallons punch.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix hamburg, bread crumbs, onion, egg and parsley.
Make into meatballs.
Brown them and pour off fat.
Stir in soup, water and pickles.
Cover; stir often.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix in blender; chill at least 6 hours before serving.
Great dip for raw vegetables.

title: chicken and cheese
directions: Bake chicken for 30 minutes in oven at 350°.
Mix sour cream, soup and cheese.
Pour fat from chicken.
Sprinkle salt over chicken (just a little).
Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake for 30 more minutes or until bubbly hot (at least 15 minutes).

title: chicken squares
directions: Combine chicken, rice, bread crumbs, celery and pimento.
Add salt and broth to eggs and mix.
Stir into chicken mixture. Place in a greased 9 x 9-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes. Cut into squares.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli, stems too, into bite size pieces.
Place in large serving bowl.
Sprinkle broccoli with bacon, onion and raisins.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Simmer, covered, about 20 minutes.

title: custard pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Prepare pastry.
Beat eggs slightly with hand beater.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour filling in pastry lined pie plate.
Place in oven and bake 20 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Bake until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean, 15 to 20 minutes longer.
Refrigerate pie.
Serve chilled.
Serves 8.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Spread chicken in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Blend soups and sour cream in a small bowl.
Spread over chicken. Cover with stuffing mix.
Drizzle with butter and chicken broth. Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: rhubarb pie custard
directions: Beat together and combine with rhubarb.
Bake in an unbaked pie shell for 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce to 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until almost set.

title: grandma arbuckle's cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm milk.
Mix sugar, eggs, vanilla, salt and butter.
Add milk.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough (not too stiff).
Butter dough; let rise for 45 minutes, or until double in size.
Roll out; spread melted butter and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Roll up; cut 1-inch long.
Put in greased baking dish; let rise for 45 minutes, until double in size.
Bake at 370° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes; drain and mash.
Add cream cheese, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Put in greased baking dish.
Top with pats of butter.
Cover; refrigerate.
Before serving, sprinkle paprika and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: thousand island chicken
directions: Wash and dry breasts.
Dip in Thousand Island dressing on all sides.
Dip into bread crumbs.
Lightly fry in oil until brown. Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and whole eggs.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients, nuts and vanilla. Pour into 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop onto cookie sheet.
Mark with a fork.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and add next 6 ingredients.
Mix cottage cheese and next 4 ingredients.
Cook 10 ounces of noodles.

title: peanut blossom cookies
directions: In large bowl, beat butter and peanut butter with mixer on medium for 30 seconds.
Add both sugars; beat until fluffy.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat well.
In medium bowl, stir flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Add to peanut butter mixture; mix well on low.
If necessary, cover and chill 1 hour.

title: almond crescents(cookies)
directions: Cream oleo, powdered sugar, sugar and almond.
Add flour gradually.
Add nuts.
Roll cookies the size of finger and slightly bend in half.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
When cool, roll in powdered sugar.

title: my best chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Beat butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla until creamy. Gradually mix in flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoon about 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until bottoms are browned. Makes 5 dozen.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Cook
broccoli	and
drain.
Saute
onion in margarine. Add flour and
stir;
add water and stir until thick.
Stir in Cheez Whiz.
Take
this
off
stove and add eggs, well beaten. Pour into casserole	dish.
Sprinkle cornflake crumbs and dot with margarine.	Cook at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Melt margarine;
add
cocoa
and
stir.
Add
sugar and milk. Bring
to
a
hard	boil.
Boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cut off heat.	Stir in Crisco and vanilla.
Spoon on yellow layer cake (thin layers, 6 to 8 layers).
Icing will run off, spoon it back on.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip, cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme and whip until creamy.
Add fruit and fruit filling; mix well.
Serve chilled.
Makes a very colorful dessert.

title: hummus(chickpea dip)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a food processor fitted with a steel blade.
Process until smooth.
Add garlic, salt and cumin. Add more lemon juice to taste if desired.
Serve as a dip with pita bread or raw vegetables.

title: broccoli with rice
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter until clear.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix broccoli, cheese, soup and vegetables.
Add rice and mix well.
Season to taste.
Place in greased casserole dish, top with bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream butter with 2 cups sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Gradually add cocoa, flour, coconut, vanilla and pecans.
Beat after each addition.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate shot cookies(makes 3 dozen)
directions: Cream butter, add sugar gradually and cream until fluffy.
Add vanilla, flour sifted with soda and rolled oats.
Mix thoroughly. Chill dough in refrigerator for about one-half hour.
Shape into rolls 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Coat each roll of dough with chocolate shot.
Slice about 3/8-inch thick and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in a slow oven (325°) for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put 1/2 cup water in pan and start it to boil.
Add sugar and vanilla; boil until it spins a thread.
Dump peanuts in and cook slowly until peanuts start popping. Remove from heat and add soda. Pour in large greased pan and cool.
Break into pieces when cool.

title: chicken and spaghetti casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add enough broth to make a thin mixture. Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: creole squash
directions: Slice squash thin and arrange in buttered casserole.
Add thinly sliced onions.
Add mustard and seasoning to tomatoes. Pour over squash and onions.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cover with grated cheese.

title: mrs. childress' chili sauce
directions: Cut up tomatoes and mix with onion and bell pepper.
Add all spices and mix.
Add vinegar and sugar.
Boil 1 1/2 hours or until sort of thick.
Put into jars and seal.
Makes several pints.

title: popovers
directions: Mix and beat all together just until smooth.
Overbeating will reduce volume.
Fill greased muffin tins 3/4 full or custard cups half full.
Bake at 400° for 30 or 40 minutes.
Great with roast beef!

title: banana rum fizzes
directions: In a blender, blend ice cream and chopped banana until smooth, but still thick and pour into 2 chilled stemmed glasses.
Add creme de cacao, rum and club soda and garnish with banana slices. Makes 2 drinks.

title: fettuccine lucassa
directions: Saute diced Canadian bacon in olive oil until lightly browned. Add scallops and cook just until tender, about 2 minutes.
Remove bacon and scallops from pan with slotted spoon; set aside, reserve liquid.
Add 1 tablespoon butter to some skillet, swirl until melted.
Add flour and cook gently until bubbling.
Remove from heat.
Add enough low-fat milk to reserve scallop liquid to make 1 1/2 cups.
Pour slowly into the roux, stirring constantly, to prevent lumps.
Return to heat and cook until sauce thickens.
Add wine and continue simmering for 10 minutes.
Sauce will be fairly thin.
Add bacon, shallots and scallops; heat gently.
Season with salt to taste.
Pour over cooked fettuccine and toss.
Serve on warm plates.
Serve with cooked broccoli flowerets, garlic bread and chilled white wine.
A truly delectable meal.

title: ricotta cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
In separate bowl, mix Ricotta cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Place mixture on top of cake mixture and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar before serving.

title: colorful rice salad
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients and stir well.
Add mayo, tossing until well mixed.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Serve on lettuce leaves and garnish with cherry tomatoes, if desired.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: cinnamon rolls(sticky buns)
directions: Mix together milk and butter.
Add sugar and eggs and mix well.
Add flour and salt and mix.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water and add.
Mix together.
Combine oleo, brown sugar and 1/2 cup water and line bottom of pan.
Add roll dough and bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Layer rhubarb, sugar, Jell-O, marshmallows in pan; mix cake mix as directed and pour over rhubarb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes.
Turn out of pan leaving upside down.
Serve with whip cream or ice cream.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix together and cover.
Best if prepared and let set overnight.
Perfect with fried chicken.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Cool and split layers to make 4.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except crumbs.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Combine ingredients in a small bowl.
Pour over beef or chicken.
Refrigerate, covered, for 1 to 2 days.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs with a fork.
Add all the other ingredients.
Pour in pie shell and bake at 350°.

title: fritter-fried okra
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a medium bowl.
Combine eggs and milk; add to dry ingredients and mix until smooth.
Stir in sliced okra.
Carefully drop batter by tablespoonfuls into deep hot oil (375°); cook only a few at a time, turning once.
Fry 2 to 3 minutes or until fritters are golden brown.
Drain well on paper towels.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake the yellow cake mix as instructed on box.
Let cool. Crumble half the cake into bite size pieces and drop into punch bowl.
Mix the vanilla pudding as instructed on box.
Let set up. Then put half of pudding on the cake pieces.
Then put half the cherry pie filling.
Then put half the pineapple.
Then put half the bananas.
Then half the nuts.
Spread 1/2 of Cool Whip on top of it.
Repeat steps starting with cake and top with rest of Cool Whip.
Spread a few nuts on top.
Let set overnight to make cake moist.
Yield:
1 full punch bowl cake.

title: cabbage rolls with turkey stuffing
directions: Remove twelve large leaves of cabbage; cut out tough inner part of rib.
Blanch each leaf one minute, until pliable.
Combine ground turkey, rice, egg, stock, sage and parsley.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Divide turkey mixture into twelve parts and form into oval lumps about four inches long.
Place an oval at stem end of baking dish.
Continue until all twelve rolls are in one layer in baking dish.
Pour 1/2 cup stock over all.
Lay strips of bacon over top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, basting twice and turning oven temperature down to 350° if bacon browns too quickly.
Yield: 6 servings.
Carbohydrate 15 g, protein 20 g, fat 11 g, calories 234.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage until brown; drain.
Separate rolls; place on ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points to center.
Press to form crust.
Spread sausage, potatoes and cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper and pour into crust.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: microwave homestyle pot roast
directions: Cut 1-inch strip from open end of large plastic cooking bag to use as closure.
Place roast in cooking bag; set bag in 12 x 8-inch glass baking dish.
Mix together tomato sauce, bouillon granules and salt; pour over roast in bag.
Gather end of bag; tie loosely with plastic strip, leaving small space for steam to escape.
Microwave at High power 10 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn every 5 minutes.
Microwave at Medium power 25 minutes. Meanwhile, cut carrots crosswise into 1-inch lengths; cut any thick pieces in half lengthwise.
Cut onion into 8 even wedges. Cut potato into 1/2-inch cubes.

title: corn chowder
directions: Takes about 1/2 hour to make. Serves 6.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare a yellow cake mix and instant pudding according to directions on package.
Into a large punch bowl, arrange in layers as follows: cake, pineapple, pudding, cherry pie filling and whipped topping, then repeat layers.
Top with nuts.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Brown sausage; drain grease and cool.
Mix all ingredients well (it's easier to use your hands).
Roll into small balls, about 1 inch in diameter.
Place on cookie sheet, about 3 inches apart.
Bake at 400° about 12 minutes.
To reheat, heat about 8 minutes at 325°.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Test at 45 minutes.
Use 1 (2 pound) loaf pan or 2 (1 pound) pans.
Frost with thin cream cheese frosting, if desired.

title: creamed corn
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Boil then simmer for 5 minutes. Blend butter, flour, and some sauce from corn mixture, and add all to the corn mixture; mix well.
Cook and stir until thickened.

title: taco - seasoning mix(microwave cooking)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl until well blended. Store in an airtight container for future use. Use this instead of a package of commercial taco-seasoning mix.

title: sausage delight
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Boil carrots, cut in small dices until tender.
Boil rice while browning sausage.
Mix all 3 ingredients together.
Toss lightly.
Season to taste.

title: derby casserole
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Blend in flour; add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted.

title: dirty rice
directions: Brown beef in large skillet.
Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Cook until rice is done, approximately 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add vanilla. Mix in flour, sifted with salt and baking powder.
Refrigerate one hour.
Roll out and cut.
Bake at 375°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts about 30 minutes.
Mix soups and sour cream.
Add to chicken and mix well.
