Place in casserole dish. Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Melt oleo and pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: scottish oat cakes
directions: Add soda to boiling water.
Let stand until cool.
Mix together flour, baking powder, salt, bran flakes, rolled oats and sugar.
Roll out thin on a floured board.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes on bottom shelf, then 5 minutes on top shelf.

title: mandel bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and dry ingredients.
Mix by hand.
Form dough into strips on greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Melt chocolate and drizzle on strips.
Cut widthwise and brown if desired.

title: chicken enchiladas au gratin
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Mix well.
Heat until well blended.
Layer tortillas, chicken, onion slices, cheese and sour cream sauce alternately in a greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish until all ingredients are used.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: pork chops italian
directions: Brown pork chops lightly.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place pork chops in baking pan and cover with combined corn, peppers, onions, bread crumbs, egg, butter, salt and pepper.
Add just enough water to cover the bottom of the pan.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: dump cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Get a baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Dump and spread in pie filling.
Dump the dry cake mix evenly over pie filling.
Dump pecans evenly over cake mix.
Pour butter over all.
Bake 35 minutes.
Set 15 minutes.
Spoon out hot and put over vanilla ice cream, or eat plain.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans and mix in milk, soup, pepper and 1/2 can of onions.
Pour into a casserole dish and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: orange slush
directions: Put in freezer until slushy.
Serve with half 7-Up and half slush in a pretty goblet.

title: bagels
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine yeast and 1 3/4 cups of the flour. Combine water, sugar and salt.
Add to yeast mixture.
Beat at low speed of mixer.
Beat 3 minutes by hand.
Stir in enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn out on floured surface and knead until smooth, 5 to 8 minutes.
Cover; let rest 15 minutes.
Cut into 12 portions.
Shape into small balls.
Punch a hole in center of each with a floured finger, working each bagel into shape. Cover; let rise 20 minutes.

title: homemade strawberry ice cream
directions: Sprinkle strawberries with half the sugar. Mix creams, remaining sugar, extracts and salt. Freeze until partially frozen. Stir in sugared fruit and continue to freeze.

title: apple carrot muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
In a small bowl, beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Add dry ingredients along with apples and carrots and mix well.
Spoon into paper liners in a muffin pan; fill 2/3 full.
Bake in 325° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Makes about 16
muffins.

title: sour cream blueberry muffins
directions: If blueberries are frozen, do not thaw before adding to batter.
In bowl, combine biscuit mix and 3/4 c. sugar.
In another bowl, combine the eggs and sour cream; stir into the dry ingredients; just until combined.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill greased muffin pan, 3/4 full.
Sprinkle with remaining sugar. Bake at 375 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes before removing from pan to cooling rack.

title: fish dressing
directions: Mix ingredients and add ketchup until a light pink or to desired taste.
This is wonderful with fried fish and French fries.

title: scandinavian fruit compote
directions: Combine tapioca, sugar and water in saucepan.
Heat, stirring constantly, to a full boil.
Add to orange juice concentrate, which has been poured into a medium bowl.
Stir in pineapple chunks and juice.
Chill at least four hours or overnight.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown beef in large pan; drain.
Add tomatoes, cut in large pieces.
Add remaining ingredients, except beans.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add beans and simmer an additional 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: crispy onion rings
directions: Soak onions in bowl of ice water about 2 hours.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add 1 1/2 cups ice water, all at once, and whisk until smooth.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before using.
Heat oil to 375°.
Place all onions in batter and stir to coat.

title: ma's blackberry jam
directions: Boil the berries and vinegar 1 minute, then add the sugar. Boil 20 minutes. Cool, then put in jars or put in jars hot.

title: gooey butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In a medium bowl, cream together the cream cheese and butter.
Stir in the egg and vanilla.
Add cake mix, and stir until well blended.
Roll into 1 inch balls and roll the balls in the confectioners sugar.
Place 1 inch apart onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 13 minutes in the preheated oven.
Remove from baking sheets to cool on wire racks. Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: e. b. double del. cookie bars
directions: Melt butter in pan at 350°.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter, covering bottom of pan.
Spread Eagle Brand over crumbs.
Top with chocolate chips and peanut butter chips.
Press firmly.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Set aside. Beat shortening until creamy and add sugar.
Continue beating until fluffy and light. Add eggs and beat well.

title: banana punch
directions: Bring sugar and 6 cups water to boil. Cool and add orange juice, 3 cups water, pineapple juice and lemon juice. Mash bananas in blender; add to sugar. Freeze overnight. Take out 1 hour before serving. Spoon out like slush and mix with equal parts of ginger ale.

title: broccoli cheese potato topper
directions: In medium saucepan mix soup sour cream, mustard and broccoli. Over medium heat, heat through, stirring occasionally.
Serve over potatoes.
If desired, garnish with red pepper.

title: oven steak
directions: Cut steak in strips or bite size pieces.
Brown in butter on both sides, using large pan.
Place in roaster pan with tight fitting lid.
In pan where steak was browned, add catsup, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar, salt, water and onion.
Let come to boil and pour over steak.
Cover and bake for 2 hours at 325°.

title: ham and yellow pea or lentil soup
directions: Wash and sort peas.
Place in a large kettle to start cooking as they need a little longer to cook than vegetables, 35 to 40 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until done.

title: microwave chocolate pudding(low-calorie, low-fat)
directions: In microwave dish, place first 5 ingredients; add a small amount of milk and mix well.
Add remaining milk; cook in microwave on High power (100%) 3 minutes, stir well.
Cook 3 more minutes.
Remove from oven; add margarine and vanilla.
Stir well. Refrigerate to chill.
Makes 5 servings.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix all together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Put 1 slice of Swiss cheese on top of each piece of chicken. Mix soup with wine; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing over that, then melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, uncovered.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix together ingredients as listed.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: crabmeat nachos
directions: Chop or shred crabmeat into small pieces and arrange on chips. Put on a cookie sheet.
Sprinkle cheese and paprika on top of each chip.
Bake 10 minutes on 350°.

title: orange drop cookies
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Drop by heaping teaspoons on a cookie sheet.
Bake in a preheated 350 degree oven for 10 minutes. May be iced.

title: super bowl fruit supreme
directions: Combine all together; mix well.
Chill about 1 hour and serve.

title: easy fudge
directions: Butter a square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Heat milk and chocolate chips over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture is smooth. Remove from heat. Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Spread evenly into prepared pan. Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into small squares.

title: peppermint brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine.
Stir in sugar and extract.
Cut into small squares.
Freeze well!

title: m&m ripple cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease
and
flour Bundt pan.
Stir together flour, baking powder
and salt; reserve.
Beat sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla
in
large
bowl.	Beat
in
reserved flour mixture alternately with
milk
on low speed.
Reserve 2 cups batter;
pour remaining batter into pan.
Carefully spoon chopped candies in ring shape in center of cake (avoid edges). Cover with reserved batter.
Bake
until wooden pick comes out clean, 1 hour and 10
minutes.
Cool
20 minutes;
remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Spread
with
glaze,
allowing some to drizzle down side.	Decorate with 1/4 cup whole candies.

title: chocolate peanut butter milk
directions: Combine peanut butter and chocolate syrup.
Stir until well blended.
Slowly add milk, stirring as you add.
Serve cold. Makes 3 3/4 cups.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook all ingredients except chicken and spaghetti in broth until tender.
Cook 1 box spaghetti; drain and add this and chopped chicken to other ingredients.
Cook over low heat (simmer) for about 25 to 30 minutes.
Pour in baking dish, grate 3/4 to 1 pound Longhorn cheese over top and place in oven just until cheese melts and bubbles.
Stuffed olives may be sliced on top if you like it to look pretty.
Makes about 6 quarts.
Freezes real well. Serve this with green salad, garlic French bread and light dessert.
You have a Great Meal!

title: florentine shells
directions: Cook noodles according to package.
Saute onion and garlic powder in margarine until tender.
Combine onion, spinach, cheeses, eggs, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Fill shells with mixture.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over shells.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese.
Makes 6 to 7 servings.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Cook and stir beef and onions until brown; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix.
Spread in greased pie plate.
Top with chilies. Beat milk, Bisquick and eggs until smooth.
Pour into pie plate. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and
cheese.
Bake until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes.
Top with sour cream, tomatoes, lettuce and cheese.

title: see's fudge
directions: Mix butter, sugar, salt and milk together in a large pot and bring to a boil, 245° on candy thermometer. Remove from heat and add marshmallow from the jar. Add the chocolate chips. Blend fast and well by whipping it. Add the vanilla and walnuts. Makes about 4 pounds; fills two 8-inch square pans.

title: skillet summer squash
directions: Choose young tender squash; it should be easily pierced with thumbnail.
Wash thoroughly and cut into half-inch crosswise slices, without removing skin.
Place butter in skillet.
Melt and add squash, onions, bell pepper, salt and pepper.
Cover tightly and cook moderately fast for 2 minutes.
Check to see if enough liquid has formed to keep from sticking.
If so, stir and cover; continue cooking for 4 minutes.
Uncover and continue cooking until most of liquid has evaporated, stirring occasionally to keep from sticking.
You may use all yellow squash.

title: roast-on-the-grill
directions: Spread soups over meat.
Top with chips, crushed.
Wrap in foil.
Cook for 1 hour.
Baste occasionally with sauce.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pat into uniform flat cakes.
Fry in skillet with oil until golden brown on both sides.
Serves 10.

title: biscochitos
directions: Sift together dry ingredients. Cream together sugar, shortening, and anise seeds until fluffy. Beat in eggs one at a time. Mix in flour mixture and brandy. Turn dough out onto floured board and roll to 1/2 to 1/4 inch thickness. Cut into shapes (The fleur-de-lis is traditional). Dust with sugar and cinnamon mix. Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: spanish noodles
directions: Spray a nonstick pan with Pam.
Combine turkey, onion and pepper.
Cook in pan until tender.
Add paste and tomatoes.
Let simmer 1 hour.
Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain noodles.
Pour turkey mixture over noodles.
Mix lightly, not to break noodles.
Serve hot.

title: cider pie
directions: Boil until it thickens (first 5 ingredients), stirring with wire whisk.
Pour into prebaked pie shell.
Refrigerate until firm. Serve with whipped cream.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Beat all ingredients well.
Bake in greased pan at 400° for 10 minutes on bottom rack and 10 minutes on top rack.
Brush with margarine.

title: savory baked chicken
directions: Season fryers as desired.
Arrange in baking pan.
In saucepan melt margarine and saute onions and garlic until tender.
Add Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and simmer 5 to 10 minutes. Spoon mixture over chicken and bake at 350°, covered, for about 35 minutes.
Uncover and continue baking 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Remove from oven.
Drain off liquid and thicken for a savory gravy.

title: punch bowl dessert
directions: Prepare 2 (8-inch) round cakes according to cake mix directions.
Cool.
Place 1 cake into punch bowl.
Prepare pudding as package directs and cover 1st cake with 1/2 pudding, then 1/2 cherry pie filling, 1/2 fruit cocktail, 1/2 pineapple chunks, 1/2 coconut and 1/2 Cool Whip topping.
Sprinkle 1/2 chopped nuts over and repeat 2nd cake layer as before.
Can make 8 to 24 hours before serving.

title: peaches and cream cheesecake
directions: Drain peach slices, reserving 3 tablespoons juice.
Combine flour, salt, butter, milk, baking powder, vanilla pudding mix and egg.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed with electric mixer.
Pour into ungreased 9-inch pie plate.
Arrange peach slices over batter.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and reserved peach juice.
Spoon mix over peaches, leaving 1-inch margin around side of dish.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and mix with a large wooden spoon.
(Do not use electric mixer.)
Spoon into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Combine chocolate and milk; cook over low heat until smooth. Add sugar, salt and syrup.
Cook, stirring, until sugar is dissolved.
Boil until small amount forms a ball in cold water. Remove from heat.
Add oleo and vanilla.
Cool to spreading consistency.
Makes enough for 4 layers.

title: apple-raisin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Coat 12 muffin tin with nonstick vegetable spray.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt in large bowl.
Make well in center.
Stir together buttermilk, applesauce, egg whites and canola in a small bowl.
Pour mixture into well of dried ingredients.
Stir until evenly moistened.
Gently fold in apples and raisins.
Divide batter evenly among 12 muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Each muffin contains 152 calories and 3 g. fat.

title: lasagna casserole
directions: Brown meat in a large skillet.
Combine all ingredients except cheeses and noodles.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes, stir occasionally.
Cook noodles 20 minutes.
Arrange layer of noodles and layer of cheeses until all ingredients are used.
Bake covered at 375° for 25 minutes in long baking dish.
Uncover the last 10 minutes.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Bake in a Corning Ware bowl at 400° for 1 hour.

title: overnight chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a casserole dish and set in refrigerator 6 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, oil and enough flour to get dough to consistency of biscuits.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutter.
Fold in half and cook on greased cookie sheet at 425° until brown.
Brush with butter.

title: beef and chicken casserole
directions: Layer chicken, dried beef and bacon in pan.
Mix sour cream and soup and pour over top.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours.

title: herman cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl; stir in Herman, butter, salt and 1 cup flour.
Beat on high speed 3 minutes.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Place on floured board; cover with towel.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend together.
Especially good with strawberries, grapes and pineapple.
Can be used with all fruits.

title: zucchini souffle(they come back for seconds for this one)
directions: Mix all together and bake in greased 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350 degrees, uncovered for 40 minutes and then 10 minutes covered.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Combine juice, shortening, egg and water.
Heat.
Blend dry ingredients in liquid.
Bake in loaf pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: jalapeno rice
directions: Remove seeds from peppers.
Combine rice, sour cream, green chilies and jalapeno.
Add salt.
Place layer of rice in lightly greased casserole dish.
Top with layer of Monterey cheese. Continue layering until all rice and Monterey cheese have been used.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Mix flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking powder, soda and salt.
In a large bowl whisk oil, eggs, molasses and vanilla until blended.
Stir in flour mixture with a large spoon.
Then add zucchini and nuts until well blended.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until done.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.

title: fezebel dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spread cream cheese on Ritz crackers.
Dot with Fezebel Dip.
Great for happy hour.

title: coconut pies (2)
directions: Do not cook pie shells first.

title: zucchini-vegetable combo
directions: In 4 to 6 quart pan or Dutch oven, combine all ingredients; bring to boil.
Boil 20 to 30 minutes.
Can also be boiled 2 to 3 minutes, then canned.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: quick salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides.
Slice potatoes and place them in a greased baking dish.
Mix soup with milk and pour over potatoes.
Salt and pepper, then sprinkle chopped onions over the mixture.
Place pork chops on top of this and cover the dish. Bake in 375° oven for 70 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix together and place in buttered casserole.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: tomato soup
directions: Boil water and bouillon cubes.
In another pan, heat oil.
Add onions, butter and sugar.
Cook until onions are transparent.
Add garlic, bacon bits and carrot.
Cook a few seconds.
Add wine, stirring until thick.
Add tomato paste, flour and tomatoes.
Place in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Add water and bouillon mixture.
Mix well.
Season with tarragon and thyme to taste.
Cover and put it in oven at 450° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, stirring from time to time. Add water to maintain consistency.
Before serving, salt and pepper to taste.

title: simply brownies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together.
Cream oleo, eggs and vanilla; add sugar/cocoa mixture.
Mix and add flour.
Add nuts if desired before turning into a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: chocolate chip and nut cake
directions: Grease 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes.
Put 1/2 cup almonds on bottom of pan.
Stir rest of almonds along with chocolate chips after all is mixed.

title: soft hermits
directions: Mix dry ingredients all together.
In another bowl, mix egg, oil, molasses, water, raisins and nuts.
Add to dry ingredients; mix well.
Bake on a cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown ground beef, bacon and sausage.
Drain off fat.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or heat in crock-pot for several hours.
Great potluck dish.

title: scrumptious chicken casserole
directions: Mix mayonnaise, chutney and soup powder together in a casserole dish, then mix in the chicken pieces, covering them with sauce.
Cover and cook +/- 1 1/2 hours at 350°F, 180°C.

title: kate knox's chess pie
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar and salt.
Add melted oleo and buttermilk.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 375° until set.

title: pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour tube pan, 10 x 4-inch pan.

title: church windows
directions: Melt margarine in double boiler, then add chocolate pieces. Remove from boiling water when melted.
Stir until smooth. Quickly add marshmallows and blend well.
Form 2 logs on wax paper and place in refrigerator.
Leave a few hours or overnight.
Slice when ready to serve.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake 10 minutes in 400° oven.

title: cooper's corn bake
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Put in casserole dish, Cover; bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour.

title: mock raspberry jam
directions: Combine ground green tomatoes, sugar and water.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 10 minutes.
Add raspberry jello.
Simmer for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Place in containers and let cool at room temperature.
After cooling, place in freezer.

title: cucumber lime salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add vinegar and next four ingredients.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Whip Jell-O with rotary beater until fluffy; fold in cucumber.
Chill until firm. Makes 6 servings.

title: "mom's" chocolate buttermilk cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar together.
Add egg yolks, buttermilk and baking soda.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and flour, sifted with baking powder and cocoa.
Mix well.
Add egg whites.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Test with pick.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Beat butter at medium speed of an electric mixer; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine next 3 ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk; mix well.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Work with half of dough at a time and store remainder in refrigerator.
Place stockinette cover on rolling pin; flour well. Roll dough to 1/4-inch on a lightly floured pastry cloth.
Cut with a 2 1/4-inch round cutter and carefully place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
(Cookies will be pale.)
Cool on wire racks.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: florida delight
directions: *I usually drain the oranges and use that liquid for part of the water.

title: cookies and cream
directions: Pour milk into a small bowl.
Spread a layer of Cool Whip on the bottom of a 14 1/2 x 11 x 6 tupperware container. Dip cookies into the bowl of milk.
Place a layer on top of Cool Whip. Alternate with Cool Whip and cookies until full. Place in refrigerator until ready to eat.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil. Add dry ingredients, mixing well. Add apples and nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Allow cake to cool slightly.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Mix everything. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: sugar coated peanuts
directions: Dissolve sugar in water in saucepan.
Pour in peanuts.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly, until almost all liquid has cooked out.
Nuts will begin turning "sugary." Pour out on baking sheet, separating nuts. Bake about 30 minutes at 300°.
Stir occasionally with spatula. Cool.

title: zippy meat loaf
directions: Put all ingredients in a mixing bowl and mix for a couple of minutes.
Order of ingredients is not important.
Place mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
I like to line my pan with foil and put a rack on top of the foil and the meat loaf on the rack so the drippings are not saturating the meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serves 8.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cut carrots and cook until barely done.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Marinate for 24 hours.

title: jimmy's favorite chocolate pie
directions: Cook cocoa, flour, sugar, salt and milk until thick.
Beat yolks, margarine and vanilla.
Add to cocoa mixture.
Blend well. Pour into cooled baked pie shell.
Cool.

title: *cornmeal mush("tarapash")
directions: Bring the water and salt to a boil. Add 1/2 stick butter and stir until melted. Add the cornmeal, stirring constantly, until it gets thick and pulls from side of pan.

title: cheese and sausage balls
directions: Mix together, roll into balls.
Then bake in oven for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: beef, potato and pea pot
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Place 1/2 meat mixture in 2-quart casserole.
Top with half the potatoes.
Add rest of beef and potatoes.
Layer peas next and top with soup.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: 15 minute coffee cake
directions: Beat the eggs, 1 1/2 cups sugar and milk, then stir in the flour, baking powder and 1/2 stick softened butter.
Mix together. Set aside the 1 stick butter, 3/4 cup sugar and 3 teaspoons cinnamon.
Pour first mixture into a greased cookie sheet.
Melt the 1 stick butter and put aside.
Take the 3/4 cup sugar and 3 teaspoons cinnamon and mix together.
Shake over cake, then dribble the butter onto cake mix.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Cool and enjoy.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix pineapple and cherry pie filling in 9 x 11-inch pan. Sprinkle cake mix on top. Place nuts all over cake mix. Lots of pats of butter on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Mix eggs and sugar; add margarine.
Beat until creamy.
Add crushed pineapple and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° until firm, about 40 minutes.

title: carol's chili
directions: Heat ground beef on low heat until light gray or for 15 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer 45 more minutes.

title: crunchy squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with 1/2 of margarine.
Saute onions, bell pepper and celery in remaining margarine and add to the squash.
Add sour cream and soup (undiluted) and water chestnuts plus 1/2 of stuffing mix and seasoning packet.
Place greased baking dish and top with remaining stuffing mix.
Cook at 350° until bubbly.

title: crunch bars
directions: Melt chocolate chips in a double boiler.
Add peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Pour over cake.
Cook and cut into bars.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: **To make sour milk add 2 Tbsp. vinegar to milk.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a bowl, beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until thick and lemon colored.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, soda, salt and baking powder.
Add sifted ingredients and zucchini to mixture.
Pour into 2 oiled and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until tester comes out clean.
Let cool 20 to 30 minutes before turning out.

title: deep fried mozzarella puffs
directions: Remove crusts from bread slices.
Cut each slice diagonally into quarters.
Cut 40 pieces of cheese the same size and thickness of bread pieces.
Beat together eggs, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese and salt.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Add celery when first 2 ingredients are just about done.
Add vegetable soup and tomato soup.
Heat. Add milk last.
Heat, do not boil.

title: lola's chocolate pie
directions: Put 1 1/2 cups milk and margarine in saucepan and bring to boiling on medium heat.
Mix all remaining ingredients (except egg whites).
Add to saucepan and cook until thick.
Cool.
Add vanilla last.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: In a large bowl, mix cereals with cooled melted margarine. Add buttermilk, sugar and beaten eggs; mix well.
Add flour, salt and baking soda; mix well.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: In bottom of 8 x 10-inch casserole dish, spread Doritos. Sprinkle chicken or turkey cubes on top.
Sprinkle chopped onions over chicken.
Pour soup over onion layer.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Add sliced olives and/or green chili peppers, if desired. Bake at 325° for one hour.
Serve with sour cream.

title: nibblesgreeley, colorado
directions: Mix first six ingredients in a large ovenproof pan.

title: leek and potato soup
directions: Bring all ingredients except cream to boil.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Coarsely mash potatoes with potato masher.
Stir in cream; heat thoroughly.

title: oatmeal scotchies cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, soda and spices; set aside.
Combine shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in oatmeal and butterscotchies.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 to 25 minutes.
Slice into squares when cool.

title: tortilla nibbles
directions: Mix
cream
cheese
and Ranch mix; spread on tortillas. Drain chilies,
pimento and olives.
Pat dry with paper towel. Get as dry as possible.
Sprinkle on cream covered tortillas; roll up tightly.
Cover
with
Saran
Wrap and refrigerate at least 2 hours. Then slice 1/2 to 3/4-inch servings.

title: marinated broccoli
directions: Trim off large leaves of broccoli; remove tough ends of lower stalks.
Wash broccoli and cut into spears.
Place in steaming rack over boiling water.
Cover and steam 10 minutes.

title: smothered pork backbone or pork fingers
directions: Brown pork fingers or backbone and remove fat.
In separate pot, saute onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Add soup and roux. Then add browned meat and turnips.
Cook until tender.

title: chewy bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs. Add flour and vanilla. Stir in nuts. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 300° for 30 minutes. Cool and enjoy.

title: brickle bars
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, cook and stir margarine or butter and unsweetened chocolate over low heat until melted.
Remove from heat; stir in sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat lightly with a wooden spoon just until combined (don't overbeat or brownies will rise too high, then fall).
Stir in flour.
Spread batter in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle almond brickle pieces and chocolate pieces evenly over batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove pan from oven and cool brownies in pan on a wire rack.
Cut into bars.
Makes 16 bars.

title: english toffee
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 of the pecans in a greased 10 x 13-inch pan.
Melt margarine in a large saucepan.
Add sugar and mix well.
Boil for 12 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour hot mixture over pecans in pan.
Place section of Hershey bar on top.
When melted, spread over chocolate to cover.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 finely chopped nuts.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Put the chili, half of the chopped onion and 1 cup of cheese in a bowl and mix up.
Put 2 tablespoons of chili mix into each tortilla and roll up like jelly roll.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan, rolled up side-by-side.
Put remainder of onion all over top. Spread other can of chili over top and sprinkle with remainder of the cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Eat.
Yum-yum!

title: best pecan pie
directions: Brown butter in saucepan until brown (do not burn - it keeps cooking after it starts turning brown).
Let cool.
In separate bowl, add ingredients in order.
Stir.
Blend in browned butter, stirring well.
Pour in pie shell and bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.
This recipe is easily doubled.
Eat one, freeze one.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix: apple, orange (ground in blender), celery, nuts, cranberry sauce, pineapple, sugar, and salt. Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water, add to mixture and let set until congealed. Serves 8 or 10.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spinners
directions: Arrange 2 slices of ham lengthwise end-to-end overlapping by 1-inch.
Lay 2 slices cheese end to end in the center of the overlapping ham slices.
At one end of ham, stack strips of chilies and pimentos.
Carefully roll up jelly-roll fashion. Place seam side down on plate.
Repeat, making 7 rolls.
Cover and chill.
At serving time, slice into 7 spinners.

title: zucchini-pineapple
directions: Peel and grate or cube zucchini.
Mix all ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir frequently.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt margarine; add minced onion and minced green pepper. Cook slowly 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings.
Great for hot dogs or hamburgers.

title: wedding punch
directions: Combine pineapple juice, sherbet, and half of ice cream. Beat until smooth.
Add ginger ale, sprite, or 7-up.
Spoon remaining ice cream into punch.
Serve immediately.

title: jogging in a jug
directions: Mix juices together well. Chill and drink cold.
It's better cold!
Drink 1/2 cup daily.

title: prayer bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl cream 1/2 cup butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add 1 cup flour and blend well.
Press in bottom of ungreased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Remove from oven.

title: southern yeast biscuit dough
directions: Sprinkle the yeast over the warm water and stir in the sugar. Set aside until bubbly. In a large mixing bowl,
combine flour and soda.
Toss lightly just to mix.
Cut in the shortening using a pastry blender, a fork, or your fingertips.
Add the yeast and buttermilk.
Stir with a large wooden spoon until well mixed. This dough can be kept in the refrigerator for up to a week and used as needed.
Yield: About 8 cups dough.

title: nacho dip
directions: Cook hamburger with onion.
Drain excess grease.
Cut cheese into chunks.
Put all ingredients into crock-pot and let cook until melted.
Serve with nachos.

title: spinach and chicken quesadillas
directions: Saute chopped onions and mushrooms and set aside.
Cook spinach and drain off excess liquid.
Brown chopped chicken tenders in a skillet.
After chicken is cooked add picante sauce to skillet and stir well.
Heat tortillas in a skillet until slightly brown.
Lay 3 tortillas on a cookie sheet and layer with spinach, chicken, mushrooms and onions, sour cream, and cheese.
Top with other 3 tortillas, cover with foil, and bake 20 minutes at 300°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Saute ground beef and onions until brown.
Lightly grease pie pan.
Spread beef evenly in pan; sprinkle salt and pepper on beef, then cover with Cheddar cheese.
Beat the 3 eggs; add milk and Bisquick.
Pour over mixture.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.
Cut in wedges like pie.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Make well in center; add syrup from pineapple, oil, beaten eggs and vanilla.
Blend.
Add pineapple, carrots and nuts.
Pour into oiled 10-inch tube pan. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° or until done.
May be baked in layers.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Let cool until partially set.
Add crushed pineapple, cheese and marshmallows.
Mix together salad dressing and whipped cream.
Add to jello.
Place in refrigerator to chill.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and 2 tablespoons of cocoa.
Stir in milk and melted shortening, mixing until smooth.
Add nuts.
Spread in pan.
Mix brown sugar and 4 tablespoons of cocoa.
Sprinkle over batter.
Pour hot water over batter; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: gullivers corn
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter and flour.
Put in pot. Bring to boil, simmer 5 minutes.
Blend butter with flour.
Add to corn mixture; mix well.
Remove from heat.
Put finished corn in casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Place under broiler until evenly browned.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: easy pudding cake
directions: Blend all ingredients except brown sugar and nuts in large mixer bowl. Beat 4 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer. Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly pressed and pulls away from sides of pan. Cool in pan 15 minutes. Spoon hot Butter Glaze over warm cake.

title: fat-free cream of potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes and onions together until cooked, about 20 minutes.
Add chicken cubes and season to taste.
Thicken with milk-flour mixture.
Add cheese; stir to melt.
Add milk as needed for desired consistency.

title: breakfast tacos
directions: Saute pepper, onion and potato in margarine.
Add eggs and scramble.
Add salt, pepper and paprika.
Serve on warmed tortillas and sprinkle with cheese.
Fold and serve with picante sauce.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Cream the butter and 1/2 cup of sugar until light and fluffy. Add water and vanilla.
Gradually add flour and nuts.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.
When completely cool, roll again in powdered sugar.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: elisabeth's chili rellenos casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch casserole and line it with split green chilies.
Layer the cheeses.
Mix the eggs, flour, evaporated milk, salt and pepper.
Pour the egg mixture over the cheese.
Place the casserole in a larger pan. Place both in the oven and fill the larger pan half full with water.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes.
Casserole should be slightly puffed in the center.
Serve with avocado, sour cream and salsa.

title: mrs. miller's crab spread
directions: Cream the cream cheese and mayo together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together and chill several hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: rolls
directions: Mix sugar, salt, dry skim milk, yeast and 3 cups flour.
Add 3 3/4 cups hot tap water and 1 cup cooking oil.
Add 3 eggs and 3 cups of flour.
Add remaining flour, 3 to 5 cups.
(You should use a total of 9 to 11 cups of flour.)
Put on floured board; knead 3 to 4 times.
Put in greased bowl; let rise until double.
Roll out and cut.
Should make approximately 60 rolls.
Let rise until double (about 30 minutes).
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: miniature cream puffs
directions: Melt butter in boiling water; add flour and salt all at once. Stir over heat until it forms a ball and leaves sides of pan. Cool slightly; add eggs, 1 at a time, beating vigorously until it forms a smooth glossy fairly stiff batter. Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet, 2 inches apart. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 300° and bake until golden brown, about 20 to 25 minutes. Yields 50 to 75 puffs.

title: butter nut pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Cream together the butter and shortening. Gradually add sugar, creaming well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add sifted dry ingredients gradually with milk, beating until well blended.
Add flavoring.
Beat well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan or large Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with 10x sugar or drizzle with frosting.

title: grandma's boiled custard
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Add vanilla.
Beat egg whites, sugar and cream of tartar until peaks.
Pour glasses 3/4 full of custard. Top with egg whites.
Don't double this recipe.
It won't work.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In saucepan saute meat and onion.
Add tomato sauce, basil, parsley, oregano, garlic salt, pepper and mushrooms; let simmer for 10 minutes.
Combine well drained spinach with cottage cheese.

title: craig's green jello salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water and refrigerate until like egg whites.
Blend cheese and pears until smooth.
Fold gelatin, cheese mix and Cool Whip.
Blend in blender, half at a time.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until set.

title: gold cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten egg yolks and beat thoroughly.
Add flavoring, then the milk alternately with the flour mixed with baking powder.
Beat well.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes in loaf pan.

title: cherry christmas balls
directions: Let cream and marshmallows stand overnight.
Add dates, walnuts and cherries; roll in balls.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cheese.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer cheese on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream margarine; add grated cheese.
Mix in flour (with pepper).
Chill slightly.
Roll out on floured surface.
Cut with small biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Place one half pecan on top of wafer.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Blend well all dry ingredients in a 9 x 9-inch square baking pan.
Do not grease or flour pan.
Mix vanilla, salad oil and cold water.
Pour over dry ingredients, mix with fork.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Place sugar, margarine and syrup in saucepan and bring to low boil until margarine is melted (stir). Cool slightly. Add very gradually to eggs, stirring constantly. Lastly, add pecans and vanilla. Pour into shell. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: 5 gallons of chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off fat.
Cook while adding all ingredients.
Cook until thickened, about 2 hours.

title: zucchini pickles(by h. j. heinz)
directions: Wash zucchini and cut into 3 x 1/2-inch pieces.
In a large bowl, combine zucchini, salt and water.
Mix well.
Cover and let stand 2 hours.
Drain and rinse well.
In a 6 to 8-quart saucepan, combine zucchini, onions and remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Immediately fill hot pint jars with zucchini and onions.
Leave 1/2-inch headspace.
Immediately pour hot vinegar mixture over zucchini, leaving 1/2-inch headspace. Carefully run a nonmetallic utensil down inside the jars to remove air bubbles.
Wipe jar tops and threads clean.
Place hot lids on jars and screw bands on firmly.
Process in boiling water canner for 15 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
In a bowl, combine hamburger, beans, soups and enchilada sauce.
Place taco chips in bottom of a baking dish. Add filling; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until cheese melts.

title: mandarin orange delight
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 1/2 cups hot water.
Add 2 cups of juice from fruit.
Add fruit and refrigerate until set.
Beat Dream Whip according to package directions.
Beat cream cheese and sugar separate from Dream Whip.
Fold Dream Whip into cream cheese mixture.
Spread over set Jell-O.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: congealed apricot salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling apricot nectar.
Add pineapple and cool.
Stir in cubed cream cheese and chopped nuts.
Stir well and pour into mold or casserole dish.
Chill until firm.

title: cheesy ham and potato casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo in a large saucepan until tender. Add flour and seasonings.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add 1 1/2 cups cheese, stirring until cheese melts.
Add ham and potatoes.
Spoon into a greased 2-quart, shallow baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese. Bake 5 minutes.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Pimentos are for color only.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Beat eggs until blended.
Melt margarine.
Set aside.
Measure dry ingredients.
Add eggs, margarine and buttermilk to dry ingredients.
Mix until blended (batter should have lumps).
Pour 1/4 cup batter or as desired on hot griddle.
Serve with favorite warm syrup.

title: apple orange cinnamon crisp
directions: Heat the oven to 375°.
Combine flour, 1/3 cup of the sugar and the salt.
Cut the butter into small pieces and rub into the flour mixture until crumbly.
In a mixing bowl, combine the remaining 1/3 cup sugar, cornstarch, orange zest and cinnamon.
Peel the apples, core and cut into chunks.
Add to the sugar mixture and toss to coat.

title: date loaf
directions: Boil sugar, milk and Karo syrup until soft ball in water. Remove from fire. Add butter and dates.
Mash when hard.
Add chopped nuts and roll in wet cloth when cold.
Cut in slices.

title: quick cocoa cake
directions: Boil
together
oleo, Crisco, water and cocoa.
Combine sugar, flour, soda,
salt,
buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Add boiled ingredients and pour in greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken fajita salad
directions: Cut chicken in stripes cook in 1 tbsp olive oil; add pepper and
onion.
Cook until chicken is done add Fajita mix.
Cover and let set about 10 minutes.
Place over salad mix can be served with tortilla chips and top with cheese.

title: ambrosia cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare and bake cake in a 13 x 9-inch pan according to package directions.
Cool.
With a knife, poke holes about 1-inch apart in cake all the way through to the bottom. Combine sweetened condensed milk, juice concentrate and rind.
Mix well.
Spoon mixture into each hole in the cake.
Spread remaining mixture evenly over the top of cake.
Chill at least 1 hour. Spread whipped topping over the cake.
Garnish with flaked coconut and orange slices, if you like.

title: chocolate crunch brownies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream the butter and sugar; add eggs.
Stir in cocoa, flour, vanilla and salt.
Spread in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Spread marshmallow cream over cooled brownies.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Saute peanuts in butter or margarine.
Mix brown sugar, corn syrup and baking soda and cook on low heat until mixture is thick. Pour over peanuts and popped corn.
Serve.

title: spice butter
directions: Vigorously mix butter and superfine sugar until fluffy.
Then blend in cinnamon and orange rind.
Chill until firm.

title: broccoli-ham rolls
directions: Combine milk, flour and salt in medium-size saucepan; cook and stir until thickened.
Add cheese; cook and stir until cheese melts.
Stir in mushrooms; set sauce aside.
Place broccoli on ham slices; roll up.
Place ham rolls, seam side down, in shallow baking pan.
Pour sauce over rolls.
Cover and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until hot.

title: apple upside-down cake
directions: Combine apples and maple syrup in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until apples are just tender.
Combine cornstarch and water; add to apple mixture.
Continue cooking, stirring constantly, until mixture is clear and comes to a boil.
Pour into 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: orange pecan goodies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in sauce pan.
Bring to boil.
Add pecans.
Stir constantly over high heat until all liquid is absorbed.
Remove from heat.
Stir until pecans separate; spread over cookie sheet, individually.

title: canned green beans
directions: Snap, string and wash beans.
Put jar lids and rings in boiling water.
Put 2 quarts hot water in canner on medium-high. Pack beans tightly in sterilized quart jars.
Add 1 teaspoon salt. Cover with hot water to top of beans and slide butter knife down inside of jars to get rid of bubbles.
Seal jars and place in canner. Turn on high.
Place lid on cooker.

title: burger bean bake
directions: Fry bacon and remove bits from grease.
Saute onions in bacon grease.
Brown ground beef.
Drain any grease from beef.
Combine all ingredients and pour into baking dish and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit crunch pie
directions: Brush bottom and sides of crust with egg yolk.
Bake crust at 350 degrees for 5 minutes or until light brown.
Pour the pie filling into the pie crust, if using filling with big chunks I sometimes cut the fruit into smaller pieces.
Mix in bowl remaining ingredients.
Mix together to form a crumbly topping.
Sprinkle the topping on the top of the filling.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes until topping is light brown (the filling may bubble over).

title: ham casserole
directions: Alternate layers of ingredients; cover with a Cream Sauce. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: caramel icing
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar in saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Add milk and stir until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add salt, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth and of spreadable consistency.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Mix. Bake in 9 x 12-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes. Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: poppy seed loaf delight
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; set aside.
Mix together sugar, oil and eggs until well combined.
Stir in milk, poppy seed and extracts.
Add dry ingredients, stirring only until moistened. Pour batter into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Prepare topping and pour over loaf.

title: seafood gazpacho
directions: Peel and seed cucumber; cut into chunks.
Stem and seed pepper.
Quarter and seed tomatoes.
Whirl vegetables and scallions in a food processor until finely chopped; transfer to a large bowl.
Squeeze 1 tablespoon juice from the lemon and stir in with the tomato juice, oil, dill, 1 1/4 teaspoons salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Add clams.
Slice shrimp in half lengthwise and add.
Chill.
Taste and add salt and pepper, if needed.

title: kluski pizza
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Put dry noodles in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
When hamburger is browned, add Ragu, tomato sauce and water.
Also add oregano or basil, garlic powder and about 1 1/2 cups Mozzarella cheese.
Pour sauce mixture over noodles.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Then add rest of cheese (1 1/2 cups) on top and bake additional 15 minutes.
Tastes better if sets for awhile after taking from oven.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter one 8 or 9-inch square cake pan.
Spread apples evenly in the bottom.
In bowl, mix sugar, oats, flour and cinnamon.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle evenly over apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: white liniment
directions: Beat eggs well before putting into vinegar.
Add turpentine last.
Good for man and beast.
Recipe was from De Witt C. Baldwin who died in 1900.

title: bachelor breakfast
directions: Brown sausage; drain and cool.
Beat eggs; add milk to eggs. Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Bake until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: coffee cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken paprika with rice
directions: Boil the chicken (without skin) until tender.
Remove chicken; set aside.
In frying pan, saute the onions with butter and paprika.
Add to chicken broth; let boil, about 20 minutes, then add half and half and flour.
Let cook.
Then add sour cream and lemon juice to gravy.
Cut up chicken in pieces; add to gravy. Chill overnight.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and mix 4 minutes with beater at medium speed.
Pour into well-greased and floured pans.
Bake for about 45 minutes.
Makes 2 regular-sized loaves of 9 x 6 1/2 x 3-inch.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and broccoli in oleo until onion is tender. Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar together until light.
Stir in beaten eggs. Sift flour, soda and cinnamon together and stir into mixture.
Blend in bourbon, chopped pecans, dates, raisins, candied cherries and pineapple. Drop batter by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 25 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: brownies
directions: Combine sugar, oleo, eggs and Hershey's syrup.
Beat well. Stir in flour and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: christmas cutouts
directions: Roll out cookie dough on floured counter.
Cut out cookies. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk together, then 1 can Eagle Brand in this mixture.
Put in refrigerator freezer for about 10 minutes.
Take out of freezer and add sour cream.
Beat this in with mixer, then add Cool Whip with mixer.
Bananas and Nilla wafers on top.
Or you can layer mixture and bananas.

title: salad
directions: Cut lettuce fine; cut onion fine.
Mix a small amount of mayonnaise and small amount of sugar.
Mix well.
Add the mix just before serving.

title: turkghetti
directions: Mix spaghetti with 1/2 pound of cheese.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: baked acorn or butternut squash
directions: Halve squash and fill cavity with brown sugar, spreading over cut side to shell.
Dot with butter.
Season and bake in moderate oven until tender, about 45 minutes.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda, salt, cinnamon and baking powder.
Add oil, eggs, vanilla, zucchini and nuts.
Mix together with a spoon for 2 minutes.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Fill 3/4 full.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Test to see if done.

title: fruit fluff pie
directions: Drain oranges, pineapple
and peaches.
Mix lemon juice with one can condensed milk.
Add whipped topping.
Chop fruit and add to previous mixture.
Put
in graham cracker crust and refrigerate.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: spoon burgers
directions: Brown onions and beef together.
Add soup, salt, pepper, water, catsup and mustard.
Simmer for 25 to 30 minutes.
Spoon on hamburger buns.

title: baked chicken
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Flip chicken over so it's covered with butter.
Put in oven; bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Mix soup, water and mushrooms with juice and garlic.
When chicken is finished, place broccoli around in between and on top of broccoli.
Then cover with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake 30 more minutes or until done.

title: baked stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini lengthwise; scoop out pulp and seeds, leaving 1/4-inch shells.
Parboil in salted water for 5 minutes; drain. Place 2 pieces of heavy foil in tray or large baking pan; set aside.

title: easy vanilla pudding
directions: In saucepan, mix first 3 ingredients.
Gradually stir in milk until smooth.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture boils 1 minute.
Remove from heat, stir in margarine and vanilla.
Chill. Makes 2 1/2 cups.
For chocolate pudding, increase sugar to 1/2 cup and add 3 tablespoons cocoa.

title: chocolate chip raisin rewards
directions: Mix all ingredients together; spread into an 8-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peach sauce
directions: In a blender or food processor, combine peaches, lemon juice and sugar.
Puree until very smooth.
Add almond extract. Serve as a sauce with fresh fruit or it is great with sliced peaches over angel food cake.

title: mulled cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Cook in microwave oven on 100% power 15 to 20 minutes or until mixture comes to a boil.
Reduce power to 30% for 12 to 15 minutes.
Strain before serving.
Serves 10 to 14.

title: frozen strawberry pie
directions: If using flour crust, bake and let it cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and beat until stiff and glossy.
Beat in egg yolks.
Add Cool Whip and blend well.
Add strawberries (may use frozen) and food coloring; blend.
Put in pie crust and freeze until firm.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Beat softened cream cheese.
Mix in milk, sugar, Dream Whip and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Pour into crust and add your favorite pie filling on top.

title: oven fried chicken(6 servings)
directions: Wash and pat chicken dry.
If desiring less fat, also skin chicken.
Roll chicken in crumbs and place in 9 x 13-inch pan. Cook at 425° for 30 minutes.
Turn and bake 30 more minutes.

title: mexican chicken dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with shredded cheese. Serve with tortilla chips or crackers (big Wheat Thins are good).

title: easy punch
directions: Mix cold cans of punch with 7-Up and stir, then when ready to serve, add the sherbet.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix all ingredients and start on medium heat.
Cook slowly until golden brown and peanuts are cracking open.
Spray cookie sheet.
Add 1 tsp. soda and stir rapidly.
Pour and spread rapidly on cookie sheet.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Blend in milk.
Mix in flour.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour into greased muffin pans.
Sprinkle with additional sugar.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Makes 30 to 36 muffins.

title: mama darnall's corn salad
directions: Cut corn from cob, then chop enough cabbage to measure same as amount of corn.
Chop onions, peppers and tomatoes.
Mix all ingredients together in a large pot and boil slowly, about 30 or 40 minutes.
Pour into hot jars and seal to store or make small part of recipe for immediate serving.
Goes great with dried beans or meat.

title: pineapple ice cream salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add ice cream and stir until melted.
Mix in pineapple and nuts, if desired.
Chill until firm.
Do not freeze.
Serves 8.

title: guacamole salad
directions: Mash
avocados	with potato masher.
Add onion, tomato, garlic powder, peppers, salt and pepper.
Add your lemon juice to suit your taste.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: taco surprise
directions: Mix together beans and taco seasoning mix.
Spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass pan with the bean mixture.
Blend the sour cream and cream cheese with the mixer until smooth.
Spread the mixture evenly over bean mixture.
Top with lettuce, covering completely. Layer remaining ingredients.
Serve with a side dish of large-sized dipping chips.

title: corned beef hash
directions: Peel potatoes and dice.
Cook in water to cover until tender. Brown corned beef in skillet.
Add potatoes and onion.
Cook about 10 more minutes.
Drain water from potatoes before you add them to corned beef.
Salt to taste.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Scoop out seeds from peppers; pan boil in salted water for 5 minutes.
Combine ingredients.
Cook until tender; salt to taste. Add rice.
Mix well.
Stuff peppers; place in muffin pan.
Garnish peppers with grated cheese or toasted bread crumbs.
Bake in oven at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, white sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into casserole.
Top with mixture of other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix together.
Pack in Pam sprayed baking dish.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour or until brown.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Mix thoroughly and cool until set.
Will keep well for a couple of days.

title: corn relish
directions: In large Dutch oven, combine vegetables.
Mix other ingredients together.
Pour over vegetables.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Ladle into hot sterilized jars (1/2-inch headspace).
Seal, process in boiling water bath 10 minutes.
Let stand at least 1 week to blend flavors.
Makes 14 (12 ounce) jars.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in a medium saucepan. Place over medium heat and stir until mixture come to a boil. Continue cooking until mixture forms a soft ball when a small amount is placed in cold water. Remove from heat and add a few drops of food coloring. Slowly pour syrup over popcorn and stir to coat. Butter hands and form into balls. Be careful that the syrup has cooled enough to handle comfortably.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Place pineapple (do not drain) in bowl.
Add dry pudding mix. Fold in Cool Whip.
Can be served over angel food cake or eat as is.
Keeps well so I usually double it.

title: watermelon pickles of grandma frances messner
directions: To prepare watermelon rinds, you will need to remove all pink fruit and dark green peel. Cut into bite size pieces.
Cover the rinds with water and boil for 10 minutes. Drain.
Combine sugar, vinegar and spices in a saucepan. Boil.
Pour over rinds and let stand overnight.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend cream cheese, peanut butter, milk and sugar. Fold in Cool Whip. Spoon into crust. Chill overnight and garnish with chipped cream, peanuts and shaved chocolate, if desired. Or, you may keep in the freezer before serving.

title: mexican hot dog
directions: Slice hot dogs in half lengthwise.
Place on corn tortillas; stuff with cheese and chile (optional).
Roll corn tortilla around hot dog; pin closed with a toothpick.
Deep fry until tortilla is crisp.
Drain on a paper towel; remove toothpicks.
Serve warm. Makes 6.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender.
Cook broccoli slightly. Drain thoroughly.
Arrange in greased casserole dish.
Drain cooked chicken and place on top of spears.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs and margarine and sprinkle over top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lentil soup with kielbasa
directions: In large saucepan or Dutch oven, brown kielbasa in hot oil until lightly browned, about 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towel, removing all but 1 tablespoon of drippings from pan.
Saute the onion, carrots and celery in these drippings until onion is tender, about 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil. Cover and reduce heat; simmer 40 to 50 minutes or until lentils are tender.
Discard bay leaf before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Combine vegetables and olives in large bowl.
For marinade, combine vinegar and remaining ingredients in jar.
Cover and shake vigorously.
Pour marinade over vegetables.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator overnight, stirring occasionally.
Makes about 13 cups.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, margarine and 3 Tbsp. sugar.
Spread in 9 x 13 inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef.
Add salt, pepper, onion, garlic, chili powder and cumin seed.
Cook until meat is well seasoned.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer 2 hours.
Makes 10 servings.

title: fudge pie
directions: Sift sugar, flour and cocoa together.
Add melted butter and mix well. Add eggs and vanilla. Beat with mixer on low speed just until blended.
Do not overbeat.
Stir in pecans. Pour into greased and floured 9-inch square pan or a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix
hamburger,
onion,
pepper,
cooked rice, salt and pepper in a
large
bowl.
Cook
mixture in loaf form in a 9 x 13-inch baking
dish at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cover with foil while cooking.
Uncover last 15 minutes.

title: vegetable cheese ball
directions: Squeeze out all of the juice from vegetables and pineapple. Add Worcestershire to softened cream cheese. Season to taste. Stir in vegetables and pineapple, mixing well. Add 1 1/4 cups of chopped nuts to mixture. Roll into ball. Roll ball in remaining chopped nuts.

title: chili
directions: Combine
all
ingredients together and simmer for 2 1/2 hours.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Mix all ingredients in order listed. Pour into pie shell. Bake 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350°. Continue baking for 45 minutes or until knife inserted into center of pie filling comes out clean. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Make cake according to box.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top before baking.
Remove from oven and poke holes in cake with end of wooden spoon.
Pour warmed fudge over cake and spread evenly. Cool.
Frost with whipped topping and garnish with sprinkles. Refrigerate.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Crumble beef into a 3 to 5-quart microwave dish. Add carrots and celery. Cover and microwave on High for 4 to 6 1/2 minutes or until beef is set, stirring twice.
Add remaining ingredients. Microwave, covered, for 12 to 18 minutes until vegetables are tender, stirring twice. Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix sugar and shortening; add eggs, milk and other ingredients. Fold in apple.
Pour mixture into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Great for Mom to use up the apples small children never really finish.

title: hamburger barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: lo-fat lasagna roll-ups
directions: Cook lasagna noodles.
Mix together tomato sauce, basil, oregano and heat through in saucepan.
Mix together mushrooms, onion and butter and saute 3 to 4 minutes.
In a large bowl, combine Ricotta, Parmesan, turkey and sauteed vegetables; mix well. Lay noodles out flat, spoon 1 tablespoon sauce mix and spread out to cover whole noodle.
Spread meat mix onto the noodle in the same fashion, then roll and place in a baking dish.
Spoon remaining tomato sauce mix over each roll before baking.
Bake, covered with aluminum foil, in a preheated 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in a airtight container.
Put 2 teaspoons in a cup; add hot water.

title: sauteed quail
directions: Cut the meat from the cleaned quail.
Cut into small pieces. Dice the onion and saute in butter until soft.
Add the quail meat and cook until done (approximately 5 minutes).
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: navy beans and pig tails
directions: Place meat in a large saucepan.
Cover with water.
Simmer until meat is tender.
Remove meat from broth.
Add navy beans, whole onion, salt and pepper.
Simmer until beans are tender.
Add additional water as needed.

title: leona's chewy pralines
directions: Mix sugar and syrup; cook over med. heat until it reaches 245°. Remove from heat; add butter. Stir until melted; add whipping cream. Cook until the whipping cream is dissolved. Add pecans and vanilla. Remove from heat; mix until it starts to thicken. Drop on buttered wax paper by a teaspoon.

title: creamy fruit cup
directions: Toss fruit with lemon juice. Add yogurt and toss lightly. Spoon into serving dishes and sprinkle each serving with brown sugar.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: easy potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion with seasonings until potatoes are very soft.
Mash potatoes until fairly smooth.
Add milk and heat to boiling.
Season to taste.
Add chopped parsley (optional). Yields 1 quart.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with hands.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Top with one large Hershey bar or chocolate chips, melted.
Spread on top of and refrigerate.

title: super antipasto
directions: Layer all ingredients on a suitable plate or platter, starting with lettuce, then sliced ripe tomatoes, Progresso pepper salad, salt, pepper and oregano, artichoke hearts, then sliced olives and anchovies, followed by salami and Provolone cut into quarters. Finish with pure olive oil and vinegar.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until done, cool and dice.
Save 3 tablespoons fat from chicken broth.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Saute onions, green pepper and garlic in 3 tablespoons fat (broth).
Add flour and brown.
Add tomato juice and chili powder and cook until slightly thick.
Drain noodles.
Add 1/2 spaghetti in casserole dish, then add 1/2 chicken, then sauce, then cheese.
Repeat layers in that order.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: parsnips
directions: Peel and halve parsnips.
Boil for about 5 minutes and drain. Allow to cool for a few minutes so not too hot to handle.
Combine equal portions of flour and grated Parmesan cheese.
Roll cooled parsnips in flour and cheese mixture.
Coat bottom of baking pan with a small amount of oil.
Place parsnips in pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crispy oat cookies
directions: Cream the butter.
Gradually add sugars, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add egg and beat well.
Add oil and vanilla, mixing well.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats and remaining ingredients.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Put in crock-pot along with cheese and Manwich; heat thoroughly.
This can also be heated in the microwave.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: To each quart jar, add 1 head of dill, 2 or 3 cloves garlic, 1 hot pepper and cucumbers (whole).
Cover with a mixture of 2 quarts water, 1 quart vinegar and 1 cup salt.
Bring this mixture to a boil before adding.
Seal and allow to stand 4 to 6 weeks before using.

title: chocolate glaze
directions: Over very low heat, melt butter and chocolate, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar and vanilla until crumbly.
Add boiling water, a teaspoon at a time to form a glaze of pouring consistency.
Pour quickly over cake.
Allow glaze to drip down sides.
Excellent when used over a Bundt cake.
Enjoy!

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
If too thick, add more pickle juice until of desired consistency.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars well.
Add eggs, salt, water and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Sift flour and soda together.
Blend in creamed mixture.
Stir in oatmeal and coconut.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cocoa krispies treats
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marsh mellows and stir until completely melted.
Add cocoa krispies cereal.
Stir until well coated.
Using buttered spatula, waxed paper or buttered hands press mixture evenly into buttered 13 x 9 x 2 in. pan.
Let cool, then cut into squares.

title: cabbage soup langer
directions: In a kettle, cook onion, garlic and cabbage in oil over moderately low heat, stirring until onion is softened.
Add flour and cook mixture, stirring, for 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes, water, lemon juice and sugar.
Add caraway seed and salt and pepper to taste.
Bring mixture to a boil and simmer for 1 hour.
Add extra water if mixture becomes too thick.

title: peking shrimp
directions: In large skillet, heat corn oil over medium-high heat.
Add shrimp.
Cook, stirring occasionally, about 3 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes and green peppers.
Stir together remaining ingredients. Add to skillet.
Stirring constantly, bring to boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Make the roll mix according to directions.
Roll out flat, about 1/2-inch thickness.
Spread butter over dough.
Cover with pepperoni, then with Mozzarella cheese.
Roll up; bake until bread is done in a 350° oven.

title: red bud day casserole or mrs. jones' scalloped chicken
directions: Cook the hen slowly for 2 1/2 hours, or until meat falls from bones, with the carrot, sliced onion, 2 teaspoons salt and 2 quarts water.
Cool bird in its own liquid.
Skim fat; separate meat and skin from bones.
Put skin through meat grinder and cut meat in bite size pieces.
Cook and grind giblets.
Crumble and mix the bread.

title: golden corn bread
directions: Measure corn meal in a 2-quart bowl.
Break eggs in a 1 1/2-quart to a 2-quart bowl.
Beat and blend in remaining ingredients.
Pour over corn meal and beat well to blend.
For a thick bread, pour into a greased 8-inch square pan and bake in a 400° oven for 25 minutes.

title: grape pie
directions: Discard seeds.	Bake pie
in
hot
oven
at 450° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 325° and bake 30 minutes.
Cool 3 to 4 hours before cutting.

title: potato balls(deep fry)
directions: Peel and cook potatoes until done.
Drain. Rinse and let cool thoroughly.
In a bowl, mix the potatoes with yolks, seasoning and bread crumbs. Roll and shape in oval balls.
Drop in deep hot fat. Let boil until browned (only a few minutes).

title: fried rice
directions: Heat oil in wok (low); add garlic and jalapeno for 2 minutes. This is to season the oil.
Raise temperature to high and add meat.
Stir-fry until done (approximately 3 minutes).
Add veggies and stir-fry until tender.
If you cook too long, they will be soggy.
Mix the package of seasoning with a small amount of soy sauce, oyster sauce and Worcestershire.
Add mixed seasoning to wok and stir in thoroughly.
Stir in the cooked rice and it is ready to serve.
Rice can also be served separate from the veggies.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain fruit and mix well with sour cream.
Chill.

title: south african raisin rice
directions: Sprinkle rice into rapidly boiling water.
Add the next 4 ingredients.
Cover; boil slowly for 20 minutes, or until rice is tender.
Add raisins, butter and sugar; toss lightly.
Serve hot with meat or poultry.

title: petite cherry cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese, add sugar and eggs, lemon and vanilla, until light and fluffy. Line muffin pans with baking cups. Put one vanilla wafer on bottom of each cup. Fill cups 2/3 full. Bake 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Top with pie filling. Chill.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Cut fruit into bite size pieces and mix with remaining ingredients.
Best if prepared the day before.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Trim fat from the beef; slice beef into thin strips, about 2-inches long. Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet. Add beef and cook over high heat until meat is lightly browned; add onions, garlic and mushrooms. Cook over medium heat until onions are soft. Remove from heat. Stir in flour, parsley, salt and pepper. Gradually add beef broth and tomato paste. Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil and thickens. Remove from heat.

title: easy berry pie
directions: Combine water and gelatin in small saucepan.
Place over low heat and stir until dissolves and mixture is clear.
In a medium bowl, combine condensed milk and lemon juice.
Stir in gelatin mixture until well combined.
Fold in sour cream.
Mix in 1 1/4 cup blueberry filling.
Spread mixture evenly into crust.
Chill remaining filling.
Cover and refrigerate pie for 3 to 4 hours. When ready to serve, garnish with reserved filling, leaving about 1/2-inch ring around the pie.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook the macaroni according to package directions.
In a medium saucepan, combine the dry ingredients.
Stir in milk until smooth.
Add margarine.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Pour over macaroni in greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: sausage-stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut each zucchini in half, lengthwise.
Place cut side down in a large skillet; add 1/2-inch water.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer until zucchini are crisp-tender, about 5 minutes. Remove zucchini and drain water.

title: chops that make you crazy(serves 4)
directions: In a small bowl, combine first 7 ingredients.
Sprinkle 1/4 teaspoon mixture or more on each side of chops, rubbing evenly. In a large skillet, heat one tablespoon of oil over high heat about 3 minutes.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Mix together and pour into two 9-inch pans that have been greased with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and beaten egg together and pat into the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Next, mix the 2 remaining eggs, cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Mix well and pour over the cake mix ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Pop a tube pan full of popcorn.
Mix with candy and nuts. Melt marshmallows and margarine over heat.
Combine mixtures in a large container.
Press into tube pan and refrigerate.
After chilled, turn into a cake plate and slice.
Keep refrigerated.

title: vicki's peanut butter pie
directions: Cream the cheese and peanut butter.
Mix well, then add Cool Whip.
Mix again; add powdered sugar.
Mix together.
Spoon in crust.
Freeze 6 hours.
Serve.
Refrigerate afterwards (freeze).

title: microwave scalloped potato and ham
directions: In 2-quart Corning Ware dish (greased), layer sliced potato and onions, Spam, parsley and sauce.
Repeat layers.
Cover and microwave for 45 minutes.

title: french pear pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs slightly in small bowl.
Stir in sour cream and vanilla.
Mix sugar and 1 tablespoon flour.
Add these ingredients to sour cream mixture; mix well.
Quarter pears and arrange in a shallow baking dish.
Top with sour cream mixture and bake for 15 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Place miniature marshmallows in a large bowl and set aside. Open and drain all three cans of fruit.
Add the cans of fruit into the bowl with the marshmallows.
Stir gently for 2 minutes. Add the sour cream in, and stir until thick and creamy.
Put the rest of the fruit and nuts in and stir again.
Allow to chill before serving.
It should be nice and thick or "set-up."
Serves 8 to 10.

title: aunt floye's dessert
directions: Layer
Blend
together
stick
oleo, 1 cup flour (self-rising) and 1 cup chopped pecans;
spread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: dixie relish
directions: Dissolve salt in water.
Pour over chopped vegetables and let stand 1 hour.
Drain.
If too salty, rinse and drain again.
Add vegetables, sugar and spices to vinegar.
Simmer 20 minutes and then bring to boiling.
Pack into hot jars.
Close.
Process in boiling water bath 5 minutes.
Begin to count processing time when water in canner returns to boiling.

title: chinese pickled beets
directions: In large pan, combine sugar and cornstarch, mixing well. Add vinegar, cloves, catsup, cooking oil, salt and vanilla and stir. Open cans of beets, add the 1 1/2 c. beet juice to the above mixture. Slice beets in half and add to mixture. Cook over medium heat, stirring until sugar has dissolved. Refrigerate before serving.

title: chicken taco casserole
directions: Line 13 x 9-inch baking dish with quartered tortillas.
Mix together first 6 ingredients in a bowl.
Put chicken (broken) over top of tortillas.
Pour mixed ingredients on top of chicken.
Put another layer of quartered tortillas on top.
Cover entire dish with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions. Drain well and set aside. Saute onion in oleo until tender. Add soup, milk and cheese.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until cheese melts.
Stir in rice and broccoli.
Pour into a 2-quart greased casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken or turkey dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° until done. Stuff chicken or turkey.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add beaten eggs.
Combine the dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Add mashed bananas, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in well-greased and floured pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: soy fried rice
directions: Heat oil.
Add eggs, mixing constantly while breaking up with fork.
Add eggs and onions to rice with soy sauce to color rice brown.
Blend very well and seve hot.

title: teriyaki marinade
