directions: Mix all ingredients together in a sealable plastic bag or a glass dish. Add meat (chicken, pork or beef) and marinate for 2-24 hours.

title: pretzel peach salad
directions: Mix pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar and oleo and pat into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex. Bake 8 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: swiss steak
directions: Roll steak in flour and brown in skillet until done.
In Dutch oven cooking pot, combine tomatoes, onion and green pepper over medium heat.
Add sugar, salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste. Simmer 10 minutes over low heat.
Lay steak in baking dish; cover with tomato sauce.
Bake 10 minutes at 250°.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan or Cheddar cheese, if desired.
Serve with rice.

title: creamy vegetables
directions: In a skillet over medium heat, combine soup, milk and pepper. Heat to boiling, stirring often.
Add vegetables; return to boiling.
Cover; cook over low heat 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring often.

title: alfredo
directions: Cook tortellini and drain.
Heat butter over medium heat.
Add cream, pepper and nutmeg.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 7 minutes.
Add Parmesan; cook 2 minutes until sauce starts top thicken.
Add tortellini, stirring 1 to 2 minutes, until heated through.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: baby food cake
directions: Blend the listed ingredients, except nuts, and beat for 2 1/2 minutes.
Add nuts and bake in a greased angel food cake pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Bring vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and pepper to boil.
Pour over vegetables.
Set overnight.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, beat Eagle Brand and peanut butter until smooth.
Add biscuit mix and vanilla; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls; roll in sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until lightly browned. Press Kiss into middle immediately after baking.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C). Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. In a large bowl, combine grated carrots, flour, white sugar, baking soda, baking powder, salt and ground cinnamon. Stir in eggs, oil, 1 1/4 teaspoons vanilla, pineapple and 3/4 cup chopped nuts; mix well. Spoon batter into prepared pan. Bake in the preheated oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center of the cake comes out clean. Allow to cool.

title: mother's lettuce
directions: Combine ingredients in bowl.
Whip until smooth and airy. Chill 1 hour before serving.
Serve over lettuce and hard-boiled eggs.

title: wine cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil and sherry together; add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Add pudding and nutmeg and beat 4 minutes.
Pour into a tube pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Turn out cake and puncture with fork.
Spread at once with glaze consisting of 1 cup powdered sugar and 3 tablespoons of cream sherry.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour and slowly add milk to form roux. Reserve.
Saute onion, celery and pepper in oil for 4 minutes.
Add tomato, thyme, honey and tamari.
Simmer, covered, for about 15 to 20 minutes or until tomatoes are soft.
Cool slightly.
Puree in a blender.
Over low heat, stir tomato into roux, a spoonful at a time.
When it is hot, add scallions and parsley.
Do not boil. Garnish with croutons.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cook rice in 2 cups of water and set aside.
Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Add seasonings.
Mix beef and rice.
Cut tops of peppers and hull out.
Fill with rice mixture.
Combine soup with 1/2 cup of water and pour over peppers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in covered dish.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 5 more minutes.

title: raspberry jam cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Beat butter and sugars until blended.
Beat on high speed 1 minute. Beat in eggs and preserves until well blended.
Beat in dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture, until very well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Bake at 350° for 70 to 75 minutes.
Cool completely.
Frost with favorite caramel frosting.

title: angel food royale
directions: Mix the cornstarch with the cold fruit juices.
Cook in a double boiler until thickened.
Add the beaten egg yolks; cook for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Add the stiffly whipped cream.
Fold in the fruits.
Serve over slices of angel food cake.
(Will serve 12.)

title: green bean supreme
directions: Combine all of the ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole. Bake at 350°
for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Before removing from oven, place onions on top of casserole.

title: gumbo
directions: Boil chicken.
Remove and debone.
Cut sausage into thin strips.
Fry.
Cut greens (onions, celery and peppers) into small pieces.
Saute.
Make roux of 1/2 cup oil and 3/4 cup flour.
Brown well.
Add sausage, greens and roux to chicken broth; also tomatoes and tomato paste.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Also add Zatarian's liquid crab boil to taste.
Cook over low heat for 3 to 4 hours. Add okra and chicken, also crab meat after you wash or drain crab meat.
Cook until okra is done.
Add shrimp and cook until shrimp are tender.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute squash with celery and onion in 1 tablespoon oleo. Crumble cornbread and cracker together.
Add 1/8 cup melted oleo. Beat eggs and add to crumbs.
Add can soup mixed with little water.
Add squash, etc.
Season to taste.
Stir.
Add cheese. Pour last 1/8 cup oleo over.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix together.
Roll out on a floured surface.
Roll in long roll.
Cut in thin strips.
Boil in chicken broth.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chex mix (low-fat)
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Melt margarine in saucepan.
Remove from heat; add garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce.
Combine cereals.
(A large kitchen garbage bag works well for mixing.) Pour margarine mixture over cereal and toss.
Add pretzels and corn nuts; toss until all pieces are coated.
Bake for 45 minutes in large shallow baking pan, stirring occasionally.
Cool completely and store in an airtight container.

title: christmas cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and beat well.
Put spice and soda in flour, add to creamed mixture with applesauce, then add gumdrops, nuts, dates and raisins.
Bake in loaf pans for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and de-bone chicken.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Spoon over chicken.
Crush crackers and sprinkle over soup and sour cream. Melt margarine and drizzle over crackers.
Sprinkle generously with poppy seeds.
Cook in 350 degree oven until bubbly.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients together and spread in baking dish.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Set aside.
Combine butter, sugar and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add 6 ounces of chocolate chips.
Add vanilla.
Melt morsels.
Into a large mixing bowl, add hot mixture.
Add eggs, beating after each addition.
Gradually blend in flour.
Stir in remaining chips and nuts.
Spread in 9-inch greased pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean when tested.

title: herring salad
directions: Soak herrings overnight, then bone and skin them.
Cut herring in small pieces.
Cut all vegetables into cubes.
Pour vinegar over entire mixture.
Best made a day before use.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar, baking powder, salt, vanilla and evaporated milk.
Finish filling freezer container with milk from carton.
Leave 3 inches in top of container.
Freeze in ice cream container.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cocoa in a large mixing bowl.
In a saucepan, bring water and shortening to a boil, then pour over flour mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into a sheet pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
It is good with or without frosting.

title: lacy oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place oats, brown sugar and baking powder into a bowl.
Add butter to oat mixture.
Stir in beaten egg; mix well.
Drop batter by 1/2 teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheets 3 inches apart.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Let stand 1 minute before removing from baking sheet.
They will become crisp as they cool.
Makes about 40 cookies.
These delicate cookies keep well if carefully stacked in an airtight container.

title: sugar-free banana split dessert
directions: Pat into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Let cool.

title: butternut casserole
directions: Season squash with 2 tablespoons butter, 1 1/2 teaspoons brown sugar, salt and pepper.
Heat 2 1/4 teaspoons butter in skillet. Add apples and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Cover and simmer over low heat until barely tender (about 5 minutes).
Spread in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Spoon squash evenly over apples.
Mix cornflake crumbs with pecans, 1/4 cup brown sugar and melted butter.
Sprinkle over squash.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: summertime cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, butter and milk.
Bring to boil.
Cook 8 minutes.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Drop by spoon onto wax paper.

title: chocolate peanut butter cups
directions: In small heatproof bowl, combine peanut butter and chocolate; place bowl in medium heatproof bowl and fill the medium bowl with boiling water.
Let stand, stirring frequently, until mixture is melted and well combined.
Set 8 fluted paper candy liners on serving platter; using a teaspoon, spoon 1/8 of chocolate mixture into each liner.
Cover platter with plastic wrap and refrigerate until candies are firm.
Makes 4 servings each.

title: venison macaroni casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Boil macaroni; drain.
Add cut up cheese; add milk; simmer until cheese melts.
Stir in venison and serve.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix powdered sugar, margarine, peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Roll in balls.
Put on cookie sheet for about 5 minutes.
Do not bake.
Melt Hershey bar, chocolate chips and paraffin wax in double boiler.
Drop balls in chocolate and put back on wax paper covered cookie sheets.
Place in cool place for 1/2 hour.
(Makes great candy for Christmas.)

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onions together.
Cook rice and broccoli separately.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chop cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: a great vegetable meal
directions: Mix ingredients in a large bowl and refrigerate, covered. Serve with an assortment of salad dressings.
Only add the dressing to individual portions.
This will remain fresh and crisp for a week in the refrigerator.

title: tortilla pinwheel
directions: Mix together all ingredients except the ham and tortillas. Spread the mixture on the tortilla, then lay the ham on the mixture. Roll the tortilla, then cut into pinwheels.

title: summer taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Set aside to cool.
Dice tomatoes and cucumbers.
Chop lettuce and green onions.
Grate cheese.
Put all ingredients in a large serving bowl.
Add ground beef and corn chips.
Toss well.
Keep in fridge until ready to serve.
Just before serving, add bottle of Italian dressing (or enough to satisfy taste).
Toss well.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients and boil for 3 minutes.
Cool and add next 2 ingredients.
Add lemon juice and bananas.
Freeze in quart containers.
When ready to use, thaw until mushy and put in punch bowl.
Pour ginger ale over mixture.
Makes about 50 servings.

title: super strawberry salad
directions: Drain strawberries and pineapple; reserve juices.
Combine strawberry and pineapple juices; add water to make 2 cups.
Pour juice into saucepan; bring to a boil.
Dissolve jello in juice mixture.
Blend strawberries, pineapple and bananas in blender. Blend with jello mixture.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Chill until set.

title: peaches and cream
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients up to and including the milk.
Mix at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Spread into a 10-inch pie plate.
Layer peaches on top.
Combine the cream cheese, sugar and peach juice and beat for 2 minutes on medium speed.
Spread on top of peaches to within 1-inch around edge. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: date nut cookies or date balls
directions: Melt margarine in a heavy pan.
Add beaten eggs, sugar, dates, vanilla and nuts.
Cook 10 minutes, stirring all the time.
Add Rice Krispies.
When cool, roll in small balls in coconut.

title: mexican tuna salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl. Serve with tostada shell or crackers.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute onions, green pepper and ground beef until brown.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Cover and bake 1 hour.
Remove cover last 15 minutes.

title: chalupas casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in a bit of oil; add flour, chili powder and 1 cup of water and let simmer, stirring occasionally, for 30 minutes.
Grease a 2-quart casserole and put in half of tortilla strips.
Combine soup or tomatoes and cheese and mix in separate bowl.
Place half of meat mixture on top of tortillas, then add a layer of cheese mix.
Repeat layers once, ending with cheese mix on top.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: texas style lasagna
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat and drain.
Add taco seasoning mix, tomato sauce and chilies; mix well.
Simmer uncovered for 15 to 20 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese and eggs.

In a greased 13x9x2 baking dish, layer tortillas, half the meat sauce, half the cottage cheese mixture and half the Monterey Jack cheese; repeat layers. Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
10 - 12 servings.

title: angel mallow frosting
directions: Combine sugar, egg whites and water in double boiler; beat with electric or rotary beater over boiling water until soft peaks form. Add Marshmallow Creme; beat to stiff peaks.
Remove from heat; beat in vanilla.
Tint frosting with food coloring, if desired.
Fills and frosts two 9-inch cake layers.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Mix Sprite and berry Punch.
When ready to use, add orange sherbet,
as much as you want, and serve.

title: quick beef with broccoli
directions: Trim fat from steak.
Slice steak diagonally across grain into thin strips.
Combine tomatoes and water; let stand 5 minutes. Drain; thinly slice and set aside.
Coat a wok or large nonstick skillet with cooking spray; place over medium-high heat until hot. Add steak; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Remove steak from wok; set aside and keep warm.
Add oil to wok; place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add broccoli; stir-fry 3 minutes.
Add tomato, green onions and garlic; stir-fry 1 minute.
Combine cornstarch, wine and soy sauce; stir well.
Add cornstarch mixture and beef to wok; stir-fry 1 minute or until sauce is thickened and bubbly.
Serve over rice.
Yield:
2 servings.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix peanut butter, sugar and crumbs together.
Melt margarine and pour over mixture.
Mix well. Spread peanut butter mixture on a cookie sheet and chill.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in double boiler.
Pour over peanut butter mixture. Chill.
After set, cut in squares.

title: sweet potatoes deluxe
directions: Slice potatoes in a casserole. Heat butter, sugar and water to a boil.
Add vanilla and pour over potatoes. Heat in a moderate oven until bubbly.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and drain, then mash.
Add all ingredients except dressing.
Put 1/2 dressing in casserole; add mixture, then top with rest of dressing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: munster monster cookies
directions: Cream together sugars and butter.
Add eggs, then remaining ingredients.
Drop by heaping tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter pie(yields 2 to 3 pies)
directions: Blend together first 3 ingredients and pour into a no-bake crust.
Cover ingredients with Cool Whip.
Top with drizzled chocolate syrup and nuts.

title: meatballs and rice
directions: Mix and shape into balls; brown in skillet.

title: diabetic italian biscotti cookies
directions: In a large bowl, beat together Splenda, eggs, and oil, for 1 minute.
Add vanilla and jelly, mix well.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well, making a ball and knead for a few seconds. Form 3 small logs, long and narrow.
Pam spray a cookie sheet. Preheat oven to 350° or 375°.
Take 1 egg, lightly beaten and brush each log.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool 10 - 15 minutes. Cut into slices 1/2 inch or wider.
Place back on the cookie sheets and put back into oven for 20 minutes or until golden brown. Yields 20 - 25 cookies

title: kathy's black bean salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients, chill at least 1 hour. Serve with chips.

title: garlic chicken
directions: Dip chicken into egg and then bread crumbs.
Fry in olive oil until golden brown, about 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Wipe pan. Melt butter on low to medium heat.
Saute minced garlic in butter for 2 minutes.
Do not brown.
Add chicken back into pan.
Add lemon juice and toss.
Serve over linguini or choice of pasta.

title: not-so plain cake
directions: Cream together shortening, eggs and sugar in large mixing bowl with electric mixer on medium speed.
In separate bowl, sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Using electric mixer on low speed, gradually mix flour mixture into other mixture.
Add almond extract and white vanilla flavor.
Mix until smooth.
Bake in 3 prepared layer cake pans for 20 to 25 minutes or in 9 x 13-inch prepared pan for 30 to 40 minutes.
Frost as desired or serve with fresh fruit.
Any Watkins extracts or flavorings can be substituted for the almond extract or white vanilla flavoring. Makes 12 servings.

title: whacky cake
directions: Put flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt together in ungreased pan.
Don't sift, but mix together well with fork.
Make 3 holes in flour mixture.
In first hole, put oil.
In second hole, put vinegar and in the third hole, put the vanilla.
Pour cold water over all.
Mix together with fork.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: double butterscotch ice cream dessert
directions: Prepare pudding mix according to package directions using 1 3/4 cups milk.
Chill 15 to 20 minutes.
Whip until fluffy. Gently fold in Reddi-Wip whipped cream and 1/2 cup chopped nuts. Refrigerate mixture 30 minutes.

title: mom's bluegrass chicken
directions: Grease casserole.
Lay out 8 slices of ham or beef.
Roll chicken breast halves around each ham slice.
Place slice of Swiss cheese on each chicken piece.
Mix mushroom soup, sour cream and wine; pour on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour, covered.

title: orange sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes and quarter.
Place in baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and cook until mixture thickens.
Pour over potatoes and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Melt margarine and brown sugar over low heat.
Let boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add milk. Bring to a boil again. Remove from heat and add vanilla and confectioners sugar (sifted).
Mix well.
Add more milk, if too hard.

title: paalak goshth
directions: Marinate meat with garlic, ginger and green chili pastes, salt, cayenne, turmeric, cumin powder, and coriander powder.
Set aside.
Wash, drain, and finely chop spinach.
Set aside.

title: meringue for a 9-inch pie
directions: Beat until fluffy and peaks form, adding sugar gradually.

title: stained glass candy
directions: In heavy saucepan, mix sugar, Karo syrup and water.
Boil, stirring constantly, until 300° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Add flavoring of choice and a few drops of food coloring. Mix thoroughly and pour evenly into a pan of powdered sugar.
Keep mixture away from sides.
As mixture cools enough to handle, cut with scissors into small pieces, always working from the outside edges.
Thirty-eight ounces of Karo syrup makes 5 batches.

title: maple ice cream pie
directions: In a small bowl, combine crumbs and butter.
Press into bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
In mixer bowl, beat marshmallow cream and sour cream until well blended.
Add ice cream, walnuts and maple extract; beat well.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into prepared pan.
Cover and freeze overnight, or until needed.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Combine tomatoes, green pepper, onion, pickles and bacon; toss gently.
Combine mayonnaise and pickle juice.
Stir well and set aside.
Layer half each of cornbread, tomato mixture and mayonnaise mixture in a large bowl.
Repeat layers.
Cover and chill for 2 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tuna pasta
directions: Cook pasta.
Drain and hold under cool running water.
Add drained tuna, tomatoes, green pepper and mayonnaise in large bowl with pasta.
Mix and serve.

title: diet 7-up salad
directions: Drain pineapple; save juice. Add enough hot water to juice to equal 1 cup. Bring to a boil. Pour into blender and add gelatin and cheese. Add sugar substitute, vanilla and 7-up. Blend on high speed for 1 minute. Pour into dish or mold. Chill for 5 hours. Can double the ingredients and add 1 cup of chopped celery.

title: bread
directions: Mix together water, salt, sugar, yeast and lard slowly; add the flour and mix.
Let raise until dough doubles in size.
Punch down; let rise again.
Punch down and put into bread pans.
Makes approximately 5 loaves of bread.
Bake at 350° approximately 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Bread should sound hollow on bottom when tapped if done.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco.
Add sugar.
Beat until smooth. Add egg yolks.
Combine flour and soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternating with milk.
Add flavoring, nuts and coconut.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° in a sheet cake pan or 3 (8-inch) cake pans for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy salad
directions: Mix the Jell-O and hot water until Jell-O is thoroughly dissolved.
Add the pie filling and stir until well blended.
Put in pretty bowl and refrigerate until set.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Blend sugar, cocoa, flour and salt.
Add boiling water and butter.
Cook until thick, "stirring constantly."
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Serve hot.
May be stored in refrigerator and reheated as needed.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Mix into baking dish.
Chill 1 hour.

title: chili sauce
directions: Mix together ingredients and cook until done.
Seal in hot jars: pints or quarts.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt in pints and 1 teaspoon in quarts.
This is delicious with beans!

title: turkey ravioli
directions: Grind turkey white meat into a large bowl; add Ricotta cheese, eggs and parsley flakes.
Mix together.
Spoon mixture onto squared noodle dough and pinch sides.
Drop into boiling water and cook approximately 15 minutes.
Serve with meatless spaghetti sauce. Makes approximately 100 ravioli.

title: perfect 7 minute icing
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla.
Place in top of double boiler.
Use medium speed to mix.
After water starts boiling, beat; cook for only 7 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla. Delicious on a coconut cake.

title: caesar salad
directions: Rub
fresh garlic cloves around inside of wooden
bowl. Hand tear
lettuce,
then add the remaining ingredients.
Mix all together thoroughly.
Top each salad with whole anchovies, halved cherry tomatoes and croutons.

title: swedish rye bread
directions: In large mixer bowl, mix first 4 ingredients with molasses and boiling water.
With mixer set at very low, add rye flour, one cup at a time.
Cool to lukewarm.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly and add sugar, salt, corn syrup, melted butter and vanilla.
Stir until mixed well.
Spread pecan halves on bottom of unbaked 9-inch crust and cover with filling.
Place in oven and bake for 40 to 50 minutes or until mixture is firm in center at 350°.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix together the sugars, shortening, pineapple, vanilla and eggs.
Set aside.
Mix together the remaining ingredients except nuts.
Put together the pineapple mixture with the flour mixture and mix well.
Add nuts.
Place by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: bonnie's chocolate mist pie
directions: Scrape cream from cookies and discard.
Crush cookies and mix with sugar and oleo.
Press into pie plate and chill.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Then add all the rest. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in greased pan or glass dish (13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch).

title: date and nut bread
directions: Put dates, nuts, soda and butter in bowl; add hot water.
Let mixture stand.
Beat eggs; add sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in date mixture, blending evenly.
Pour in buttered loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 1 hour until done.
Cool slightly and turn from pan.
Cool before slicing.

title: shortcut doughnuts
directions: You will need paper towels.

title: quick spaghetti salad(delicious!)
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain well.
Chop all vegetables into medium small pieces.
Add salad dressing and Salad Supreme; mix well. Chill and serve.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: white chili
directions: Place chicken in a large heavy saucepan. Add cold water to cover and bring to simmer. Cook until just tender, about 15 minutes; drain and place on plate or rack to cool.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Add cheese to cooked and drained green beans.
Mix sour cream, butter, onion flakes, flour, salt and pepper.
Add green beans and cheese.
Top with corn flake crumbs or Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients together.
Fold in 8 ounces of Cool Whip (reserve remaining Cool Whip for top of pie).
Pour into graham cracker pie shell.
Top with remaining Cool Whip. Refrigerate until chilled.

title: cherry cream cheese refrigerator pie
directions: Blend softened cream cheese and milk until smooth.
Gradually add lemon juice until mixture becomes more firm.
Pour mixture into cooled baked pie shell.
Add cherry pie filling as topping. Refrigerate.

title: six-layer casserole
directions: Preparation Time: 20 minutes.
Baking Time: Approximately 35 minutes.
Oven Temperature: 375°.

title: muenster cheese pie
directions: In small bowl combine egg, flour, salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 milk and beat until smooth.
Add rest of milk; blend well.
Add 1/2 cheese.
Pour into greased 8 to 10-inch pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 425° and sprinkle rest of cheese over top.
Bake 2 minutes more, until cheese melts.
Mixture may be made up to 1 hour before baking.
Allow to cool slightly before cutting into wedges.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer for about 1 hour.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Heat 1 inch of salted water (1/2 teaspoon of salt to 1 cup of water) to boiling.
Add carrots; cover and heat to boiling.
Cook until tender (25 minutes for whole, 5 minutes for shredded, 18 to 20 minutes for lengthwise strips or 12 to 15 minutes for crosswise slices); drain.

title: 7 minute frosting
directions: Mix all
together in top of double boiler and cook over boiling
water,
beating
with
electric
mixer,
until stiff. Remove from
boiling
water
and
add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 3 tablespoons powdered sugar.
Beat until stiff enough to spread on cake.
Will be enough icing for a 2 layer cake.

title: pink punch
directions: Put sherbet in punch bowl, add cola and ginger ale.

title: microwave devil's food cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter in 1-quart mixing bowl.
Add egg, beating until fluffy.
Blend in hot water.
Stir in remaining ingredients and beat thoroughly.
Microwave on Low and Defrost for 16 to 20 1/2 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before removing from dish. Makes 1 layer.

title: pickled squash
directions: Mix squash, peppers and onion.
Add salt.
Let mixture stand for 1 hour.
Drain off juice and add celery and mustard seed.
Mix sugar and vinegar; pour over.
Bring mixture to a boil and continue to boil for 10 minutes.
Put into jars and seal.

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Combine water with raisins.
Boil gently 5 minutes; let cool. Cream shortening with sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add vanilla and raisin/water mixture.
Mix well.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add flour mixture to batter, blending well. Stir in walnuts.
Drop on greased sheets.
Bake at 350° about 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: quick potato pyrizhky
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix in about 3/4 cup flour.
Season with salt.

title: moussaka
directions: In large pan melt butter, saute chuck, garlic and onions, stirring until brown.
Add herbs, spices and tomato sauce; bring to boiling, stirring.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, 1/2 hour. Stir in bread crumbs when ready to assemble.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Cut oleo into flour and sugar mixture.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: twinkie delight
directions: Line oblong pan with Twinkies.
Cover with layer of Cool Whip. Pour strawberries over top.
Keep refrigerated until time to serve.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Heat 4 tablespoons margarine and oil in large saucepan.
Add mushrooms; saute 5 minutes.
Remove mushrooms and add flour to juice.
Stir for roux.
Cook until bubbly.
Slowly add broth and cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add cream, sherry, Parmesan and nutmeg.
Stir until cheese melts.
Add turkey and mushrooms.
Stir well.
Combine with noodles and pour into "Pammed" casserole dish.
Melt 2 tablespoons margarine and toss with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: baked shrimp and asparagus casserole
directions: Combine the first five ingredients.
Spoon into a greased 8 inch square baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 425° for 20 minutes or until shrimp turn pink.
Serve over rice.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: hot rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over flour, sugar and salt.
Blend and cool.
Add beaten eggs.
Sprinkle yeast into lukewarm water; stir until dissolved.
Combine with egg mixture.
Add flour mixture and blend well.
Cover with foil and place in refrigerator.
Keep in fridge at least 4 hours before making rolls.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Cream butter and flour together.
Add pecans and press into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove and let cool.

title: kugle
directions: Cook noodles.
Beat eggs.
Add oleo, sour cream, cream cheese and cottage cheese.
Beat after addition of each item.
Add sugar. Add a drop or 2 of vanilla and almond extract.
Grease baking dish lightly. Sprinkle mixture of cinnamon and sugar on top of noodle mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and milk until smooth.
Gradually add sugar; beat until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Fill crusts.
Pour filling over cheese mixture.
Refrigerate.
Can use blueberry or any type pie filling.

title: chicken and yellow rice
directions: Boil chicken and remove from bone. Boil rice according to directions.
Add both soups and 1/2 cup chicken broth; stir in chicken.
Pour in large baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until all ingredients are hot.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add syrup and water. Cook, stirring often, until thickened.
Add gelatin.
Cool.
Put berries in cooled crust.
Spoon on filling.
Cool.

title: italian chicken
directions: In skillet, saute chicken strips in 1/3 of dressing until brown.
Add vegetables and remaining dressing.
Cover and simmer 7 to 9 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Serve over the hot pasta and top with Parmesan cheese.

title: triple fudge cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large saucepan, cook chocolate pudding as directed on package.
Blend cake mix (dry) thoroughly into hot pudding by hand, 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Sprinkle top of batter with chocolate pieces and nuts.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream, if desired.
Serves 15 to 20.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Mix batter with sugars until smooth. Beat egg into mixture. Sift flour, baking powder and salt, add to taste. Stir in coconut and cornflakes. Drop by tsp. 2 in. apart onto ungreased cookie sheets. Cool before removing from cookie sheet. Eat until gone.

title: pork tenderloin diane
directions: Sprinkle surfaces of tenderloin medallions with lemon pepper. Heat butter over medium-high heat in large skillet; do not let brown.
Add medallions and saute until nicely browned on each side, about 3 to 4 minutes per side.
Remove medallions to serving plate; keep warm.
Add remaining ingredients to skillet and cook and stir until blended and heated through.
Pour over medallions.
Serves four.

title: lazy woman's pie
directions: Melt butter.
Place
in 7 x 11-inch Pyrex pan.
Mix all together in the
pan
in which it is to be baked.
(This looks too moist,
but
have
faith,
it
will turn out with a lovely crust on top.) Bake at 350°.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook rice in 2 cups water. Fry bacon and drain off grease. Saute green pepper and onion in bacon grease. Combine all ingredients and bake at 350°to 375° about 2 hours.

title: crock pot roast
directions: Place potatoes in crock pot, then place roast on them.
Add carrots, salt and pepper.
Add both cans of soup.
Cook on high for 4 hours or maybe cook on low while you are working.

title: willie's swiss steak
directions: Drain tomatoes and reserve juice.
Cover pan with foil and coat with margarine.
Cut steak into serving pieces and arrange on foil.
Sprinkle with soup mix, mushrooms, peppers and tomatoes. Mix juice, A.1. and cornstarch.
Pour over meat and vegetables. Bring foil over, sealing tightly.
Bake 2 hours at 365°.

title: coffee punch
directions: Mix together and cool overnight in refrigerator.
Add 1 quart milk and 1/2 gallon of vanilla ice cream and serve. Makes 20 servings.

title: chicken rotel(club member: leslie jordan)
directions: Saute onions and peppers in margarine. Add cheese; stir until melted. Add tomatoes. Boil spaghetti; drain well.
Layer out chicken and spaghetti in baking dish. Pour sauce over this. Cook until bubbly at 350°, about 20 minutes.

title: chocolate supreme
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and pat this mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 15 minutes in a 350° oven. Cool.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and pepper; drain.
Pour mixture in large saucepan.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms, olives, cubed Velveeta and cooked spaghetti.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour into 5-quart casserole and top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 12 to 16.
Freezes well.

title: claire's toll house pie
directions: Beat eggs and cream with both sugars.
Gradually add 1/2 cup flour until evenly blended.
Add 1 cup melted butter.
Stir until smooth.
Into pie crust lay chocolate morsels and nuts.
Pour on top of chocolate mixture.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 10 minutes (check in 1 hour, depending on stove).
Center should not jiggle when pie is shook.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In casserole dish, place chicken breasts on bottom with 1 slice Swiss cheese on top of each chicken breast.
Spread mushrooms soup (right from can) on top of chicken and Swiss cheese.
Place stuffing on top of all that and bake 1 hour at 350° (30 minutes covered and 30 minutes uncovered).

title: all-time antipasto salad
directions: Separate broccoli into florets.
Peel stems and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Blanch broccoli, then refresh in cold water.
Cut carrots, celery and bell pepper into 1 1/2-inch sticks.
Wipe mushrooms to clean; cut off ends of stems, if necessary.
In a large plastic container, combine broccoli, carrots, celery, bell pepper, mushrooms, artichokes and olives.
Mix well.
In a blender or food processor, combine Italian salad dressing, herb seasoning, sugar, mustard, seasoned pepper and garlic powder.
Blend until smooth.
Pour dressing over broccoli mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight, turning and shaking from time to time. Serve in a pretty glass or wooden bowl.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: lemon yogurt pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Put all ingredients into a large mixing bowl and blend at low speed.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed. Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 65 to 75 minutes or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool for 30 minutes in pan on a rack.
Remove from pan; cool completely.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: puff pastry snack
directions: Mix egg and water. Unfold dough on a lightly floured surface. Roll out to about 14 by 10 inches. Cut in half, horizontal. Brush both tops with egg mixture. Top one side with filling. Place other dough on top of filling and seal the edges. Place on top of a lightly greased baking sheet. Cut into strips. Brush top with egg mixture.
Bake
at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Brown meat in hot fat; add vegetables.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cover.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients. Stir well. Spread batter evenly in an ungreased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking pan. Combine hot water, brown sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa.
Pour mixture over batter. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: hearty french onion soup
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan over medium heat.
Add onions. Cook for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden, stirring gently.
Stir in sugar and flour.
Cook for 3 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Add broth, thyme, bay leaf and pepper; mix well. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat, stirring constantly.
Boil for 6 minutes, stirring constantly; reduce heat.
Simmer, loosely covered, for 30 minutes.
Remove and discard bay leaf.
Ladle into ovenproof bowls.
Top with French bread; sprinkle with Swiss and Parmesan cheese.
Broil 4 to 6 inches from heat source for 2 minutes or until golden.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: sherry herring(sherrysild)
directions: Mix together everything but herring to make a sauce.
Pour sauce over the herring and let stand a few hours before serving. Decorate with fresh dill before serving.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients.
Place mixture in greased muffin tins.
Bake for 15 to 18 minutes.
Can use paper muffin cups.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in bottom of greased pan.
Mix other ingredients until crumbly.
Sprinkle crumbly mixture over apples.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 40 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: dirty rice
directions: Chop all the seasonings.
Brown sausage.
Add onion.
Cook 3 minutes.
Do not brown onion.
Add remaining ingredients, rice and water.
Lower fire and cook slowly until rice is tender.

title: basil chicken
directions: Bone, skin and halve chicken breasts.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil over medium-high heat in skillet.
Sprinkle chicken with paprika. Cook chicken 5 minutes on each side.
Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Simmer, covered, 10 to 15 minutes, until juices run clear.
Makes 4 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well.
Press into pan and bake 45 minutes in a 400° oven.
May spread catsup over top before cooking.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Press into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix next 3 ingredients; spread over top.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells or half cook lasagna noodles; set aside.
Combine cheeses, eggs, parsley and pepper.
Stuff cooked shells or place a large tablespoon of filling on lasagna noodle and roll up.
Pour 1/2 jar of your favorite spaghetti sauce into a 9 x 13-inch pan; place shells on top.
Pour rest of sauce over shells.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix everything together well.
Grease 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 to 50 minutes.
Check with a toothpick.

title: pastry shells
directions: Mix flour and salt; cut in shortening with pastry blender. Add water in small amounts to dry material.
Shape into balls; place in bowl and cover tightly until ready to use.
Roll 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured board.
Bake at 450° about 15 minutes. Yields 1 (9-inch) double-crust pie, 2 (9-inch) pie shells or 14 (4-inch) tart shells.

title: grandmother's light, luscious, lovely pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients vigorously until smooth.
Cook batter on ungreased griddle, turning each pancake when bubbles form.
Cook on the second side about 1 minute.
Accompany the pancakes with butter and hot syrup.
The batter keeps well in refrigerator for a week.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: squash casserole
directions: Partially cook 6 cups squash and 1/2 cup chopped onion.
Drain and add 1 cup sour cream, 1 can celery soup, 1/2 cup margarine (I use very little) and Uncle Ben's Stuff and Such (I use Stove Top stuffing and add a bit more sage).
Bake at 350° until bubbly (30 to 35 minutes).
Cover with shredded cheese the last few minutes.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift the dry ingredients into a mixing bowl and set aside. In another bowl, mix the egg, margarine, juice and water.
Add the dry ingredients and mix well.
Mix in the nuts, orange rind, cranberries and cherries.
Pour mixture into one 9 x 5 x 3-inch greased loaf pan or two 7 x 3 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or 40 minutes for smaller loaves.
Remove and cool. Wrap in plastic.

title: pineapple nut ball
directions: Mix ingredients, saving some of the chopped pecans to place on outside of roll.
Roll in ball and chill overnight.
Roll in remaining nuts before serving.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until light brown, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, peanut butter, egg and vanilla together. Mix dry ingredients.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Roll in 1-inch balls.
Roll into sugar.
Press ball with fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until mixture threads.
Add peanuts, stirring all the time, until color changes to light brown.
Remove from stove.
Add soda, salt and oleo; pour on greased cookie sheet!
Cool, then break into pieces!

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Mix well.
Beat in eggs.
Add milk and stir.
Pour into casseroles.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: shirley's barbecue sauce
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and simmer, stirring occasionally to keep from burning.
Cook bacon with onions.
Drain off most of fat; add to catsup mixture and simmer until very thick, stirring occasionally.
Serve with meatballs, chicken, etc.
Makes 1 quart.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add fruit cocktail and egg.
Beat well. Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour. (Toothpick in center will come out dry when done.)
Double recipe for large flat pan.

title: fresh garden salad
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions.
Drain.
Add dressing and toss. Then add the rest of the ingredients.
Toss. Cover and chill.

title: spinach-mushroom quiche
directions: Prepare pie crust mix as label directs.
On lightly floured surface with lightly floured rolling pin, roll dough into a 13 x 15-inch rectangle; use to line a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
With fork, make a decorative edge.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: fruit punch (often used for weddings)
directions: Combine ingredients in a large bowl.

title: broccoli nut salad
directions: Toss all but mayo, sugar and vinegar together.
Mix mayo, sugar and vinegar together.
Toss over salad.
Serve immediately and enjoy!

title: cherry-cola congealed salad
directions: Boil sugar, water and cherries.
Remove from heat as soon as it comes to boiling point.
Add jello.
Cool slightly.
Add cola slowly, pineapple and pecans.
Put in refrigerator and let congeal. Serve with mayonnaise or whipped cream.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 55 minutes.
Top with bread crumbs.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: mincemeat
directions: *Boiled cider is cider that is allowed to boil until it becomes syrupy.

title: disneyland beef stew
directions: Brown beef in oil.
Add boiling water, salt and pepper. Simmer, covered, for 2 hours or until meat is tender.
(Add more water, if necessary.)
Mix flour with 1 cup of liquid from meat pot until smooth.
Add to stew and cook until thickened.
Cook vegetables in steamer or in a small amount of water until fork pierces easily, but vegetables are still crisp.
Add to stew; then add additional salt and pepper to taste and simmer.
Mushrooms may be added to pot during last 15 minutes cooking time.
Serve over rice.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: toffee heath squares(microwave)
directions: Sprinkle nuts over buttered 8-inch square dish.
Place sugar, butter and water in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Microwave at High for 5 to 6 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes until thick.
Stir well; quickly spread over chopped nuts.
Sprinkle chocolate pieces over toffee.
Cover dish so heat melts chocolate; let stand 5 minutes. Spread chocolate evenly over top.
Refrigerate to set.
Turn out of dish.
Break into pieces.
Makes about 1 pound.
Ooooooh so goooood!

title: beef bagel dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together except bagels.
Let sit overnight.
Cut or tear bagels into dipping size pieces.
Store in Ziploc bag in the refrigerator.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Saute all meat, onion and pepper lightly, drain.
Place melted butter in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Toss cooked pasta with butter. Cover with 1/2 of pizza sauce.
Add half the cheese, half the meat mixture and all the mushrooms.
Sprinkle with spices, add remaining meat and cheese.
Top with remaining pizza sauce.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: turnip greens
directions: Pick and wash greens.
Add water and meat.
Cook 1/2 hour before adding greens.
Cook until tender.
Place sliced turnips on top of greens and cook until well done.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and yogurt together in mixing bowl until creamy. Fill into the 2 pie crusts evenly.
Chill overnight in the refrigerator (at least 6 to 8 hours).
Then ready to eat.

title: border buttermilk
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Fill with crushed ice up to 3/4 full.
Blend until mixture is slushy; serve immediately.

title: creamy nutty tuna
directions: Soften cheese and mix with remaining ingreds. May be served as a spread for crackers or filling for finger sandwiches. Yield 6-8 servings

title: the homestead's lemon chiffon pie
directions: Combine lemonade and condensed milk.
Fold in whipped topping. Pour into pie shell.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: seafoam topping
directions: Combine egg whites, sugar, cold water and salt; beat until thoroughly mixed.
Place over rapid boiling water in a double boiler, continuing to beat until mixture peaks on beater.
Remove from boiling water.
Add vanilla.
Mix.
Spread on cake.

title: apple stuff
directions: Put apples, 3/4 cup sugar and cinnamon in pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.
Cream butter, 1 1/2 cups sugar, vanilla and eggs together.
Sift flour and baking powder together and blend into butter mixture.
Spread over apple mix.
Bake another 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pecan praline
directions: Mix milk and sugars; bring to a boil.
Turn down heat; cook slowly until mixture forms a soft ball in cool water.
Add butter, vanilla and pecans.
Let this set awhile, then beat until it begins to thicken.
Drop by spoonful onto wax paper; let cool.

title: swedish apple pie(a definite favorite!)
directions: Fill a 2 1/2-quart casserole 2/3 full with diced apples. Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon sugar and cinnamon.
Mix together butter, 1 cup sugar, flour, egg, salt and nuts.
Pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top is brown.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Cook meat and onion together; drain.
Use large skillet.
Add sauce and Velveeta to meat.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Add all ingredients; mix well.
Spread chips in casserole dish.
Pour meat and cheese over chips.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Combine cocoa and flour.
Add remaining ingredients, but the melted butter last.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes or until firm and set.
Serve warm or cold.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Fill paper cups in muffin tins 2/3 full.
Combine the cream cheese with the sugar, beat in the egg and salt.
Stir in the chocolate chips.
Drop one rounded teaspoonful of the cheese mixture into each cupcake.
Bake as package directs.

title: rolled oats cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Mix ingredients and stir in the oatmeal last.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: scotch eggs
directions: Hard-boil 6 eggs and peel.
Divide sausage into six portions. Flatten and wrap raw sausage around eggs, covering completely. Beat one raw egg with a pinch of salt; use to coat eggs and then roll in bread crumbs.
Bake in preheated oven for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: cheerio cookies
directions: Mix sugar, vanilla, syrup and peanut butter over low heat until smooth.
Add Cheerios and chocolate chips.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan and press.
Refrigerate.

title: hot rice
directions: Cut margarine in pot and spread over bottom. Add drained mushrooms, chicken broth, bell peppers, onions, jalapenos, rice and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Stir and cover. Reduce heat and cook for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli chowder
directions: Pour chicken broth into a large saucepan. Add broccoli; bring to a boil. Cover and cook for 10 to 15 minutes, until tender. Remove broccoli from the broth; drain and place on cutting board to cool. To broth, add milk, ham, half and half, Swiss cheese and butter. Chop the broccoli and add to the chowder base. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes. Yields 2 1/2 quarts of chowder.

title: topsy turnovers
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly coat a baking sheet with cooking spray.
In medium bowl, combine chopped broccoli or spinach, egg, cheese, onion flakes, garlic powder and salt; set aside.
Unroll pizza dough and pull gently to form a 13 x 10-inch rectangle.
Cut dough in half crosswise, then cut each half into thirds lengthwise to make 6 equal pieces.
Place equal amounts of filling on one side of each piece of dough.
Moisten one short side of each piece with a small amount of water.
Fold dough over filling and seal edges using the tines of a fork.
Place turnovers on baking sheet. Bake 15 to 17 minutes until golden.
Remove from baking sheet to wire racks and cool completely.
Wrap each turnover separately and freeze if desired.

title: mountain dew cake
directions: Put mixture in 3 pans.
Bake at 350°.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix soda with sour cream and allow to dissolve. Cream butter and sugar well. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each. Add flour and sour cream alternately. Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan. Set oven temperature at 300°. Place cake in COLD oven and allow to bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean when inserted in middle of cake.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well. Add enough Maraschino cherry or strawberry juice to color and consistency for dipping.

title: popsicles
directions: Mix well and add 2 cups cold water.
Pour into ice trays and freeze.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add enough barbecue sauce to moisten
meat.
In	a long casserole dish, layer the Sloppy Joe mixture
across
the bottom.
Drain the corn and cover the meat layer
with
the corn layer.
Spread mashed potatoes over the corn layer.
Top
with	Velveeta.
Bake
at
for 20 minutes.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Brown meat; add onions, garlic and peppers.
Saute lightly. Add all other ingredients, except beans and liquid.
Turn on high to start, then to low and cook all day.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine broccoli and soup.
Pour into casserole dish and top with onions.
Bake in a 325° oven for 20 minutes.

title: stewed squash
directions: Wash and slice squash; put in large pot.
Add all ingredients. Cook squash until tender. If water cooks out before squash is tender, add more.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until thick.
Add oil; mix well.
Sift together flour, soda, powder and cinnamon.
Stir into egg mixture. Add carrots and walnuts.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: spaghetti with meat sauce(crock-pot)
directions: In skillet brown beef and drain.
Put in crock-pot.
In blender place 1 can tomatoes, undrained.
Add the carrot, onions and garlic.
Blend until chopped.
Stir into meat the tomato paste, parsley, bay leaf, sugar, basil, salt, oregano and pepper.
Mix well.
Cover.
Cook on low 8 to 10 hours.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Add other ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Mix and put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: go to bed cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 2 cookie sheets.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add cream of tartar and salt until foamy.
Gradually add sugar (2 tablespoons at a time) and beat until soft peaks form. Stir few drops of green food coloring and oil of mint together. Gently fold in chocolate chips (or mint chips).
Drop by teaspoon 1-inch apart on greased cookie sheets.
Place in preheated oven. Turn off oven, shut oven door and "go to bed."
Takes approximately 8 to 12 hours to complete.
Delicious!

title: chocolate cream cheese frosting
directions: Soften cream cheese with milk.
Add sugar, 1 cup at a time, blending after each addition.
Add chocolate and salt; beat until smooth.

Add more milk, if necessary, for a spreading consistency. Make 1 1/4 cups frosting or enough to cover tops of two 8 or 9-inch layers or top and sides of an 8 x 8 x 2-inch cake or about 2 dozen cupcakes.
Double the recipe to cover tops and sides of two 10-inch layers.

title: potato meat balls
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Then grate potatoes into mixture.
Shape into balls and brown in oil.
Place in casserole and add can of soup and milk.
Bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: husband's cake
directions: Blend shortening and sugar.
Combine tomato soup with water and soda.
Add to shortening mixture, alternately with sifted dry ingredients.
Add raisins and nuts.
Bake in well-greased and floured tube or loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from pan. Allow to cool.
To keep moist, wrap in Saran Wrap.
May also be frozen.

title: crazy cake(makes 1 (8-inch) layer)
directions: Mix together dry ingredients and blend together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° until cake tests done with a toothpick about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Layer first 3 ingredients, then repeat.
Add water, cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and top with cheeses.
Bake for 15 minutes more.

title: eggplant patty casserole
directions: Dice eggplant and cook in small amount of water until done. Drain well.
Put in mixing bowl.
Saute onion until clear and add to eggplant.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add more cracker crumbs if needed to hole together.
Form into patties and fry in small amount of oil.
Lay in casserole dish and cover with mushroom soup. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 patties.

title: zucchini bites
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix all the ingredients; spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown, about 25 minutes.
Cut into rectangles, about 2 x 1-inch.
Refrigerate any remaining appetizers.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: pecan pie (marie's)
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly with sugar, dash of salt, corn syrup and melted butter.
Add pecans; pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Place pecan halves on top to decorate.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 50 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between outside and center of filling comes out clean.
Cool, slice and enjoy.

title: christmas morning cake
directions: Grease Bundt pan; put in 1/2 of the nuts.
Arrange rolls over nuts in layers.
Sprinkle dry pudding mix over rolls.
Cover and let rise overnight.
After rising, melt margarine and pour over pudding.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over mixture. Add nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hot roll recipe
directions: Combine ingredients.
Let rise about 2 hours. Put in refrigerator. Add enough flour when taken out of refrigerator to knead.
Roll out and put in pan to rise (1 to 2 hours). Cook at 350°.

title: zesty carrot strips
directions: Clean and cut carrots into strips.
Cook until tender in salted water.
Place in a large baking dish in an even layer.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach to package directions.
Drain.
In small bowl, lightly beat eggs.
In large bowl, combine spinach, stuffing mix, beaten eggs, cheese, butter and salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly and roll into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes if frozen, 7 to 10 minutes if unfrozen or until lightly browned. Serve immediately or freeze for later use.
Makes about 50.

title: ruby champagne punch
directions: In punch bowl, combine lemon flavored iced tea mix, peach nectar, Rose wine, water and fruit punch; chill.
Just before serving, add pink champagne and ice mold.
Makes about 25 (5 ounce) servings.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Wash eggplant and without peeling it, slice about 3/4-inch thick.
Dip slices first in flour, then into egg mixture, then into breadcrumbs so they are well coated.
Saute them in little olive oil a few at a time until they are nicely browned on both sides; tend them carefully and add oil as needed.
When they are crisp and brown, arrange in baking dish and put slice or two of Swiss or Mozzarella cheese on each one.
Make thick tomato sauce by diluting tomato paste with wine.
Mix tomato sauce with oregano, salt, pepper and crushed garlic; spread 2 to 3 tablespoons on each slice.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese on top of it all.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes and serve steaming hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers together.
Pour mixture over crackers.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter in large pan; saute onion and add broccoli and soup.
Simmer a few minutes.
Add Cheez Whiz and rice.
Put in casserole dish and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Coarsely chop peppers, onions and celery and saute in hot shortening until tender.
Toss in shrimp and cook slowly until pink.
Add tomato paste; season to taste.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes, adding a little water if necessary.
Serve over white rice.
Serves 6.

title: creamy spinach dip
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Chill; serve with assorted vegetable dippers.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: bean bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given until thoroughly blended together.
Bake in a 375° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mom's cherry delight
directions: Mix pie filling, pineapple and Eagle Brand milk.
Mix well. Fold in Cool Whip and mix until well blended.
Put in refrigerator for 1 day before serving.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 400°.

title: crunchy salmon scallop
directions: Cook onions and green peppers in butter until tender.
Stir in flour and seasonings.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly. Cook until thickened, stirring occasionally.

title: grandma twaddle's sugar cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoon and bake at 350°.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: carrots in buttered honey
directions: Drain carrots, reserving liquid.
Measure needed amount of carrot liquid into saucepan.
Add honey, butter, salt and pepper. Cook for a few minutes to blend.
Add carrots and simmer gently until heated through, about 20 minutes.

title: mary's chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese, into large bowl and mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish and sprinkle on cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes approximately 6 servings.

title: bean casserole
directions: Save 1 teaspoon of the taco seasoning for the topping.
Brown hamburger and onions.
Add all ingredients.
Put in casserole dish.

title: sand-dabs
directions: Add ingredients in order given; mix well.

Take small amount and roll in hand to make small round or long roll for cookies. Bake in 325° oven; may need to cook a little longer. Roll cookies in powdered sugar when cookies are taken from the oven.

title: texican chicken
directions: Combine Ro-Tel, soup and onion.
Set aside.
In 2-quart casserole, layer the crushed Doritos, 1/2 of the chicken, 1/2 of the Ro-Tel mixture, 1/2 of the sour cream and 1/2 of the cheese. Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, butter and 1/4 cup sugar.
Press into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 8 minutes.
Combine pineapple, cornstarch and sugar in saucepan.
Cook until thick.
Cool and spread over pretzel mixture.
Whip Dream Whip and add cream cheese.
Spread over pineapple mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: oven fried chicken with lemon sauce
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Shake chicken pieces in flour mixture, arrange chicken, skin side down, in single layer in shallow pan.
Brush well with butter.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Turn chicken, pour sauce which has been refrigerated over chicken.
Bake 30 minutes or longer until chicken is brown and tender.
Serves 4.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Add the eggs.
Sift the flour, cocoa and salt.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: yellow cake
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Set aside.
Blend all other ingredients and beat.
Fold in egg whites.

title: cardamon bread
directions: Beat together first 3 ingredients.
Mix together next 4 ingredients.
Gradually add all together.
Bake in loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: brazilian rice
directions: Saute onion in 2 tablespoons olive oil, then add garlic.
When onion and garlic are transparent, add rice and water.
When rice and water come to a boil, add salt.
Cover and lower temperature to low heat and simmer until no water is in bottom of pan, approximately 20 minutes.

title: luann's mexican lasagne
directions: Cook hamburger; mix in taco seasoning and set aside.

title: cuke dressing
directions: Let vinegar and sugar sit for 1/2 hour.
Add mayo and whisk or blend.
Add milk; mix.
Set this mixture aside and peel and slice cucumbers.
Place cukes in a bowl.
Whisk liquid and pour over the cukes.
Refrigerate.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix ingredients except margarine.
Cut margarine and spread on top of mixture.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Stir 3 or 4 times while baking.

title: old fashioned sweet potato pie
directions: Peel and boil potatoes until tender; mash.
Add all ingredients together, mixing well.
Pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: holiday punch
directions: Pour juice in coffeepot and add 1 cinnamon stick and 1 1/2 teaspoons whole cloves in basket of coffeepot.
Perk.

title: moist meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except 3 tablespoons of catsup; form into loaf.
Put into well-greased loaf pan.
Spread remaining catsup on top of meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut butter crunch pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and corn syrup until thoroughly combined. Add Rice Krispies and stir until well coated.
Press mixture evenly and firmly in bottom and around sides of lightly buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Chill until firm.
Spread softened ice cream evenly in chilled crust.
Freeze.
Makes 8 servings.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook
macaroni
following
directions;
drain.
Return macaroni to pan and immediately stir contents of cheese packet into hot macaroni.
Blend well.
In large bowl combine remaining ingredients with macaroni;
toss
with
fork and season to taste. Chill thoroughly before
serving.
Makes
6 to 8 servings.

title: easy refrigerator pickles
directions: In large jar, alternately layer the sliced cucumbers and onions. In a medium saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, celery seed, salt, mustard seed and turmeric.
Bring to a boil, stirring just until the sugar is dissolved. Pour over the cucumbers and onions. Cover tightly and refrigerate for 24 hours before using.
Stores for several months.
Makes up to seven cups, really crispy and delicious.

title: crunchy corn bread
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together corn muffin mix, rolled oats and cracked wheat.
Add eggs and milk; stir until mixture is moistened. Stir in pecans.
Spread batter evenly in a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Drizzle with the 1 tablespoon syrup.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 20 minutes or until done.
Serve warm, cut into squares, with additional maple syrup or butter or margarine.

title: family meat and vegetable casserole
directions: Place hamburger in large boiler and cook over medium-high heat. Stir until separated and cook about 10 minutes.
Add onion and cook for 5 minutes.
Add tomato soup, water, noodles and juice from mixed vegetables.
Cook until thick, about 10 minutes.
Add vegetables and pour into large casserole dish.
Cover with cheese and bake about 5 or 10 minutes.
Then serve.

title: microwave roasted potato wedges
directions: In 12 x 8-inch baking dish, microwave oil, garlic, salt and paprika on High 30 to 45 seconds until garlic softens.
Stir in brown sauce.
Cut each potato unpeeled lengthwise into 6 wedges. Add to oil, stirring to coat all sides.
Cook, covered, on High 15 to 18 minutes, turning over and rearranging twice.
Discard oil mixture.
Makes 6 servings, 125 calories.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken
until
tender.
Remove from broth, debone and cut into pieces. Add soups, broth and stuffing cubes. Pour into sprayed casserole.	Dot
with
margarine
cut
into small pieces. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mandarin pasta salad
directions: Dressing:
Finely chop ginger root.
In small bowl, whip ginger root, garlic, vinegar, orange juice, vegetable oil, sesame oil, soup mix and sugar.
Cover refrigerated until ready to use.

title: chicken breasts with marsala and prosciutto
directions: Pound chicken breasts between wax paper to 1/4-inch thick. Heat oil and butter in large skillet over medium high heat. Quickly saute chicken, turning once until lightly browned 45 to 60 seconds per side.
Do not crowd the skillet.
Remove from heat and transfer chicken to large plate; sprinkle with sage.
Top each with the prosciutto.
Add Marsala to skillet.
Cook over medium-high heat scraping up brown bits from skillet until liquid is reduced and slightly thickened, about 1 to 2 minutes.
Add cream.
Reduce until thickened; reduce heat to low.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Add chicken and cook, spooning sauce over chicken until heated through.
Arrange on platter; sprinkle with chopped parsley.

title: hungry boy casserole
directions: Saute hamburger, onions, peppers and celery.
Add tomato paste, pork and beans, lima beans, kidney beans, salt and pepper. Top with canned biscuits.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: moon craters
directions: Butter 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Cook corn syrup, sugar and 2 tablespoons margarine in saucepan over low heat for 5 minutes or until mixture comes to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter until smooth. Add cereal, stirring until all pieces are evenly coated.
Press firmly into prepared pan.

title: vegetable fry batter
directions: Stir oil into flour; mix until smooth.
Add egg to milk and add all at once to the oil and flour mix.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Batter will be thin!
Dust food lightly with flour, then dip in batter.
Fry in hot grease.
Drain on paper towel.

title: strawberry rhubarb
directions: Mix gelatin with hot water; dissolve.
Add rhubarb and strawberries.
Chill and serve.

title: butter pecan coconut cake
directions: Mix dry cake mix and frosting mix first.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Let set 10 minutes before removing from the pan.
No frosting is necessary.
Freezes well.

title: venison casserole
directions: Spray 1 large loaf pan with Pam generously.
Slice onions and squash, 1/4-inch thick slices.
Brown venison very slightly in iron "spider."
Line bottom of loaf pan with onion slices, follow with chunks of venison stew beef (tenderloin will also work).
Now, place layer of squash slices.
Alternate like this until you have used all ingredients.
Place 3 sticks margarine on top of casserole.
Cover concoction with black pepper, then cover with layer of tinfoil or lid and place on gas grill at low to medium heat for 45 minutes.
After 45 minutes, remove tinfoil or lid and add 6 ounces of your favorite home brewed barbecue sauce and cook, uncovered, for no longer than 15 minutes.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients until thick.
Stir in Eagle Brand milk and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Line 9 x 13-inch dish with vanilla wafers.
Layer pudding with bananas.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with crushed vanilla wafers.

title: steve's stir-fried chicken or beef, shrimp, etc.
directions: Slice chicken, onion and veggies thinly.
Peel garlic; reserve.
Heat wok or heavy frypan until hot.
Add oil and garlic (preferably peanut).
Heat until smoking.
Keep flame on high. Add veggies in order of denseness (e.g., add broccoli 30 seconds before mushrooms, etc.).
Stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove.
Add 1 more tablespoon oil; heat until smoking.
Add chicken.
Stir just until white.
Add veggies 30 seconds.
Add soy sauce; mix.
Add cube.
Add cornstarch and water.
Stir until thickened.
Add ginger and sesame.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: homemade pizza
directions: Dissolve the yeast in large bowl with 1/2 cup warm water.
Stir the dry milk and salt together with rest of the water until dissolved, then pour over the yeast.
Add olive oil and flour, stirring to mix.
Turn out on a floured surface and let rest (while you wash out and oil the bowl).
Knead the dough until smooth, adding more flour if necessary, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Return to bowl; cover with plastic wrap and let rise until doubled the volume.

title: kolar
directions: Put yeast and sugar
in
bowl.
Pour water over all and let stand.
Cut oleo into
flour and salt.
Put egg yolks into yeast. (Save
egg whites in another bowl.) Pour yeast and egg yolks
into flour, and mix and knead.
Let rise for 45 minutes or until double in size.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Boil meat until tender.
Remove from bones and chop up with hand chopper. To the broth left in pot, add tomato juice, then potatoes which have been cut in bite size pieces.
Boil until tender.
Then add meat back in and add ketchup until the color is a deeper red and thicker looking.
You can add vegetables to your own liking (peas, butterbeans, whatever).

title: cheesecake squares
directions: Combine flour, margarine and brown sugar; mix well to make a crumb mixture.
Add chopped nuts; stir and then press mixture into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, about 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Mix, press into oblong pan and bake for 20 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: southern broccoli
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking dish or 2-quart casserole. Combine broccoli and all other ingredients; pour in baking dish. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hamburger rice pie
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, onions, bell pepper, seasonings and 1/2 can tomato sauce; spread in greased 9-inch pie pan, pushing mixture in sides of pan to form an edge.
The mixture that will be leftover will be used for topping.

title: wassail
directions: Bring to a boil the apple cider, cloves and cinnamon.
Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add orange juice, pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Heat all together.
Add a little sugar, if needed.
Great drink for company during Christmas season.

title: fruit salad with celery seed dressing
directions: Drain canned fruit.
Cut to bite size pieces.
Add sugar and mix well.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Add bananas.

title: james garner's chili patty
directions: Mix these together and freeze in patty form. When ready to cook, make pie crust and cover each frozen patty.
Bake these at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: deviled ham dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and refrigerate at least an hour before using.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.
Great served with Bugles corn snacks.

title: bread pudding (diabetic)
directions: Brush bread lightly with melted oleo; sprinkle with 1 teaspoon sugar substitute and cinnamon.
Quarter each bread slice.
Layer with raisins in a 1 1/2 quart dish coated with cooking spray. Combine eggs, milk, vanilla and remaining 2 teaspoons sugar substitute, pour over bread and raisins.
Place dish in a pan containing 1 inch hot water.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes to 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops, pour off excess grease.
Add celery, onion soup, water and thyme; simmer until chops can be cut with fork. Remove chops, add rice, place chops on top.
Cover and simmer until rice is done.
Watch that rice doesn't stick, may have to add a little water.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed until all liquid has cooked out. Add 1 stick margarine and the Cheez Whiz.
Pour into greased casserole dish and top with crackers and 1 stick melted margarine. Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.

title: yellow-haired girl salad
directions: This recipe is for only one Yellow-Haired Girl Salad (multiply if necessary).
Wash lettuce, pat dry.
Drain 1 pear or peach half and 1 cherry on paper towel.
Wash celery and pinch off leaves. Cut celery into 2-inch long x 1/4-inch wide strips.
Keep 4 strips for salad.
Place pear/peach half, cut side down on salad plate for the head.
Tear the lettuce leaf to look like a dress.
Use the celery strips at the sides and bottom of the lettuce for arms and legs.
Place one raisin at the end of each strip for hands and feet.
Use raisins for eyes, nose and buttons.
Place shredded cheese "hair" around the head.
Cut one cherry smile for the face. Now your Yellow-Haired Girl Salad is ready to eat!

title: special k treats
directions: Combine syrup, peanut butter and brown sugar and boil over low heat (sticks easily so be sure you stir constantly only until it boils).
Remove from heat and stir in the Special K cereal.

title: meat favorite(pork chops or steaks)
directions: Brown in electric skillet, chops or steaks, at 360°.
Pour can of cream of mushroom soup over meat.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serve with heated mushroom soup as sauce.
(Can be done with regular skillet on stove and simmer in oven.)

title: jambalaya
directions: Fry salt pork cubes until lightly browned and pour off fat. Add butter, onion, garlic and bell pepper and saute for a few minutes.
Add sausage, ham, shrimp and herbs and continue to simmer for 8 to 10 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and water or broth. When the mixture starts to boil, add pepper and salt, if needed. Add rice and allow to cook until rice is tender.
Stir from bottom to mix ingredients well.

title: turkey-vegetable casserole
directions: In a colander, run hot water over vegetables for about 1 minute or until thawed.
Drain vegetables well.
Place turkey in a stack, then cut it all at once into thin strips.

title: one step lasagne
directions: Combine sauce with water.
Cover bottom of 9 x 12-inch dish with 1 1/2 cups of sauce.
Arrange layer of uncooked noodles; sprinkle with cheese.
Add sauce, repeat with noodles and cheese. Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: mermaid's delight
directions: Combine tuna, bread crumbs, mayonnaise, eggs and onion.
Mix lightly.
Shape into patties.
Brown on both sides in margarine.

title: microwave english toffee
directions: Combine butter, sugar, water and corn syrup.
Microwave uncovered High power.
Cook 3 minutes, then stir.
Cook 1 minute, then stir.
Cook 4 minutes, then stir and cook 1 minute and stir. Cook up to 1 minute more.
Stir.
Add vanilla and pour onto ungreased cookie sheet or 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and spread evenly.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate until cool.
Turn over and repeat the chocolate chips and nuts again. Cool and break into pieces.

title: double stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes; remove insides.
Mix with butter, cheese, salt and pepper.
Stuff shell.
Sprinkle with more cheese.

title: corn dish
directions: Mix ingredients in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cook 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry jello
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries and crushed pineapple.
Pour 1/2 in casserole dish; let stand firm.
Cover with sour cream and pecans.
Pour the other half on top.
Top with remaining sour cream.

title: fruit salad
directions: Whip until stiff, whipping cream and powdered sugar.
Fold into mixed fruits.
Chill several hours.

title: apple blondies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In large bowl combine butter and sugar with mixer.
Beat about 2 minutes.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Stir in vanilla.

title: pie crust(makes 4)
directions: Mix with mixer or by hand until a ball can be formed.
Do not overwork.
Divide evenly into 4 sections.
Can freeze dough for future use.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and blend well.
Pour into sprayed casserole dish.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Mix together cream cheese and sugar.
Add fruits and their juice.
Add lemon juice.
Fold in Cool Whip and freeze. Freezes and keeps well.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Heat soup.
Mix in cream cheese, onion, mayo and shrimp.
Mix gelatin with 1/2 water and add to mixture.
Put in decorative bowl and set in refrigerator.

title: refrigerator "overnight" cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Form in long rolls.
Refrigerate overnight. Slice thin; bake at 350° until light brown.

title: peanut butter crisscrosses(makes 4 dozen)
directions: Mix butter, Crisco and sugar well; add baking ammonia.
Beat for 20 minutes (important).
Add flour, salt and vanilla.
Fold in coconut.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Cookies are very light in color.
Do not remove from pan immediately or they will crumble.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt and add to eggs.
Blend.
Add corn syrup, butter and vanilla and blend.
Mix in oatmeal and pour into baked pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all together well.
Pour into greased casserole dish and add topping.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: nonfat whipped cream
directions: Dissolve milk in cup of water and scald.
Soak gelatin in cold water.
Combine scalded milk, gelatin and sugar.
