Stir and chill in refrigerator until it jells.
Beat mixture until it acquires consistency of whipped cream.
Add vanilla; beat again.

title: easy broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli and onion until tender.
Mash or blend.
Add mushroom soup and milk.
Season with margarine.
Add salt and pepper.
Garnish with grated cheese.

title: magic biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift dry ingredients in large bowl.
Cut in butter until well blended.
Add yeast and buttermilk. Mix thoroughly.
Turn out on a floured surface and knead 20 to 30 times.
Roll out and cut.
Place on cookie sheet and let raise 10 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken pineapple
directions: Place chicken in roasting pan or large casserole.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Dot butter on and around chicken. Add pineapple, garlic, soy sauce, brown sugar (enough to cover chicken pieces lightly) and ketchup.
Bake for about 40 minutes at 375° or until chicken is tender, basting often.
Serve over rice, flavored with butter and garlic.
Serves 4.
This dish can be completely prepared the day before, refrigerated covered, and popped into oven before company arrives.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, margarine and eggs.
Put oatmeal in blender and blend to powder.
Add remaining ingredients to cream mixture.
Roll into golf ball size balls.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix peaches and butter in pan together.
Mix sugar, flour and milk together until there are no lumps.
Pour into the middle of peaches.
Swirl through peaches.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: chocolate covered cherries(1st prize, montgomery co. fair, maryland)
directions: Drain cherries and let dry on paper towels.
Reserve juice. Combine butter, corn syrup, salt and powdered sugar in a bowl. Add enough cherry juice to make the "dough" hold together.
Form into a ball; wrap in plastic wrap and chill 1 to 2 hours.
Take a marble-size piece of dough, flatten it out and wrap around each cherry.
Put on cookie sheet and chill 1 to 2 hours or until firm. Melt candy coating over low heat.
Holding the stems, dip each cherry into the coating and set into individual candy wrappers. Chill.

title: strawberry freezer jam
directions: Combine fruit and sugar.
Let stand 10 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Bring to a boil pectin and water; boil rapidly for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add berries and stir for about 2 minutes.
Pour into containers, leaving at least 1-inch at top.
Cover.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour. Refrigerate until set.
Store in freezer.
Refrigerate after opened.
Yield: 5 pints.

title: ham and salami sub
directions: In a large frying pan, melt butter over medium heat.
Add salami, ham (cut into small pieces), pickles and onions; cook for about 4 minutes.
Place cheese on top of all ingredients; cook until cheese melts.
Place evenly into sub roll.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: mom's awesome chocolate icing
directions: Bring oleo, milk and cocoa to a full boil in a heavy saucepan, stirring constantly.
Mix in vanilla and confectioners sugar.
Beat by hand until smooth and spread over warm cake. Icing will harden upon cooling.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Drain juice off cherries.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over jello. Set aside and let cool.
Add Cokes and cut up cherries.
Drain juice off pineapple.
Add pineapple to Coke mixture.
Crumble up cheese; add nuts.
Pour in mold and chill.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix well.
Pour in pan. Sprinkle with Ritz crackers.

title: champagne punch
directions: Mix together in a punch bowl.
Garnish with orange slices and ice ring.

title: mary rachel ritchie's homemade ice cream
directions: In ice cream maker can, add eggs, vanilla, sugar, salt and Milnot.
Fill the rest of the can up with milk.
Secure lid and put crushed ice and rock salt down the sides and have at it!
Ooo good eats!

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook hamburger; drain.
In mixing bowl, add hamburger, sour cream, potato soup, cheese and bacon bits.
Mix together.
In casserole dish, layer bottom of bowl with hash browns, then add all other mixed ingredients.
Bake in oven at 325° for 1 hour.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Prepare celery and apples; mix with the nuts in a medium sized bowl.

title: white chocolate party mix
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Slowly melt chocolate in double boiler.
Do not melt directly over heat.
Pour over mixture to coat.
Pour onto wax paper to cool and store in dry container.

title: cornbread doger
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°. Butter a cookie sheet.
Mix corn meal, salt and sugar. Stir in melted butter and boiling water. Continue to stir until mixture is smooth. Wet your hands in cold water. Shape handfuls of mixture into sausage shaped rolls.
Keep hands wet to prevent batter sticking to them.
Place rolls on greased cookie sheet and bake for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Spray bottom of deep pan with Pam.
Spread pork chops on bottom, then pour in potatoes.
Pour in all the soup, then 1/4 cup water.
Season to taste.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or longer if pork chops are thick.

title: seafood casserole
directions: In skillet, saute onion and celery until transparent.
In a large bowl, mix soup, milk, sour cream, shrimp, crab and rice. Add celery and onion.
Add salt, pepper and parsley.
Mix well. Do not beat.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan and bake at 325° until rice is done and firm. Sprinkle cheese on top and finish baking (5 to 10 minutes) until lightly brown.

title: salmon mousse
directions: Drain salmon.
Reserve liquid.
Add water to equal 1/2 cup liquid.
Flake salmon and set aside.

title: coal miner's cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on box. Stir pie filling into cake batter. Bake as directed on box.

title: klug's famous punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Put scoops of sherbet on top.

title: how to freeze okra
directions: Cut up okra.
Put in a 3-quart dish or bowl and microwave for 7 to 10 minutes on High.
Cool and bag.
When ready to cook, thaw okra; add meal, flour, salt and pepper and fry.

title: fudge krispies
directions: Combine chocolate chips, margarine and syrup in medium pan. Stir over low heat until chips are melted.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla and sugar.
Add Rice Krispies and spread into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill and store in refrigerator.

title: bread and butter pickles(crisp)
directions: Wash cucumbers thoroughly.
Do not pare cucumbers and slice thin (1/8-inch).
Add onions, green peppers and whole garlic cloves.
Add salt.
Cover with cracked ice.
Mix thoroughly.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain thoroughly.
Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over cucumber mixture.
Heat just to boil.
Seal in hot sterile jars.
Makes 8 pints.

title: banana cream pie
directions: In saucepan, over medium heat, mix water and cornstarch until dissolved.
Stir
in condensed milk and egg yolks.
Cook and stir until
thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat;
add butter
and vanilla.
Cool
slightly.
Arrange two bananas on bottom
of prepared pastry shell.
Pour filling over bananas; cover.
Chill at
least
four hours or until set.
Spread top with
whipped cream;
garnish
with
remaining banana slices. Refrigerate.

title: spread for sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients.
May keep in refrigerator to use as needed.

title: ice cream sundae pie
directions: Allow ice cream to soften or stir with a spoon until pliable. Spoon into crust. Cover and freeze until firm, about 3 hours. Serve pie wedges with fudge topping, walnuts and whipped cream topped with cherries.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken breasts into bite-size squares (after boiling until tender).
Put into large casserole bowl.
Mix soup, sour cream, broth, salt, pepper and poppy seed.
Pour over chicken, then crush crackers and put over the mixture.
Put melted oleo over, then put into hot oven at 350° until golden brown.

title: hot water pie crust
directions: Place the lard and salt in a large bowl and heat a bit with a tablespoon until lard is softened.
Pour boiling water over the lard and blend again.
Let mixture cool to room temperature, but stir often so water and lard won't separate.
Stir in the flour and form mixture into a ball.
Chill for several hours or overnight, then let the dough sit out at room temperature for about 30 minutes before rolling out.

title: dadio soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Drain. Mix all the remaining ingredients into a large pan. Cook until the potatoes are tender. Salt & pepper to taste. Serve with biscuits & hot sauce.

title: monterey fondue
directions: Trim crusts from 12 slices of bread.
Spread with soft butter and arrange 6 slices in a greased (3-quart) flat pan.
Cover with half of a can of corn, drained, half of a can of chili, seeded and cut in strips, and Jack cheese.
Repeat these four layers. Combine eggs, slightly beaten, and milk and pour over ingredients in casserole dish.
Cover and refrigerate for 4 hours or longer (overnight, if desired).
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes, until puffy and brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: walking salad - kid's style
directions: Mix peanut butter and raisins together.
Place mixture in the cored apple.
Wrap for a good snack on a trip.

title: oven-made caramel corn
directions: Spread corn in a large shallow pan.
Put in oven to keep warm. Combine butter, sugar, syrup and salt in 2-quart heavy saucepan. Place on medium heat; stir until sugar dissolves.
Continue to boil to the firm-ball stage (248°), about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in baking soda.
Syrup will foam.

title: banana dip
directions: In a blender, combine bananas, sugar and honey.
Blend well. Fold in Dream Whip.
Can make 24 hours ahead. Refrigerate.
Cube any fresh fruit.
Serve in hollow half of pineapple.
Dip cubed fresh fruit in banana dip.

title: jello salad
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Mix well with spoon.
Add box of jello (orange is best) and can of crushed pineapple.
Mix together well and refrigerate.

title: mock stroganoff burgers
directions: In covered dish, season ground chuck to your own taste and cook in microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Add onion, mushrooms, green beans, flour and reserved liquid, mixing well.
Heat 5 more minutes.
Add sour cream, stirring well.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Serves 10.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with onion.
Drain.
Mix with other ingredients, except grated cheese.
Pour into greased baking dish; top with grated cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: beet mold
directions: To beet juice, add enough water to make 3 cups.
Bring to boil, dissolve Jell-O.
Add remaining ingredients except beets together. Set aside to thicken.
Add beets.
Chill until firm.

title: easy broccoli quiche
directions: Layer cooked broccoli, onion and green pepper in baking dish. Blend
rest
of
ingredients
and pour over vegetables. Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.	Serves 6.

title: yam and apple casserole
directions: Peel and slice yams 1/2 inch thick.
Cook yams in water on top of stove until tender.
Peel and core apples.
Cut each apple into six rings.
Layer yams and apple rings in a buttered casserole dish.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with mace and sugar.
Bake covered at 350 degrees about one hour.

title: applescotch crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients and mix well.
Pour into an ungreased 9-inch pan.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except onion rings.
Place in casserole dish and top with onion rings.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: spinach casserole (salenchi)
directions: Bring water and olive oil to a boil and add spinach and seasonings.
Lower heat and cook until defrosted.
Drain.
Layer 1/3 of spinach in a one quart casserole dish.
Top with 1/3 mozzarella cheese, 1/3 pepperoni, 1/3 mushrooms, and a sprinkling of bread crumbs.
Repeat two times.
Cover with sliced tomatoes and sprinkle with parmesan cheese.
Bake in a 325 degree oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: corned beef dinner
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water according to package directions.
Drain well.
While macaroni is cooking, mix remaining ingredients except crumbs and margarine.
Gently stir in drained, cooked macaroni.
Pour mixture into a greased 1-quart casserole. Top with bread crumbs and dot with margarine.
Microwave at 70% (Roast) for 6 minutes or bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Good served with Harvard Beets.
Serves 2.

title: sliced pumpkin pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, spices and salt; mix with pumpkin.
Line 9-inch pie plate with crust.
Fill with pumpkin mixture, then dot with butter.
Add top crust, cut slits and seal.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes or until done.
Can be frozen.

title: christmas church salad
directions: Mix and pour into glass pan to set.
"Good."

title: brunch casserole
directions: Brown sausage; add onions.
Drain.
Spread bread crumbs in buttered
baking
dish.
Top with sausage and cheese.
Mix milk, eggs
and
seasonings;
beat well and pour over cheese. Cover
and refrigerate
overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until set.
Serve with fresh fruit bowl.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water. Add strawberries with juice. Mix crumbs, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar. Press into 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes, no longer. Let cool.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Put margarine in bottom of pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch); melt.
Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Put in pan.
Now, add cherries on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Just mix together.
It makes a large amount.
You may not need to use all of the 16 ounce package macaroni.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix well.
Seal lid tightly so you can turn over several times before serving.
Refrigerate.

title: sauerkraut surprise cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream butter or margarine and sugar until light.
Beat in eggs one at a time and add vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cocoa.
Add to creamed mixture alternating with water and beating after each addition.
Stir in sauerkraut.
Turn into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool in pan and frost with sour cream chocolate frosting.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Let stand overnight.
Next day, add the walnuts and whipped cream.

title: quick party punch
directions: Mix together in a punch bowl.
Use chilled pop and punch; can add ice.
Optional for 7-Up:
Can use Squirt or Sprite pop.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Mix all
ingredients.
Cool
over low heat until all of cheese is melted. Serve with choice of chips.

title: bennett's grits
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces and fry in a heavy saucepan. Remove bacon from pan. Add onion, green pepper and celery to bacon drippings. Saute until onion is clear.
Add the canned tomatoes, grits, 1 can of water and bacon to onion mixture.
Cook until grits are done, 15 to 20 minutes.
May have to add a little more water.

title: new orleans creamy pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients over medium heat.
Boil to soft ball stage using candy thermometer.
Remove from heat; stir until thick.
Spoon out on buttered surface.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook both meats, then combine them.
After meats are prepared, add partially cooked vegetables.
Let simmer for quite some time for flavor to mix.
This stew is delicious with cornbread, a salad and dessert.

title: magnificent mustard(great for gift giving)
directions: Mix vinegar and dry mustard and let it stand overnight.
Next morning, stir in well beaten eggs, sugar and salt.
Bring to a slow boil and cook until mixture coats the spoon, stirring constantly.
Cool and refrigerate.
Great on ham or beef sandwiches.

title: pork chops and stuffing
directions: Brown chops on both sides in skillet.
Pour off drippings. Mix bread crumbs, onion, butter, 1/4 cup water and seasoning. Place mounds of stuffing on chops.
Blend soup with 1/3 cup water. Pour over chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick crescent taco pie
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain.
Stir in taco seasoning, water, olives (if desired); simmer 5 minutes.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Place in ungreased 9 or 10-inch pie pan, pressing to form a crust.
Sprinkle corn chips over bottom of crust. Spread meat mixture over corn chips.
Spread sour cream over meat; cover with shredded cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes; until crust is golden brown.
Serve in wedges with shredded lettuce.

title: party hot dogs
directions: Mix jelly and mustard; cut up hot dogs or sausages.
Heat until jelly melts and hot dogs are warm.

title: baked corn
directions: Melt butter or margarine in whatever you are going to bake corn in. Mix sugar and cornstarch. Beat eggs. Add corn, eggs and milk to cornstarch and sugar mix. Add the melted butter or margarine. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: easy mexican chicken
directions: Saute or microwave chicken so it can be shredded or cut in small cubes.
Place Doritos in 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Break Doritos in smaller pieces.
Mix chilies, soup and chicken together. Pour 1/2 of mixture on Doritos.
Sprinkle 1/2 to 1 cup shredded cheese on top.
Pour remaining soup mixture next.
Top with rest of cheese.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: no bake peanut brownies
directions: Combine crumbs, peanuts, sugar and peanut butter, using a whisk.
Melt chocolate and milk over low heat, stirring constantly until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Set aside 1/2 cup chocolate.
Pour remaining chocolate over crumb mixture and stir until well blended.
Spread evenly in a greased 9-inch pan.
Frost with the 1/2 cup chocolate that was set aside.
Chill 1 hour. Yield: 2 1/2 dozen.

title: dill pickles
directions: Heat first 3 ingredients to boiling.
In clean sterilized jars, put cukes, dry mustard, garlic and dill weed.
Pour boiling vinegar mixture over cukes; seal!!!
Do not open for 6 to 8 weeks.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Spread pineapple in bottom of pan.
Spread blueberries on top. Sprinkle sugar over blueberries.
Spread cake mix over this. Pour melted margarine over cake mix.
Top with nuts.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together; let set.

title: no bake lemon pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a large bowl and pour into graham cracker crusts.
Chill and serve.
Makes 2 pies.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese and prepare as directions say in large pan.
Add celery soup, Cheddar cheese soup and tuna; mix well.
Place in casserole dish; top with bread crumbs or crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Make sure your casserole dish is well-greased with butter.

title: cocoa pudding
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Serve when cooled.

title: orange blush punch
directions: Combine orange juice concentrate, cranberry juice and sugar in a serving pitcher; stir well to dissolve sugar.
Chill thoroughly.

title: peach cobbler
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, slice 4 or 5 cups peaches.
Sprinkle half cup sugar over top of peaches.
Over that, sprinkle yellow cake mix.
Sliver 1 stick margarine over all and pour 1 1/2 cups water over the top.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Mix ingredients and form a ball.
Roll out dough to about 1/2-inch thick and cut into pieces.
Fry quickly in vegetable oil, heated to 400°, in an iron skillet.
Turn and brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: thanksgiving dressing
directions: Mix bread, onions and eggs.
Then add sage, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour enough broth (from cooking giblets) in mixture to moisten.
Stuff turkey.

title: gravy train
directions: Brown meat and onions in a skillet.
Drain off excess grease. Add tomatoes and Veg-All; heat until vegetables are warm.
Serve warm with homemade biscuits.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Peel eggs and put in glass jar.
While warm, cover with vinegar from Penrose hot sausages.
Let stand at room temperature for 48 hours, then refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni for 5 to 7 minutes in medium skillet; saute onion.
Mix together drained macaroni, onion, chicken, cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup and 3/4 of cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put into casserole dish, top with remaining cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown ground chuck in large skillet; drain fat.
Dust with flour.
In a bowl, dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water.
Pour over meat.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Mixture will begin to thicken.
Lower heat.
In separate skillet, saute onion and mushrooms in butter and garlic powder.
Add to beef.
Add soup.
Simmer until heated throughout.
Salt and pepper to taste. (I like a lot of black pepper.)
Add sour cream just before serving.
Serve over egg noodles or rice.

title: plains tribes watercress soup
directions: Place chicken consomme and water in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add scallions; reduce heat to low and simmer 3 to 4 minutes.
Add watercress leaves; turn heat off and let soup steep about 1 minute.
Serve at once, seasoning each helping with fresh ground pepper and garnishing, if you like, with slices of lemon or lime.
Or chill soup, skim off fat and serve cold.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Melt oleo and cook in heavy skillet with onions until tender, but not brown. Put half of the onions and oleo mixture in a casserole dish.
Add 1/2 cup grated cheese and 1/2 cup crushed Ritz crackers.
Repeat layer and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Beat cake mix, butter and 1 egg in large mixer bowl at low speed until crumbly.
Press lightly into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Beat 2 eggs, 3/4 cup sugar, 2 teaspoons vanilla and cream cheese until smooth and fluffy.
Spread over crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until set. Mix sour cream, 1/4 cup sugar and remaining tablespoon vanilla. Spread over cheese; cool.
Spread pie filling over sour cream mixture.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.

title: chicken kabobs with peanut sauce
directions: Cut chicken into 3/4-inch pieces. In a large bowl, mix together soy sauce, brown sugar, ginger and garlic. Add chicken pieces to mixture. Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix flour, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper. Sprinkle 1 side of beef steak with half of the flour mixture.
Cut beef into 4 or 5 serving pieces.
Heat shortening in 10-inch skillet until melted.
Cook meat over medium heat until brown, about 15 minutes.
Mix tomatoes with remaining ingredients.
Pour over meat; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until meat is tender, about 45 minutes.

title: plain pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and Crisco.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Beat well after each.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add flavoring. For chocolate cake add 5 tablespoons cocoa.

title: tangy tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill to allow flavor to blend.

title: red french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in bottle or jar.
Shake well. Refrigerate.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Combine and reserve 1 cup mixture for topping.

title: scotch shortbread "cookies"
directions: Mix sugar and butter.
Sift cornstarch with flour (1 cup) and add 2 cups flour; mix in 1 cup flour on counter and pound in with hand (to get air out).
Add not quite last cup of flour (counter should come clean).
Press into jelly roll pan and prick with fork.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
After 10 minutes, flatten with spatula until golden brown.
Slice in 1-inch squares when warm.

title: twix bars
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with a layer of Club crackers.
Mix together and boil for 5 minutes the graham cracker crumbs, milk, margarine, brown sugar and white sugar.
Pour over crackers.
Put on another layer of Club crackers.
Melt in microwave 1 1/2 minutes the peanut butter and chocolate chips. Stir to melt and then frost bars.

title: easy steak and vegetables
directions: In large pan, brown steaks on both sides in hot oil.
Drain off fat.
In bowl, mix together mushroom soup, dry soup mix and water. Place potatoes and carrots in pan with steaks.
Pour soup mixture over meat and vegetables.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: cherry squares
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and beat 2 minutes.
Add the next 3 ingredients.
Stir.
Save out 1 1/2 cups batter.
Spread the remainder of the batter in a large greased jelly roll pan and cover with cherry pie filling.
Pour saved 1 1/2 cups batter on top of the cherry filling.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
When cool, drizzle powdered sugar icing over the top of the cooled cake.

title: 7-up fruit punch
directions: Combine fruit juices, sugar and mint leaves; chill thoroughly (overnight if desired).
Just before serving, add 7-Up and strawberries.
Pour over large cake of ice in punch bowl.
Float thin slices of lemon or lime if desired.
One recipe serves 65 people.

title: blackberry wine cake
directions: Combine cake mix and gelatin.
Add eggs, oil and wine.
Beat on low speed until moistened.
Beat on medium speed for 3 minutes, scraping bowl frequently.
Spray bundt pan.
Sprinkle pecan pieces on bottom of pan, pour batter in pan and bake at 325° for 45-50 minutes.
While cake is baking, make glaze.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Brown diced bacon and onion.
Add flour and stir until smooth. Combine water, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add slowly to bacon and onion mixture.
Add sliced potatoes and mix lightly. Cover tightly and simmer 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: "blondie" brownies
directions: Preparation time: 15 minutes.
Bake time: 27 to 30 minutes.

title: frittata(breakfast casserole)
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and then add the remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish at 350° for 40 minutes or until done. Serves 10.
Great for brunch.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together and marinate for 24 hours.

title: katie's can't fail chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken; remove meat from bones.
Save broth.
Melt margarine; stir into dressing.

In a greased dish (9 x 13-inch), put a layer of dressing crumbs, layer of chicken, layer of mushroom soup (diluted with a can of broth), layer of crumbs, then the rest of the chicken, then the can of chicken soup.
Top with a layer of crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly, about 45 minutes.

title: german chocolate icing
directions: Put all ingredients, but nuts and coconut, in a pot and cook until thick.
Take off stove and let cool.
Add coconut and nuts. Stir and put on cake.

title: fettuccini alfredo
directions: Cook noodles in large Dutch oven with no salt; drain. Melt butter in a saucepan and stir in garlic powder; add to the noodles. Gradually add the whipping cream, 1/2 cup of Parmesan cheese and the sour cream. Cook on low until heated through. Pour into serving dish and sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese. Serves 6 to 8.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Grind all vegetables.
Sprinkle with the salt.
Let stand 4 hours.
Drain.
Cover with water again and drain 2 times.
Combine sugar, vinegar, celery seed, turmeric, mustard seed and water. Bring to boil in large kettle, then add vegetables and bring to boil.
Boil 20 minutes.
Put in pint jars and seal.
Process 10 minutes in hot water bath.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into 6 serving size pieces.
Combine flour and salt; pound 2 tablespoons of the flour mixture into meat.
In a 10-inch skillet, brown meat on both sides in hot shortening; transfer meat to a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Stir remaining flour mixture into pan drippings in skillet.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, onion, celery, carrot and Worcestershire.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes more.
Pour over meat in baking dish.
Bake uncovered in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until meat is tender.
Serve with hot cooked rice or noodles.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix the walnuts, dates or raisins and soda with 1 cup boiling water.
Mix together rest of the ingredients.
Add the mayonnaise mixture to the walnut mixture.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) pans.
Bake 25 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: sweet sour salad dressing("very good")
directions: Grate onions in blender with sugar, mustard, salt and 1/2 the vinegar.
Beat and add oil gradually and remainder of vinegar. Beat until thick.
Add celery seed by hand, stirring with spoon. Store in refrigerator.
Blend on low speed, then high.

title: apricot salad
directions: Heat pineapple juice.
Dissolve Jell-O in juice, then add baby food.
Chill until Jell-O is firm.
Add all other ingredients and mix with electric mixer until well blended.
Keep refrigerated.

title: marinated carrot salad(makes 8 to 10 servings)
directions: In a heavy 8-quart stockpot, combine 4 quarts water, 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 tablespoon salt.
Bring to a boil.
Add carrots.
Cook until crisp-tender, 10 minutes.
Partially fill a large bowl with ice cubes and water.
Drain carrots.
Place into water; stir until cooled.
Drain; set aside.

title: chicken-broccoli rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: In saucepan, heat butter and sugar.
Keep on low heat.
Stir until well blended.
In blender, mix milk, egg, cocoa, cornstarch and salt.
Cornstarch and cocoa should be added while blender is running so that they will not cake up on sides of blender.
When mixture is blended, pour into pan with sugar and butter.
Turn heat to high and stir with French whip constantly until mixture comes to a boil and gets very thick.
Turn burner off and add vanilla extract.
Stir well to blend vanilla into mixture.
Pour into 10-inch baked pie shell.
Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: sunday waffles
directions: Follow recipe on the waffle mix.
Add enough chopped walnuts to make the desired texture.
Cook as package directs.
Serve with real maple syrup or strawberries and whipped cream.
A Sunday treat.

title: 9th street vegetable pie
directions: Saute vegetables in margarine until crisp, but not soft. Drain well.
Add seasonings.
Slice tomatoes and cover bottom of prebaked pie shell.
Add cooked vegetables.
Mix mayonnaise and Mozzarella cheese and spread over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Beat eggs; add water and mix. Add with sugar and flour; mix well.
Put mixture in an unbaked pie shell.
Dot with butter and sprinkle cinnamon over top.
Bake at 425° until rhubarb is tender and filling is set.

title: roquefort grapes
directions: Trim crust from white bread and roll thin.
Dip in melted butter; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and garlic salt.
Roll around one stalk of asparagus.
Put in refrigerator and fasten with toothpick if necessary.
Bake in 400°
oven for 15 minutes.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift and mix flour, sugar, cocoa and baking soda in bowl.
Mix water and mayonnaise; add to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan (greased).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown onion, pepper and beef in oil.
Stir in tomatoes, rice and seasonings.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cover dish with foil while baking.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and soda. Mix in oil, cinnamon and eggs. Add apples. Grease and flour 3 (9-inch) cake pans. Spoon batter equally into the pans. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: marinated chicken parmesan
directions: Marinate chicken in Italian dressing overnight.

title: jesse's pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly in large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients in given order.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: pepper relish
directions: Boil 2 hours.
Seal in sterilized jars.

title: hot rice and mushrooms
directions: Mix well and cook for 45 minutes at 400°.

title: mrs. alfred j. orlidge's fruit cocktail cookies
directions: Drain fruit cocktail; cream butter, brown sugar, white sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with 1/3 cup of cocktail syrup.
Add cocktail and nuts.
Drop by spoonful on greasy cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: "dig-in" edible play dough
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Add flour, a small amount at a time, while stirring to get a good consistency for modeling.
You may have to knead it with your hands to get it thoroughly mixed. Mixture may appear grainy due to the powdered milk.

title: fruit and nut tropical slaw
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 2 tablespoons syrup.
Cut up and set aside.
Combine syrup and lemon juice.
Coat banana with one tablespoon of juice mixture; set rest aside.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and dry pudding mix.
Add pineapple, marshmallows and nuts.
Store in refrigerator until chilled.

title: moist sugar cookies
directions: Refrigerate overnight.
Use soup spoon to drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add to cooked broccoli.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes in a long baking dish.

title: blueberry cream cheese pie
directions: Prepare pie shell.
Remove the cream cheese from the refrigerator and let stand in a bowl about 1/2 to 1 hour or until soft.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Cream or beat with a mixer until fluffy and light.
In a separate bowl, pour out the whipping cream and beat until it looks like regular whipping cream.
Mix into cream cheese mixture.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Putting on 2 separate cookie sheets, bake the wings at 425° for 30 minutes, turning after the first 15 minutes.
Mixing the rest of the ingredients together, this makes a sauce. Taking the chicken out of the oven, putting it in a large enough bowl for all, add 1/2 of the sauce.
Mix the chicken wings and sauce together well, reserving the rest of the sauce for dipping. Enjoy!

title: oceanic chicken
directions: Mix flour, salt, celery salt, garlic salt and nutmeg.
Coat chicken.
Brown chicken in hot butter.
Place in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine syrup from pineapple, soy sauce and sugar. Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.
Baste.
Saute pineapple 15 minutes before chicken is done.
Top with pineapple.

title: old fashioned coconut pie
directions: Blend coconut with milk and let mixture stand.
Cream butter with sugar.
Add eggs, then the coconut and milk.
Pour the mixture into an unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Bake crust at 425° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°. Remove crust from oven.
Brown meat; drain.
Add vegetables; cook until tender.
Stir in sauce. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Spoon half of meat; cover with cheese.
Repeat again, ending with cheese on top. Serve with salad and crusty French bread.

title: swiss cream steak
directions: Melt 4 tablespoons Blue Bonnet stick in a large skillet. Saute onions; remove from skillet.
Put steak strips in flour seasoned with salt, pepper and paprika.
Melt remaining Blue Bonnet in skillet.
Brown well on both sides.
Mix in sauteed onions, water and sour cream until blended.
Cover; cook over medium heat until meat is tender, 35 to 45 minutes.
Uncover; cook until sauce thickens, about 10 minutes.
Serve over hot cooked noodles, if desired.

title: cauliflower italiano
directions: In skillet, cook onion and garlic in salad dressing until tender.
Add cauliflowerets and 1/4 cup water.
Cook, covered, over low heat for 10 minutes.
Add green peppers.
Cook until cauliflower is tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat through.
Serves 6.
